omment": "fixeddashesusing ascript,Script-assisted fixes: perCS1andMOS:ITALICS", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HIV_trial_in_Libya"}
{"title_page": "Yo Yo Honey Singh", "text_new": "{{pp|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Indian rapper}}{{EngvarB|date=November 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Yo Yo Honey Singh\n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = Yo Yo Honey Singh and Huma Qureshi at Celebrity Cricket League 2014 (cropped).jpg\n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| caption          = Yo Yo Honey Singh in 2013\n| birth_name       = Hirdesh Singh\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1983|03|15}}\n| birth_place      = [[Hoshiarpur]], [[Punjab, India|Punjab]], India\n| origin           = [[Delhi]], India\n| genre            = [[Bhangra (music)|Bhangra]], [[Indi-pop]], [[R&B]], [[Reggaeton]], [[Rap]], [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| occupation       = Music composer, Singer, Rapper, Pop Artist and Actor\n| yearsactive      = 2003\u2013present\n| label            = Mafia Mundeer Records, [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| website          = https://instagram.com/yyhsofficial\n| current_members  = Singsta, Hommie Dilliwala, Simar Kaur, Lil Golu\n}}\n\n'''Hirdesh Singh''' (born 15 March 1983), known by his professional name, '''Yo Yo Honey Singh''' or '''Honey Singh''', is an [[Indian people|Indian]] [[Composer|music composer]], [[rapper]], [[Pop music|pop singer]] and [[Actor|film actor]]. He started out as a session and recording artist, and became a [[Bhangra (music)|bhangra]] music producer. Later, he got success with his music and started making songs for [[Bollywood]] films. Currently, he is one of the most paid artist in the Indian music industry.\n\n== Early life ==\n\nSingh was born on 15 March 1983 at [[Hoshiarpur]], [[Punjab, India|Punjab]] to a [[Sikh]] family.<ref>{{cite news|title=Yo yo born in Hoshiarpur, Punjab|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/delhi-based-singer-yo-yo-honey-singh-forays-into-bollywood/1/204302.html|access-date=6 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714153236/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/delhi-based-singer-yo-yo-honey-singh-forays-into-bollywood/1/204302.html#|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Born in Hoshiarpur|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/131129/entertainment-tvmusic/article/honey-singhs-angrezi-beat|access-date=6 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714233644/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/131129/entertainment-tvmusic/article/honey-singhs-angrezi-beat#|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=yo yo's birth place is Hoshiarpur,  Spouse- Shalini Talwar SinghPunjab|url=http://www.abplive.in/movies/2014/01/31/article256646.ece/Few-interesting-things-about-Honey-Singh%E2%80%99s-life#.U7lxl_mSwpo|access-date=6 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714190919/http://www.abplive.in/movies/2014/01/31/article256646.ece/Few-interesting-things-about-Honey-Singh%E2%80%99s-life#.U7lxl_mSwpo#.U7lxl_mSwpo|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Honey Singh to lure Sikh votes|url=http://www.sikh24.com/2014/04/rapper-honey-singh-stands-with-delhi-gurdwara-committee-and-akalis-in-favour-of-bjp/|access-date=13 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140519101906/http://www.sikh24.com/2014/04/rapper-honey-singh-stands-with-delhi-gurdwara-committee-and-akalis-in-favour-of-bjp/#|archive-date=19 May 2014|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Honey Singh's marriage with Sikh rituals at a Gurudwara in Sarojini Nagar|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/news-feed/chunk-ht-ui-punjabsectionpage-dontmiss/yo-yo-honey-singh-married-or-not/article1-1081904.aspx|access-date=13 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714133931/http://www.hindustantimes.com/news-feed/chunk-ht-ui-punjabsectionpage-dontmiss/yo-yo-honey-singh-married-or-not/article1-1081904.aspx#|archive-date=14 July 2014|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> His birth name is Hirdesh Singh. He studied music at the [[Trinity School (Belvedere)|Trinity School]] in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite news|title=Rapper's concert scrapped after online protest over 'obscene' lyrics|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-01-01/india/36093628_1_honey-singh-organisers-online-petition|publisher=TOI|accessdate=8 January 2013|author=Vineet Gill|date=1 January 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130707203457/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-01-01/india/36093628_1_honey-singh-organisers-online-petition#|archive-date=7 July 2013|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> His family later moved to [[Delhi]].<ref>{{cite web|title=yo yo's family moved to delhi from hoshiarpur|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/artists/0dc9c4bc-8bcc-42f1-9033-bec41160377f|access-date=14 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171227235938/https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/artists/0dc9c4bc-8bcc-42f1-9033-bec41160377f#|archive-date=27 December 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\n\nSingh is married to Shalini Talwar Singh, whom he introduced to audiences for the first time on the television show ''[[India's Raw Star]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Rapper Yo Yo Honey Singh admits being married|url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/nation/rapper-yo-yo-honey-singh-admits-being-married_873308.html|accessdate=5 September 2013|newspaper=Zee News|date=1 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130904012307/http://zeenews.india.com/news/nation/rapper-yo-yo-honey-singh-admits-being-married_873308.html#|archive-date=4 September 2013|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Yo Yo Honey Singh: Lesser known facts!|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/music/Yo-Yo-Honey-Singh-Lesser-known-facts/photostory/40987355.cms|accessdate=12 September 2014|newspaper=The Times of India|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140909083105/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/music/Yo-Yo-Honey-Singh-Lesser-known-facts/photostory/40987355.cms#|archive-date=9 September 2014|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn late 2014, Singh disappeared from the music scene, before making a comeback the following year, but mostly avoided the media. In March 2016, he attributed his 18 month long absence from the public to his [[bipolar disorder]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Honey Singh on his bipolar disorder: After sunset, I feared my family|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/music/was-scared-to-face-people-honey-singh-on-his-absence/story-Jptr97v9syqqbdjI1IHR2K.html|accessdate=23 October 2016|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|date=16 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161023203825/http://www.hindustantimes.com/music/was-scared-to-face-people-honey-singh-on-his-absence/story-Jptr97v9syqqbdjI1IHR2K.html#|archive-date=23 October 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Promotion ==\n\nSingh and [[Diljit Dosanjh]]'s song \"[[Lak 28 Kudi Da]]\" reached No. 1 in the BBC Asian Download Charts in May 2011. The song was released as a promotional track for [[Diljit Dosanjh]]'s film ''[[The Lion of Punjab (film)|Lion of Punjab]]''.<ref name=\"punjabiportal.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.punjabiportal.com/articles/honey-singh-diljit-dosanjh-lak-28-kudi-da-no1-in-bbc-asian-download-charts |title=Honey Singh/Diljit Dosanjh&nbsp;\u2013 Lak 28 Kudi Da No:1 in BBC Asian Download Charts |publisher=punjabiportal.com |accessdate=20 November 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121129040627/http://www.punjabiportal.com/articles/honey-singh-diljit-dosanjh-lak-28-kudi-da-no1-in-bbc-asian-download-charts |archive-date=29 November 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nSingh received the ETC award for the best sound in 2006 for his song \"Glassi\", the PTC award for the Best Folk Pop Award 2009 for \"Rebirth\", and the PTC award for Punjab's Best Music Director 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=Yo Yo Honey Singh Mafia Mundeer|url=http://www.desihiphop.com/yo-yo-honey-singh-mafia-mundeer/|publisher=desihiphop|accessdate=8 May 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120508061611/http://www.desihiphop.com/yo-yo-honey-singh-mafia-mundeer/#|archive-date=8 May 2012|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIt has been reported that he was paid the highest fee ever for a Bollywood song (as of 2012) of  {{INRConvert|7|m}} for a song in the films ''[[Cocktail (2012 film)|Cocktail]]'' and ''[[Mastan]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Honey Singh paid highest fee for song|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Punjab/Chandigarh/Honey-Singh-paid-highest-fee-for-song/SP-Article1-849513.aspx|newspaper=Hindustan Times|date=2 May 2012|access-date=21 July 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130903235403/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Punjab/Chandigarh/Honey-Singh-paid-highest-fee-for-song/SP-Article1-849513.aspx|archive-date=3 September 2013|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nSingh topped the chart of trending videos of 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=Honey Singh: The sound of 2012|url=http://www.ndtv.com/article/people/honey-singh-the-sound-of-2012-306689|publisher=NDTV|date=28 December 2012|access-date=28 December 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121228061441/http://www.ndtv.com/article/people/honey-singh-the-sound-of-2012-306689#|archive-date=28 December 2012|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He earned two places on YouTube's list of top 10 trending videos of 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=Yo! Yo! Honey Singh was to 2012 what Dhanush was to 2011.|url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/music/the-medium-and-its-message/article4244861.ece|newspaper=The Hindu|date=28 December 2012|location=Chennai, India|first=Budhaditya|last=Bhattacharya|access-date=28 December 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130103205234/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/music/the-medium-and-its-message/article4244861.ece#|archive-date=3 January 2013|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> His song \"Brown Rang\" made it to the top spot. \"High Heels\", in collaboration with [[Jaz Dhami]], took the fourth spot.<ref>{{cite news|title=Yo! Yo! Honey Singh tops the chart of trending videos of 2012|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/top-youtube-indian-videos-2012-honey-singh/1/238316.html|work=India Today|date=28 December 2012|access-date=28 December 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121231064040/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/top-youtube-indian-videos-2012-honey-singh/1/238316.html#|archive-date=31 December 2012|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nSingh prefers to sing in Hindi and his native language Punjabi rather than English.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-05-09/news-and-interviews/31640719_1_akon-hindi-films-punjabi | work=The Times of India | title=The Times of India: Latest News India, World & Business News, Cricket & Sports, Bollywood}}</ref>\n\nThe Punjabi album ''[[International Villager]]'' was released on 11 November 2011.<ref>[http://www.punjabiportal.com/articles/honey-singh-iv-international-villager Honey Singh's Most Awaited Album] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111205103112/http://www.punjabiportal.com/articles/honey-singh-iv-international-villager# |date=5 December 2011 }} Honey Singh's Most Awaited Album</ref> The track \"Gabru\" from the album, featuring singer J-Star, topped the Asian music charts, including the official BBC Asian charts.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/asiannetwork/chart/downloads/ Asian Network&nbsp;\u2013 The Official Asian Download Chart&nbsp;\u2013 The Official Asian Download Chart] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120107174532/http://www.bbc.co.uk/asiannetwork/chart/downloads/# |date=7 January 2012 }}. BBC (18 February 2012). Retrieved 23 February 2012.</ref>\n\nHe has performed at many college festivals, including  Ansal Institute of Technology and Ramjas College, Delhi.<ref>{{cite news|title=Honey Singh performs at Ansal Institute of Technology|url=http://www.indiancolleges.com/education-news/Honey-Singh-performs-at-Ansal-Institute-of-Technology/1688|accessdate=8 May 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120821024051/http://www.indiancolleges.com/education-news/Honey-Singh-performs-at-Ansal-Institute-of-Technology/1688#|archive-date=21 August 2012|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== Bollywood ===\nHis debut song in [[Bollywood]] films was ''[[Shakal Pe Mat Ja]]'', featuring Gagan Sidhu. Singh charged Rs.&nbsp;7&nbsp;million for a song in the film ''Mastan''. This was the largest amount paid to a song artist in Bollywood to date, making Singh one of the highest-paid musical artists in Bollywood.<ref>[http://www.hindustantimes.com/Punjab/Chandigarh/Honey-Singh-paid-highest-fee-for-song/SP-Article1-849513.aspx Honey Singh paid highest fee for song] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130903235403/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Punjab/Chandigarh/Honey-Singh-paid-highest-fee-for-song/SP-Article1-849513.aspx |date=3 September 2013 }}. ''Hindustan Times'' (2 May 2012). Retrieved 4 May 2012.</ref><ref>[http://daily.bhaskar.com/article/ENT-yo-yo-honey-singh-becomes-the-costliest-bollywood-singer-3203076.html Yo-Yo Honey Singh becomes the costliest Bollywood singer] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130817050132/http://daily.bhaskar.com/article/ENT-yo-yo-honey-singh-becomes-the-costliest-bollywood-singer-3203076.html# |date=17 August 2013 }}. ''Daily Bhaskar'' (2 May 2012). Retrieved 4 May 2012.</ref>\n\nThe song \"Angreji Beat\" from Singh's album ''[[International Villager]]'', featuring [[Gippy Grewal]], was featured in [[Saif Ali Khan]]'s film ''[[Cocktail (2012 film)|Cocktail]]''.\n\nSingh launched his single \"Bring Me Back ft. Spoken Word\" at the Video Music Awards India, which aired on [[MTV India]]. After the show, his song was premiered on the channel.\n\nIn late 2013, he produced songs in the films ''[[Chennai Express]]'' and ''[[Boss (2013 Hindi film)|Boss]]''. He has also had songs in smaller-budget films such as ''[[Mere Dad Ki Maruti]]'', ''[[Bajatey Raho]]'' and ''[[Fugly (2014 film)|Fugly]]''.\n\nIn February 2015 he released the songs \"Birthday Bash\", followed by songs in films including ''[[Gabbar is Back]]'' and ''Bhaag Johnny''.{{citation needed|date=August 2018}}. He faced an accident in 2016 and was unavailable for any project, hence giving his opponents to go through, Honey singh Returned in late 2018 with the song '''MAKHNA''', The song became a major success, also the same year he sung and composed songs for movie [[Baazaar]] & [[Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety]].\n\n=== Acting ===\n\nSingh made his acting debut with [[Baljit Singh Deo]]'s [[Cinema of Punjab|Punjabi]] film ''[[Mirza - The Untold Story]]'' (2012), performing the role of Deesha, a mad gangster. Despite only being a cameo appearance, the role went on to win Singh the PTC Punjabi Film Award for Best Male Debut. The following year, Singh appeared in another [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]] film, this time a [[comedy film|comedy]] by [[Amit Prasher]], ''[[Tu Mera 22 Main Tera 22]]'', as Rolly, a childish and spoilt brat, alongside [[Amrinder Gill]]. This was Singh's first main role in a film.\n\nSingh then made his debut as an actor in Bollywood cinema with the 2014 musical-thriller film ''The Xpose'', alongside Himesh Reshammiya. The film was released on 16 May 2014, to mixed reviews from critics, though it was a box office flop.\n\nIn 2016, Singh starred in the Punjabi action film ''[[Zorawar]]'', directed by Vinnil Markan, which is marketed as one of the most expensive Punjabi films to date. The film was critically acclaimed.\n\n== Criticism of lyrics ==\n\nIn the aftermath of the [[2012 Delhi gang rape case]], the lyrics to some of his songs, which depict violence against women and rape positively, have caused controversy.<ref>{{cite news|title=The nadir of all depravity?|url=http://blogs.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Outraged/entry/the-nadir-of-all-depravity|accessdate=30 December 2012|newspaper=The Times of India|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121230001710/http://blogs.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Outraged/entry/the-nadir-of-all-depravity#|archive-date=30 December 2012|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> A [[first information report]] (FIR) was lodged against Singh for his offensive lyrics, and a group of social activists filed an online petition demanding cancellation of his New Year performance at a [[Gurgaon]] hotel.<ref>{{cite news|title=Gurgaon hotel cancels rapper Honey Singh's concert, FIR in Lucknow over offensive lyrics|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-12-31/lucknow/36078951_1_honey-singh-online-petition-gurgaon-hotel|accessdate=1 January 2013|newspaper=The Times of India}}</ref> After the campaign, Singh's New Year concert was cancelled by the hotel.<ref>{{cite news|title=Anger wave washes away Honey Singh show|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Music/Anger-wave-washes-away-Honey-Singh-show/Article1-983281.aspx|accessdate=1 January 2013|newspaper=Hindustan Times|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130101012513/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Music/Anger-wave-washes-away-Honey-Singh-show/Article1-983281.aspx#|archive-date=1 January 2013|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Singh denies writing these offensive lyrics.<ref name=ibn>{{cite news|title=Honey Singh denies writing offensive lyrics, his lawyer says he is considering legal action|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/honey-singh-denies-writing-offensive-lyrics-his-lawyer-says-he-is-considering-legal-action/313337-3-244.html|accessdate=1 January 2013|publisher=CNN-IBN|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130103120112/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/honey-singh-denies-writing-offensive-lyrics-his-lawyer-says-he-is-considering-legal-action/313337-3-244.html#|archive-date=3 January 2013|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nSingh's song \"Party All Night\" in [[Akshay Kumar]]'s film ''[[Boss (2013 Hindi film)|Boss]]'' was at the centre of a controversy. Producers of the movie had to submit a petition in [[Delhi High Court]] claiming that they had 'muted' an alleged vulgar word in Singh's song. The court  heard a petition filed by lawyer Sanjay Bhatnagar seeking a stay on the film, contending that without the censor board's approval, the song could not be released with such a vulgar word. The petitioner had sought a stay on the release of the film until either the word or the song was deleted from the film.<ref>{{cite news|title=Muted word from Honey Singh's song is not vulgar : Akshay Kumar|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/muted-word-from-honey-singh-s-song-is-not-vulgar-akshay-kumar/article1-1135401.aspx|accessdate=15 October 2013|newspaper=Hindustan Times|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131018064953/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Muted-word-from-Honey-Singh-s-song-is-not-vulgar-Akshay-Kumar/Article1-1135401.aspx#|archive-date=18 October 2013|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nHis work has been perceived{{by whom|date=April 2018}} as being [[Profanity|vulgar]], [[misogyny|misogynist]], promoting [[violence against women]] and a bad influence on youth.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Yo Yo Honey Singh: A vulgar obsession or our own creation?|url = http://blogs.reuters.com/india/2012/12/31/yo-yo-honey-singh-a-vulgar-obsession-or-our-own-creation/|website = Reuters Blogs|date = 31 December 2012|accessdate = 1 January 2016|first = Sankalp|last = Phartiyal|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151226025124/http://blogs.reuters.com/india/2012/12/31/yo-yo-honey-singh-a-vulgar-obsession-or-our-own-creation/#|archive-date = 26 December 2015|url-status = live|df = dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = The biggest problem with Yo Yo Honey Singh: Bollywood's embrace of him|url = http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/the-biggest-problem-with-yo-yo-honey-singh-bollywoods-embrace-of-him-574960.html|website = Firstpost|date = 1 January 2013|accessdate = 1 January 2016|last = Chintamani|first = Gautam|language = en-US|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160104211257/http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/the-biggest-problem-with-yo-yo-honey-singh-bollywoods-embrace-of-him-574960.html#|archive-date = 4 January 2016|url-status = live|df = dmy-all}}</ref> There have been reactions in print to Singh, such as from [[Annie Zaidi]], who wrote  \"[[An Open Letter to Honey Singh]]\" in January 2013,<ref name=\"TSG-20130105\">{{cite news|url=http://www.sunday-guardian.com/artbeat/an-open-letter-to-honey-singh-2|title=An open letter to Honey Singh|last=Zaidi|first=Annie|date=5 January 2013|work=The Sunday Guardian|accessdate=4 February 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141130004722/http://www.sunday-guardian.com/artbeat/an-open-letter-to-honey-singh-2#|archive-date=30 November 2014|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> and Sandipan Sharma, who wrote \"Thanks for the crassness: An open letter to Honey Singh from a parent\" in July 2014.<ref name=\"HT-20140723\">{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/music/thanks-for-the-crassness-an-open-letter-to-honey-singh-from-a-parent/article1-1242802.aspx|title=Thanks for the crassness: An open letter to Honey Singh from a parent|last=Sharma|first=Sandipan|date=23 July 2014|work=The Hindustan Times|accessdate=4 February 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205105646/http://www.hindustantimes.com/music/thanks-for-the-crassness-an-open-letter-to-honey-singh-from-a-parent/article1-1242802.aspx#|archive-date=5 February 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 2014, he and singer [[Raftaar (Singer)|Raftaar]] were in dispute over whether Raftaar should receive credit for the lyrics of the song \"Yeh Fugly Fugly Kya Hai\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/yo-yo-caught-in-a-fresh-controversy-with-punjabi-rapper-raftaar/1/359720.html|title=Yo Yo caught in a fresh controversy with Punjabi rapper Raftaar|website=India Today|accessdate=28 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171216182313/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/yo-yo-caught-in-a-fresh-controversy-with-punjabi-rapper-raftaar/1/359720.html#|archive-date=16 December 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nSingh was reportedly in rehab in Chandigarh, according to [[Jasbir Jassi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/chandigarh/i-met-honey-singh-in-a-rehabilitation-centre-jasbir-jassi/article1-1383703.aspx|title=I met Honey Singh in rehab in Chandigarh, says Jasbir Jassi|date=24 August 2015|website=hindustantimes.com|accessdate=28 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150917075326/http://www.hindustantimes.com/chandigarh/i-met-honey-singh-in-a-rehabilitation-centre-jasbir-jassi/article1-1383703.aspx#|archive-date=17 September 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> However, Jassi later denied saying this.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abplive.in/movies/yo-yo-honey-singh-in-a-chandigarh-rehab-battling-drug-addiction--127480|title=Yo Yo Honey Singh in a Chandigarh rehab battling drug addiction?|first=|last=admin|website=abplive.in|accessdate=28 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Albums ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n |-\n ! scope=\"col\" |Year\n ! scope=\"col\" |Album\n ! scope=\"col\" |Artist\n ! scope=\"col\" |Music director\n\n |-\n | 2005\n | ''Peshi''\n | Bill Singh\n | rowspan=\"21\" | Honey Singh\n\n |-\n | rowspan=\"2\" | 2006\n | ''The Beat''\n | Ashok Masti\n |-\n | ''Surma''\n | Bopaz\n\n |-\n | 2008\n | ''Rebirth''\n | Raj Brar\n\n |-\n | rowspan=\"3\" | 2009\n | ''[[The Next Level]]''\n | [[Diljit Dosanjh]]\n\n |-\n | ''Lock Up''\n | [[Preet Harpal]]\n\n |-\n | ''The Beginning''\n | Resham Singh Anmol\n\n |-\n | rowspan=\"6\" | 2010\n | ''The Crown''\n | Raja Baath\n\n |-\n | ''Dream''\n | Dolly Singh\n\n |-\n | ''Khalaas&nbsp;\u2013 The Pure''\n | Inderjit Nikku\n\n |-\n | ''The Folkstar''\n | [[Nishawn Bhullar]]\n\n |-\n | ''The Rising Queen''\n | Rimz J\n\n |-\n | ''Zanjeer -The Game Changer''\n | Karran Jesbir\n\n |-\n | rowspan=\"7\" | 2011\n | ''Hard Work''\n | Bai Amarjit\n\n |-\n | ''Never Done Before''\n | Balli Riar\n\n |-\n | ''Singing Between the Lines'' (song: \"Jaan Mangdi\")\n | [[Jassi Sidhu]]\n\n |-\n | ''[[Alfaaz&nbsp;\u2013 The Boy Next Door]]''\n | Alfaaz\n\n |-\n | ''Jatt Soorme''\n | Garry Hothi\n\n |-\n | ''Talwar'' (song: \"Kawan diyan daaran\")\n | [[Gippy Grewal]]\n\n |-\n | ''[[International Villager]]''\n | Various\n\n |-\n | 2012\n | ''Born This Way''\n | Varinder Brar\n |-\n | 2014\n |''[[Desi Kalakaar]]''<ref name=\"Indialive.today\">{{cite web|url=http://indialive.today/yo-yo-honey-singh-stars-with-sonakshi-sinha-in-desi-kalakaar/|title=Yo Yo Honey Singh Clubs in with Sonakshi Sinha for Desi Kalakaar|work=indialive.today|accessdate=16 August 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819083904/http://indialive.today/yo-yo-honey-singh-stars-with-sonakshi-sinha-in-desi-kalakaar/|archive-date=19 August 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n | Honey Singh, [[Lil Golu]]\n|Honey Singh\n|}\n\n=== Single Music Videos ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n |-\n ! scope=\"col\" |Year\n ! scope=\"col\" |Track\n ! scope=\"col\" |Artist\n ! scope=\"col\" |Music director\n |-\n |2006\n |''Begani Naar''\n |[[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]]\n | rowspan=\"16\" | Honey Singh\n |-\n | rowspan=\"3\" | 2011\n | ''[[Lak 28 Kudi Da]]''\n | [[Diljit Dosanjh]], Honey Singh\n |-\n |''[[Brown Rang]]''\n |Honey Singh\n |-\n |''Chamak Challo'' (a remix)\n |J-Star, Honey Singh\n |-\n| rowspan=\"6\" |2012\n| ''15 Saal'' (''No Official Video'')\n | Diljit Dosanjh, Honey Singh\n |-\n | ''High Heels''\n | [[Jaz Dhami]], Honey Singh\n |-\n | ''Siftan''\n | Money Aujla, Honey Singh\n |-\n | ''Break Up Party''\n | Leo, Honey Singh\n |-\n | ''Satan''\n | Honey Singh, [[Neha Kakkar]]\n |-\n |''This Party Getting Hot''\n | [[Jazzy B]