oday.com/story/news/world/2017/01/24/iraqi-forces-secure-eastern-mosul-islamic-state/96997934/ |archivedate=24 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"250 families\" /><ref name=\"residual\">{{cite web |url=https://www.stripes.com/news/civilians-return-to-mosul-as-iraqi-forces-mop-up-residual-isis-fighters-1.479136 |title=Civilians return to Mosul as Iraqi forces mop up residual ISIS fighters |work=Stars and Stripes |date=21 July 2017 |accessdate=22 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170721230747/https://www.stripes.com/news/civilians-return-to-mosul-as-iraqi-forces-mop-up-residual-isis-fighters-1.479136 |archivedate=21 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"July 22 airstrike log\" />\n* By 3 December 2016, the ISF and Peshmerga had captured a total of {{convert|5677|km2|sqmi|sp=us}} and 369 villages from ISIL.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/mosul-offensive-federal-police-forces-liberate-61-villages-1400-square-kilometers/ |title=Mosul offensive: Federal Police forces liberate 61 villages and 1400 square kilometers |date=30 October 2016 |work=iraqinews.com |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031162303/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/mosul-offensive-federal-police-forces-liberate-61-villages-1400-square-kilometers/ |archivedate=31 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2016/10/30/battle-mosul-intensifies-shiite-militias-join-fray/93017632/ |title=Battle for Mosul intensifies as Shiite militias join fray |work=USA Today |first=John |last=Bacon |date=30 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031014644/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2016/10/30/battle-mosul-intensifies-shiite-militias-join-fray/93017632/ |archivedate=31 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Joint Forces Continue to Advance, Liberating More Areas in Mosul |first=Mira |last=Rojkan |url=http://www.basnews.com/index.php/en/news/iraq/315744 |publisher=BasNews |date=4 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220082722/http://www.basnews.com/index.php/en/news/iraq/315744 |archivedate=20 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* Iraqi forces launch [[Western Nineveh offensive (2017)|another offensive]] on 25 April 2017, to secure the Iraqi\u2013Syrian border<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2017/04/25/iraqi-troops-capture-largest-neighborhood-western-mosul/100873154/ |title=Iraqi troops capture largest neighborhood in western Mosul |work=USA Today |agency=[[Associated Press]] |date=25 April 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170427102813/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2017/04/25/iraqi-troops-capture-largest-neighborhood-western-mosul/100873154/ |archivedate=27 April 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* The [[Popular Mobilization Forces|PMU]] captures 360 villages, and an area of around 14,000 square kilometres to west of Mosul, by mid-June 2017<ref>{{cite news |url=http://en.abna24.com/news/middle-east/hashd-shaabi-west-mosul-operation-ends-successfully_835614.html |title=Hashd Shaabi: West Mosul operation ends successfully |date=10 June 2017 |publisher=Ahlul Bayt News Agency |agency=[[Tasnim News Agency]]\n|url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170801213852/http://en.abna24.com/news/middle-east/hashd-shaabi-west-mosul-operation-ends-successfully_835614.html |archivedate=1 August 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n| combatant1  = {{flagicon|Iraq}} '''[[Iraq]]'''<ref name=\"guardian1017\">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/oct/17/iraqi-forces-begin-assault-on-isis-stronghold-mosul |title=Mosul offensive: forces launch mass attack on Iraqi city in bid to oust Isis |first1=Martin |last1=Chulov |first2=Hannah |last2=Summers |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017145243/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/oct/17/iraqi-forces-begin-assault-on-isis-stronghold-mosul |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Kurdistan}} [[Iraqi Kurdistan]]\n{{flagicon image|Seal of Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve.svg|size=25px|border=}} '''[[Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve|CJTF\u2013OIR]]'''\n* {{flag|United States}}<ref name=\"guardian1017\" />\n* {{flag|France}}<ref name=\"guardian1017\" />\n* {{flag|United Kingdom}}<ref name=\"guardian1017\" />\n* {{flag|Canada}}<ref name=\"Canadatroops\">{{cite news |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/harjit-sajjan-supporting-troops-iraq-1.3809333 |title=Canadian troops supporting Kurds in fight to free Mosul from ISIS |first=Lee |last=Berthiaume |publisher=CBC News |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018094059/http://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/harjit-sajjan-supporting-troops-iraq-1.3809333 |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Australia}}<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.skynews.com.au/news/top-stories/2016/10/17/australia-to-have-role-in-battle-for-mosul.html |title=Australia to have role in battle for Mosul |publisher=Sky News Australia |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018205626/http://www.skynews.com.au/news/top-stories/2016/10/17/australia-to-have-role-in-battle-for-mosul.html |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Germany}}<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2016/9/24/germany-will-take-part-in-the-battle-for-mosul |title=Germany 'will take part in the battle for Mosul' |work=Al-Araby Al-Jadeed (The New Arab) |date=24 September 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220064908/https://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2016/9/24/germany-will-take-part-in-the-battle-for-mosul |archivedate=20 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Turkey}}<ref name=\"aj1023\" />\n* {{flag|Netherlands}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.defensie.nl/actueel/nieuws/2019/12/20/23-militairen-onderscheiden-voor-uitzonderlijke-inzet-tijdens-missies|title=23 Militairen onderscheiden voor uitzonderlijke inzet tijdens missies|last=|first=|date=19 December 2019|website=Defensie|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n{{flag|Iran}}<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.csmonitor.com/World/Middle-East/2016/1029/What-role-is-Iran-playing-in-the-Mosul-offensive |title=What role is Iran playing in the Mosul offensive? |first=David |last=Iaconangelo\n|work=[[Christian Science Monitor]] |date=29 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107232617/http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Middle-East/2016/1029/What-role-is-Iran-playing-in-the-Mosul-offensive |archivedate=7 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><br />'''Supported by:'''<br />{{flag|Pakistan}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1345432/pakistan-helped-iraq-in-defeating-is-says-iraqi-envoy |title=Archived copy |access-date=10 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190212070604/https://www.dawn.com/news/1345432/pakistan-helped-iraq-in-defeating-is-says-iraqi-envoy |archive-date=12 February 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref><br />{{flag|Hezbollah}}<ref name=\"Hezbollah\">{{cite news |url=http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2016/11/hezbollah-fighters-train-iraqi-shiite-militants-near-mosul.php |title=Hezbollah fighters train Iraqi Shiite militants near Mosul |first=David |last=Daoud |work=[[Long War Journal]] |date=5 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161106165104/http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2016/11/hezbollah-fighters-train-iraqi-shiite-militants-near-mosul.php |archivedate=6 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n| combatant2  = '''{{Flag|Islamic State|size=23px}} '''\n| commander1  = {{flagicon|Iraq}} Lt. Gen. Abdul Amir Rashid Yarallah<br />{{small|(Commander of the opera