ikes and shelling,<ref>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/sporadic-clashes-in-iraqs-mosul-after-victory-declaration/2017/07/11/3aab681e-6603-11e7-94ab-5b1f0ff459df_story.html Clashes shake west Mosul after victory over IS declared] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170716072901/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/sporadic-clashes-in-iraqs-mosul-after-victory-declaration/2017/07/11/3aab681e-6603-11e7-94ab-5b1f0ff459df_story.html |date=16 July 2017}}</ref><ref name=200ISIS>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/world/200-isis-fighters-may-remain-in-mosul-us-commander-says|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170716072759/http://www.foxnews.com/world/2017/07/13/200-isis-fighters-may-remain-in-mosul-us-commander-says.html|url-status=dead|title=200 ISIS fighters may remain in Mosul, US commander says|first=Lucas|last=Tomlinson|date=13 July 2017|archivedate=16 July 2017|website=Fox News}}</ref><ref name=facespockets>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKBN19Z0SR?il=0 |title=Iraq faces pockets of Islamic State resistance in Mosul's Old City |publisher=[[Reuters]] |date=14 July 2017 |accessdate=15 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170716072733/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKBN19Z0SR?il=0 |archivedate=16 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> until 20 July.<ref name=\"ISIL remnants\">{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/remnants-intensify-suicide-attacks-mosuls-old-city/ |title=IS remnants intensify suicide attacks in Mosul's Old City |publisher=Iraqi News |date=20 July 2017 |accessdate=21 July 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170802062113/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/remnants-intensify-suicide-attacks-mosuls-old-city/ |archive-date=2 August 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"250 families\">{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/250-families-still-besieged-mosuls-old-city-army-officer/ |title=250 families still besieged in Mosul's Old City: Army officer |publisher=Iraqi News |date=20 July 2017 |accessdate=21 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170723072303/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/250-families-still-besieged-mosuls-old-city-army-officer/ |archivedate=23 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"residual\"/> The Iraqi military and [[United States Central Command|CENTCOM]] claimed that these were \"clearance operations.\"<ref name=\"daysafter\">{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKBN19X14G |title=Iraq strikes Islamic State in Mosul days after declaring victory |publisher=Reuters |date=12 July 2017 |accessdate=12 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170712095349/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKBN19X14G |archivedate=12 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=centiraq>{{Cite web|url=https://www.inherentresolve.mil/Media-Library/News-Releases/Article/1241247/iraqi-security-forces-liberate-mosul/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170716170956/http://www.centcom.mil/MEDIA/NEWS-ARTICLES/News-Article-View/Article/1241247/iraqi-security-forces-liberate-mosul/|url-status=dead|title=Iraqi Security Forces liberate Mosul|archivedate=16 July 2017|website=U.S. Central Command}}</ref>\n| campaignbox = {{Campaignbox Iraqi Civil War (2014\u20132017)}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Battle of Mosul (2016\u201317)''' ({{lang-ar|\u0645\u0639\u0631\u0643\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0648\u0635\u0644}}, ''Ma'rakat al-Maw\u1e63il''; {{lang-ckb|\u0634\u06d5\u0695\u06cc \u0645\u0648\u0648\u0633\u06b5}}, ''\u015eeriy M\u00fbsil'') was a major military campaign launched by the Iraqi Government forces with allied militias, the [[Kurdistan Regional Government]], and international forces to retake the city of [[Mosul]] from the [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|Islamic State]] (ISIL),<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dunford |first1=Daniel |title=Battle for Mosul: UN prepares for aftermath 'chaos' |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37643228 |publisher=BBC News |date=15 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161015025231/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37643228 |archivedate=15 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=The Coming Battle for Mosul |url=https://www.nytimes.com//2016/10/15/opinion/the-coming-battle-for-mosul.html |work=The New York Times |date=14 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161015135834/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/15/opinion/the-coming-battle-for-mosul.html |archivedate=15 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=von Hein |first1=Matthias |title=Interview: Battle for Mosul likely to lead to power struggle |url=http://www.dw.com/en/interview-battle-for-mosul-likely-to-lead-to-power-struggle/a-36049145 |work=[[Deutsche Welle]] |date=14 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161015121521/http://www.dw.com/en/interview-battle-for-mosul-likely-to-lead-to-power-struggle/a-36049145 |archivedate=15 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> which had [[fall of Mosul|seized the city]] in June 2014.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Yan |first1=Holly |last2=Muaddi |first2=Nadeem |title=Why the battle for Mosul matters in the fight against ISIS |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/17/middleeast/battle-for-mosul/ |publisher=CNN |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018205707/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/17/middleeast/battle-for-mosul/ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> During the [[international military intervention against ISIL|military intervention against ISIL]], Iraqi and [[Peshmerga]] forces had already made unsuccessful [[Mosul offensive (2015)|attempts to retake the city in 2015]] and [[Mosul offensive (2016)|again in 2016]], despite limited gains.\n\nThe offensive, dubbed '''Operation \"We Are Coming, Nineveh'''\" ({{lang|ar|\u0642\u0627\u062f\u0645\u0648\u0646 \u064a\u0627 \u0646\u064a\u0646\u0648\u0649}}; ''Qadimun Ya Naynawa''),<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0628\u0627\u062f\u064a \u064a\u0637\u0644\u0642 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0639\u0645\u0644\u064a\u0627\u062a \u062a\u062d\u0631\u064a\u0631 \u0646\u064a\u0646\u0648\u0649 \u062a\u0633\u0645\u064a\u0629 \"\u0642\u0627\u062f\u0645\u0648\u0646 \u064a\u0627 \u0646\u064a\u0646\u0648\u0649\" \u0623\u0645\u0646 |url=http://www.alsumaria.tv/news/182977/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B7%D9%84%D9%82-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%B9%D9%85%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B1-%D9%86%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%88%D9%89-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%8A/ar |publisher=[[Al Sumaria]] |date=17 October 2016 |language=Arabic |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019170941/http://www.alsumaria.tv/news/182977/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B7%D9%84%D9%82-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%B9%D9%85%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B1-%D9%86%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%88%D9%89-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%8A/ar |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"atlantic1020\">{{cite news |last1=Winter |first1=Charlie |title=How ISIS Is Spinning the Mosul Battle |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2016/10/isis-mosul-propaganda-iraq-kurds-peshmerga/504854/ |work=[[The Atlantic]] |date=20 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020230854/http://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2016/10/isis-mosul-propaganda-iraq-kurds-peshmerga/504854/ |archivedate=20 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> began on 16 October 2016, with forces besieging ISIL-controlled areas in the [[Nineveh Governorate]] surrounding Mosul,<ref name=\"ibt1016\">{{cite news |last1=Haddad |first1=Tareq |title='US military has started shelling Mosul' says Peshmerga commander |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/us-military-has-started-shelling-mosul-says-peshmerga-commander-1586650 |work=[[International Business Times]] |date=16 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018173357/http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/us-military-has-started-shelling-mosul-says-peshmerga-commander-1586650 |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"bbc1017\">{{cite news |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraq and Kurdish troops make gains |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37679325 |publisher=BBC News |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017132532/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37679325 |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"cnn1016\">{{cite news |last1=Blau |first1=Max |last2=Park |first2=Madison |last3=McLaughlin |first3=Eliott C. |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraqi forces close in |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/17/middleeast/mosul-isis-operation-begins-iraq/index.html |publisher=CNN |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017071928/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/17/middleeast/mosul-isis-operation-begins-iraq/index.html |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> and continued with Iraqi troops and Peshmerga fighters engaging ISIL on three fronts outside Mosul, going from village to village in the surrounding area in the largest deployment of Iraqi troops since the [[2003 invasion of Iraq]].<ref name=\"dt1017\">{{cite news |title=What is the battle for Mosul? Everything you need to know about the fight to liberate Isil's last bastion of power in Iraq |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/17/what-is-the-battle-for-mosul-isils-last-bastion-of-power-in-iraq/ |work=The Telegraph |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017134739/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/17/what-is-the-battle-for-mosul-isils-last-bastion-of-power-in-iraq/ |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The battle was also the world's single largest military operation in nearly 15 years, the largest since the [[2003 invasion of Iraq]].<ref name=\"decade\"/>\n\nAt dawn on 1 November 2016, [[Iraqi Special Operations Forces]] entered the city from the east.<ref name=\"rferl1101\">{{cite news |title=Iraqi Troops Launch Ground Assault On Eastern Neighborhood Of Mosul |url=http://www.rferl.org/a/mosul-iraq-attack-assault-/28087932.html |publisher=[[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]] |date=1 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161101165042/http://www.rferl.org/a/mosul-iraq-attack-assault-/28087932.html |archivedate=1 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Met with fierce fighting, the government advance into the city was slowed by elaborate defenses and by the presence of civilians,<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi forces say IS defences, civilians hamper Mosul advance |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-11-06/mosul-iraqi-forces-say-is-defences-and-civilians-hamper-advance/7999152 |publisher=[[ABC News (Australia)]] |date=6 November 2016 |language=en-AU |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161106094152/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-11-06/mosul-iraqi-forces-say-is-defences-and-civilians-hamper-advance/7999152 |archivedate=6 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> but the [[Prime Minister of Iraq|Iraqi Prime Minister]] [[Haider al-Abadi]] declared \"full liberation of eastern side of Mosul\" on 24 January 2017.<ref name=\"Eastern Mosul liberated\">{{cite web |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/25/c_136010100.htm |title=Iraqi PM declares full liberation of eastern side of Mosul |publisher=Xinhua |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170131191736/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/25/c_136010100.htm |archivedate=31 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi troops began their offensive to recapture western Mosul on 19 February 2017.<ref name=CNNwestmosul>{{cite web |url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/02/19/middleeast/iraq-starts-operation-to-drive-isis-out-of-west-mosul/index.html |title=Iraq starts operation to drive ISIS out of west Mosul |author1=Faith Karimi |author2=Hamdi Alkhshali |author3=Basma Atassi |publisher=CNN|access-date=2017-02-19 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170219053207/http://www.cnn.com/2017/02/19/middleeast/iraq-starts-operation-to-drive-isis-out-of-west-mosul/index.html |archivedate=19 February 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 July 2017, the Iraqi Prime Minister arrived in Mosul to announce the victory over ISIL, and an official declaration of victory was proclaimed on 10 July.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2017/07/10/iraqi-forces-have-retaken-mosul-u-s-backed-coalition-confirms/465022001/ |title=Iraqi forces have fully retaken Mosul, U.S.-backed coalition confirms |work=USA Today |date=10 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170711103419/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2017/07/10/iraqi-forces-have-retaken-mosul-u-s-backed-coalition-confirms/465022001/ |archivedate=11 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"formally declares victory\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-40558836 |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraq PM Abadi formally declares victory |publisher=BBC News |date=10 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170711051709/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-40558836 |archivedate=11 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"completely freed\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/07/10/middleeast/mosul-what-next/index.html |title=Mosul completely freed from ISIS: What's next for the city left in ruins? |publisher=Cable News Network |date=10 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170710233845/http://www.cnn.com/2017/07/10/middleeast/mosul-what-next/index.html |archivedate=10 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"clearing\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-40555602 |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraqi troops clearing last IS militants |publisher=BBC News |date=10 July 2017 |accessdate=10 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170710160801/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-40555602 |archivedate=10 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> However, heavy clashes continued in a final pocket of ISIL resistance in the Old City, for almost another 2 weeks.<ref name=\"sporadic\">[http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/mosul-isis-victory-airstrike-1.4198966 Sporadic clashes continue in Mosul after victory declared] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170711111135/http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/mosul-isis-victory-airstrike-1.4198966 |date=11 July 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"250 families\" /><ref name=\"residual\" /><ref name=\"July 22 airstrike log\">{{cite web|url=http://www.inherentresolve.mil/Portals/14/Documents/Strike%20Releases/2017/07July/20170722%20Strike%20Release.pdf?ver=2017-07-22-060600-830|title=Strike Release: July 22, 2017|publisher=[[Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve|CJTF\u2013OIR]]|date=22 July 2017|access-date=29 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612140142/http://www.inherentresolve.mil/Portals/14/Documents/Strike%20Releases/2017/07July/20170722%20Strike%20Release.pdf?ver=2017-07-22-060600-830|archive-date=12 June 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> It was estimated that removing the explosives from Mosul and repairing the city over the next 5 years would require $50 billion (2017 USD),<ref name=\"numbers\">{{cite web |url=https://www.stripes.com/news/middle-east/by-the-numbers-the-fight-against-islamic-state-in-iraq-1.477461 |title=By the numbers: The fight against Islamic State in Iraq |publisher=Stars and Stripes |date=11 July 2017 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170711084915/https://www.stripes.com/news/middle-east/by-the-numbers-the-fight-against-islamic-state-in-iraq-1.477461 |archivedate=11 July 2017 |df=dmy-all |access-date=12 July 2017}}</ref> while Mosul's Old City alone would cost about US$1 billion to repair.<ref name=\"completely freed\" />\n\nThe Battle of Mosul was concurrent with the [[Battle of Sirte (2016)|Battle of Sirte]] in Libya and the [[Raqqa campaign (2016\u201317)|Raqqa campaign]] conducted by the [[Syrian Democratic Forces]] (SDF) against [[Raqqa|ISIL's capital city]] and stronghold in [[Syria]].<ref>{{cite news |title=This is why everything you've read about the wars in Syria and Iraq could be wrong |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/syria-aleppo-iraq-mosul-isis-middle-east-conflict-assad-war-everything-youve-read-could-be-wrong-a7451656.html |date=2 December 2016 |work=The Independent |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161202123936/http://www.independent.co.uk/voices/syria-aleppo-iraq-mosul-isis-middle-east-conflict-assad-war-everything-youve-read-could-be-wrong-a7451656.html |archivedate=2 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n{{TOC limit|4}}\n\n== Background ==\n[[File:2016.08 Mosul area.svg|{{largethumb}}|Map of the territorial control during the 2016 Mosul offensive, as of August 2016]]\n=== General background ===\n{{Main|Fall of Mosul|Mosul offensive (2015)}}\nMosul is Iraq's second most populous city. It [[fall of Mosul|fell]] to 800\u20131,500 ISIL militants in June 2014, because of the largely [[Sunni Islam|Sunni]] population's deep distrust of the primarily [[Shia]] Iraqi government, and its corrupt armed forces.<ref name=\"lemonde1017\" /><ref name=\"reuters1016\">{{cite news |title=Factbox: Once-tolerant Mosul site of Iraq push against Islamic State |url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/factbox-once-tolerant-mosul-iraq-push-against-islamic-232623181.html |accessdate=18 October 2016 |agency=Reuters |date=16 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019012341/https://www.yahoo.com/news/factbox-once-tolerant-mosul-iraq-push-against-islamic-232623181.html |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> It was in the [[Great Mosque of al-Nuri (Mosul)|Great Mosque in Mosul]] that ISIL leader [[Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi]] declared the beginning of ISIL's self-proclaimed \"caliphate\" which spans Iraq and Syria.<ref name=\"reuters1016\" /> The original population of 2.5 million has fallen to approximately 1.5 million after two years of ISIL rule. The city was once extremely diverse, with ethnic minorities including [[Armenians in Iraq|Armenians]], [[Yazidis]], [[Assyrian people|Assyrian]], [[Iraqi Turkmen|Turkmen]], and [[Shabak people|Shabak]] people, all of whom have suffered and continue to suffer considerably under the (majority Sunni Arab) Islamic State.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bulos |first1=Nabih |title=The battle in Iraq that could turn the tide against Islamic State: The fight for Mosul is about to begin |url=https://www.latimes.com/world/middleeast/la-fg-iraq-mosul-20161002-snap-story.html |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=2 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017163757/http://www.latimes.com/world/middleeast/la-fg-iraq-mosul-20161002-snap-story.html |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Mosul remains the last stronghold of ISIL in Iraq,<ref name=\"nyt1017\">{{cite news |last1=Gordon |first1=Michael R. |last2=Arango |first2=Tim |title=Kurdish Troops Advance on ISIS-Held Villages East of Mosul |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/17/world/middleeast/iraq-isis-mosul-battle.html |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=The New York Times |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017120726/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/17/world/middleeast/iraq-isis-mosul-battle.html |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> and the anticipated offensive to reclaim it was promoted as the \"mother of all battles.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ensor |first1=Josie |title=Isil 'launches suicide attacks' on Kurdish forces in Mosul as bloody battle to retake terror group's Iraq stronghold begins |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/17/bloody-battle-to-retake-mosul-begins-as-iraqi-forces-move-to-wip2/ |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017132203/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/17/bloody-battle-to-retake-mosul-begins-as-iraqi-forces-move-to-wip2/ |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi army begins 'mother of all battles' to reclaim Mosul |url=https://www.msn.com/en-gb/news/world/iraqi-army-begins-mother-of-all-battles-to-reclaim-mosul/ar-AAj2lYY?li=BBoPWjQ |accessdate=17 October 2016 |publisher=msn.com |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018212622/http://www.msn.com/en-gb/news/world/iraqi-army-begins-mother-of-all-battles-to-reclaim-mosul/ar-AAj2lYY?li=BBoPWjQ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Hughes |first1=Chris |title=ISIS under devastating attack as 'mother of all battles' begins in Mosul |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/isis-under-devastating-attack-mother-9064344 |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=The Mirror |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019082003/http://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/isis-under-devastating-attack-mother-9064344 |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Wedeman |first1=Ben |title=Will ISIS be pushed easily from Mosul? |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/07/11/middleeast/iraq-mosul-isis-conflict-explainer/ |accessdate=17 October 2016 |publisher=CNN |date=25 August 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018213104/http://www.cnn.com/2016/07/11/middleeast/iraq-mosul-isis-conflict-explainer/ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== Preparations for the battle ===\n{{Main|Mosul offensive (2016)}}\nIn the weeks leading up to the ground offensive, the US-led [[Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve|CJTF \u2013 OIR]] coalition bombed ISIL targets, and the Iraqi Army made gradual advances on the city.<ref name=\"dt1017\" /> [[Royal Air Force]]'s [[General Atomics MQ-9 Reaper|Reaper]] drones, [[Eurofighter Typhoon|Typhoons]], and [[Panavia Tornado|Tornados]] targeted \"[[rocket launchers]], [[ammunition]] [[Stockpile (military)|stockpiles]], [[artillery]] pieces and [[Mortar (weapon)|mortar]] positions\" in the 72 hours before the ground assault began.<ref>{{cite news |title=Isil 'launches suicide attacks' on Kurdish forces in Mosul as bloody battle to retake terror group's Iraq stronghold begins |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/17/bloody-battle-to-retake-mosul-begins-as-iraqi-forces-move-to-wip2/ |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017132203/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/17/bloody-battle-to-retake-mosul-begins-as-iraqi-forces-move-to-wip2/ |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[Airborne leaflet propaganda|Leaflets]] dropped on the city by the Iraqi military advised young male residents to \"rise up\" against ISIL when the battle began.<ref name=\"nyt1017\" /> To prepare defenses against the assault, ISIL operatives dug 4&nbsp;m<sup>2</sup> holes around the city, which they planned to fill with burning oil to reduce visibility<ref name=\"dt1017\" /> and slow advances.<ref name=\"ptv\">{{cite web |url=http://www.presstv.com/Detail/2016/10/17/489433/Iraq-Mosul-five-villages |title=PressTV-LIVE UPDATE: Final push to retake Mosul |work=presstv.com |accessdate=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017144408/http://presstv.com/Detail/2016/10/17/489433/Iraq-Mosul-five-villages |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> They also built hundreds of elaborate tunnels in the villages surrounding Mosul, rigged with explosives and booby-traps, and laid [[improvised explosive device]]s (IEDs) and mines along the roads.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dehghanpisheh |first1=Babak |title=Abandoned villages on road to Mosul rigged with tunnels and bombs |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKCN12J1OX |accessdate=3 November 2016 |agency=Reuters |date=20 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104010848/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKCN12J1OX |archivedate=4 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> There was considerable concern that ISIL might employ chemical weapons against soldiers and civilians.<ref name=\"aj1030\">{{cite news |last1=de Bretton-Gordon |first1=Hamish |title=Chemical dangers in the battle for Mosul |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/opinion/2016/10/chemical-dangers-battle-mosul-161026091359992.html |accessdate=3 November 2016 |publisher=Al Jazeera |date=30 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161102105412/http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/opinion/2016/10/chemical-dangers-battle-mosul-161026091359992.html |archivedate=2 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nAccording to Iraqi sources, the assault towards Mosul was being waged from Al-Khazer axis (east of Mosul), [[Mosul Dam]] (northern axis), [[Bashiqa|Baashiqa]] axis (eastern axis), Al-Qayyarah axis (southern axis), and Talul el-Baj- Al-Khadr axis (southwestern axis).<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://jcpa.org/battle-mosul-aftermath/ |title=The Battle for Mosul and Its Aftermath |date=2016-10-26 |newspaper=Jerusalem Center For Public Affairs |language=en-US|access-date=2016-11-13 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114002054/http://jcpa.org/battle-mosul-aftermath/ |archivedate=14 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== Forces involved in the offensive ===\n[[File:Lt. Gen. Stephen J. Townsend Qayyarah September 2016.jpg|thumb|U.S. Lt. Gen. [[Stephen J. Townsend]], commander of the Combined Joint Task Force, at [[Qayyarah Airfield West]], 22 September 2016]]\nAbout 3,000\u20135,000 ISIL fighters were estimated to be in Mosul city, according to the United States Department of Defense.<ref name=\"AV\">{{cite AV media |people=Peter Cook, various reporters |date=17 October 2016 |title=Defense Department Briefing |url=https://www.c-span.org/video/?417070-1/peter-cook-briefs-reporters-military-operations-mosul | access-date = 17 October 2016 |time=23:02 |location=Arlington, Virginia, United States |publisher=[[C-SPAN]] |quote=The estimate [of ISL fighters in Mosul] I've seen was\u2026 3,000 to 5,000\u2026 We've seen other numbers that are higher. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018045203/https://www.c-span.org/video/?417070-1%2Fpeter-cook-briefs-reporters-military-operations-mosul |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Other estimates ranged as low as 2,000 and high as 12,000 ISIL fighters.<ref name=\"lemonde1017\" /><ref name=\"auto2\" /> ''[[Mosul Eye]]'' estimated approximately 8,000\u20139,000 fighters loyal to ISIL, with \"half of them... highly trained, and the rest... either teenagers or not well trained. About ten percent of the fighters are foreign (Arabs and non-Arabs). The rest are Iraqis. Most are from Nineveh's townships and districts.\"<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite news |last=Wright |first=Robin |date=27 October 2016 |title=The Secret Eye Inside Mosul |url=https://www.newyorker.com/news/news-desk/the-secret-eye-inside-mosul |newspaper=The New Yorker |access-date=29 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161028135139/http://www.newyorker.com/news/news-desk/the-secret-eye-inside-mosul |archivedate=28 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Prior to the start of the battle, in late September 2016, it was estimated that around 20,000 ISIL fighters were living in Mosul,<ref name=\"push deeper\">{{cite web |url=http://samachartoday.com/2016/09/27/forces-push-deeper-into-key-is-held-northern-town/ |title=Forces push deeper into key IS-held northern town |publisher=Samachar Today |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170227155947/http://samachartoday.com/2016/09/27/forces-push-deeper-into-key-is-held-northern-town/ |archivedate=27 February 2017 |df=dmy-all |access-date=26 February 2017}}</ref> many of whom later fled the city to Syria and Ar-Raqqah, when Iraqi forces began to besiege Mosul.\n\nThe Iraqi-led coalition was initially estimated by [[CNN]] to have 94,000 members,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/17/middleeast/mosul-isis-operation-begins-iraq/ |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraqi forces inflict 'heavy losses' on ISIS |last1=Walsh |first1=Nick |last2=Blau |first2=Max |last3=Grinberg |first3=Emanuella |last4=Hume |first4=Tim |date=17 October 2016 |website=CNN |access-date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017194025/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/17/middleeast/mosul-isis-operation-begins-iraq/ |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> but this number was later revised upward to 108,500;<ref name=\"Mosul battle forces\">{{cite news |last=Hume |first=Tim |date=25 October 2016 |title=Battle for Mosul: How ISIS is fighting to keep its Iraqi stronghold |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/24/middleeast/iraq-mosul-isis-tactics/ |newspaper=CNN |access-date=29 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161029044039/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/24/middleeast/iraq-mosul-isis-tactics/ |archivedate=29 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> 54,000 to 60,000 [[Iraqi security forces]] (ISF) soldiers, 16,000 [[Popular Mobilization Forces]] (PMF) fighters (also referred to as PMU), and 40,000 [[Peshmerga]] (including approximately 200 Iranian Kurdish female fighters from the [[Kurdistan Freedom Party]] (PAK))<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dehghanpisheh |first1=Babak |last2=Georgy |first2=Michael |title=Kurdish women fighters battle Islamic State with machineguns and songs |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-mosul-womenfighters-idUSKBN12Y2DC |accessdate=5 November 2016 |agency=Reuters |date=4 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104163756/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-mosul-womenfighters-idUSKBN12Y2DC |archivedate=4 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> were deployed in the battle.<ref name=\"cnn1017\" /><ref name=\"ptv\" /> The Iraqi and Peshmerga forces deployed for the Mosul operation were estimated to have outnumbered the ISIL militants present by 10-to-1.<ref name=\"decade\"/>\n\nAmong the PMF units, the [[Nineveh Plain Protection Units]] composed of [[Assyrian people|Assyrians]] are among the paramilitary forces in the government coalition.<ref name=\"NPF\">{{cite news |url=http://www.syriacsnews.com/npf-declaring-participation-mosul-offensive/ |title=NPF declaring their participation to Mosul offensive |publisher=Syriac International News Agency |date=18 October 2016 |accessdate=18 October 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018133332/http://www.syriacsnews.com/npf-declaring-participation-mosul-offensive/ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Lodge |first1=Carey |title=Christian Forces Will 'Fight Relentlessly' To Free Mosul From ISIS |url=http://www.christiantoday.com/article/christian.forces.will.fight.relentlessly.to.free.mosul.from.isis/98274.htm |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Christian Today |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20171010054612/https://www.christiantoday.com/article/christian.forces.will.fight.relentlessly.to.free.mosul.from.isis/98274.htm |archivedate=10 October 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Shia militias, including several brigades of the paramilitary organization Hashd al-Shaabi, the [[Peace Companies]], [[Kata'ib Hezbollah]], the [[League of the Righteous]], the [[Badr Organization]], Saraya Ashura, Saraya Khorasani, [[Kata'ib al-Imam Ali]], [[Harakat Hezbollah al-Nujaba]] and [[Turkmen Brigades (PMU)|Turkmen Brigades]] also took part.<ref name=\"PMF cut off\">{{cite web |url=http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2016/11/iraqi-popular-mobilization-forces-attempt-to-cut-off-islamic-state-in-mosul.php |title=Iraqi PMF attempts to cut off Islamic State in Mosul |publisher=The Long War Journal |author1=Amir Toumaj |date=4 November 2016 |accessdate=5 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105133800/http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2016/11/iraqi-popular-mobilization-forces-attempt-to-cut-off-islamic-state-in-mosul.php |archivedate=5 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"lobs1017\" /> The [[Ezidi]] community of the Sinjar region contributed the [[Sinjar Resistance Units]] (YB\u015e) and [[\u00caz\u00eedxan Women's Units]] (YJ\u00ca),<ref name=Ezidi>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/isis-iraq-kurdish-trained-yazidi-women-launch-operation-revenge-free-women-a7416906.html |title=All-female Yazidi militia launches operation for revenge on Isis in northern Iraq |publisher=The Independent |date=14 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114170145/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/isis-iraq-kurdish-trained-yazidi-women-launch-operation-revenge-free-women-a7416906.html |archivedate=14 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> which are operating in concert with Sunni Arab [[Shammar]] tribal militias and [[People's Defence Forces]] (HPG) of the [[Kurdistan Workers' Party]] (PKK).<ref>{{cite news |title=On patrol with the Sinjar Resistance Units |url=https://widerimage.reuters.com/story/on-patrol-with-the-sinjar-resistance-units |accessdate=1 December 2016 |agency=Reuters |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161202035410/https://widerimage.reuters.com/story/on-patrol-with-the-sinjar-resistance-units |archivedate=2 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Other [[Assyrian people|Assyrian]] forces involved in the planned offensive included the [[Nineveh Plain Forces]] (NPF) and [[Dwekh Nawsha]], who are allied to the Peshmerga.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.syriacsnews.com/npf-declaring-participation-mosul-offensive/ |title=NPF declaring their participation to Mosul offensive \u2013 Syriac International News Agency |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018133332/http://www.syriacsnews.com/npf-declaring-participation-mosul-offensive/ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all |access-date=18 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yMcLRJT7CAA |title=Dwekh Nawsha Document the what happened in Batnaya.P9 |date=16 January 2017 |via=YouTube |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170203075731/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yMcLRJT7CAA |archivedate=3 February 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Peshmerga soldiers prepare to conduct a combined arms live-fire exercise near Erbil, Iraq.jpg|left|thumb|[[Peshmerga]] soldiers prepare to conduct a combined arms live-fire exercise with an Italian instructor near [[Erbil]], on 12 October 2016.]]\nAn [[Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve|international coalition]] of 60 nations, led by the United States, is supporting Iraq's war against ISIL, providing logistical and air support, intelligence, and advice.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraq, Syria Make Significant Strides Countering ISIL, Press Secretary |url=http://www.defense.gov/News/Article/Article/976204/iraq-syria-make-significant-strides-countering-isil-press-secretary-says |accessdate=18 October 2016 |publisher=U.S. Department of Defense |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018233950/http://www.defense.gov/News/Article/Article/976204/iraq-syria-make-significant-strides-countering-isil-press-secretary-says |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The international coalition forces are headquartered {{convert|60|km}} south of Mosul at [[Qayyarah Airfield West]] (or Q-West) in [[Qayyarah]], which was retaken from ISIL in June.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Forey |first1=Samuel |title=Bataille de Mossoul: reportage \u00e0 Qayyarah, dans le QG de la coalition |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/international/2016/10/16/01003-20161016ARTFIG00175-qayyarah-dernier-verrou-strategique-avant-mossoul.php |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=Le Figaro |date=16 October 2016 |language=fr-FR |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017124143/http://www.lefigaro.fr/international/2016/10/16/01003-20161016ARTFIG00175-qayyarah-dernier-verrou-strategique-avant-mossoul.php |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> About 560 U.S. troops from the [[101st Airborne Division]] were deployed to Q-West for the battle, including command and control elements, a security detachment, an airfield operations team, and logistics and communications specialists.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sisk |first1=Richard |title=101st Soldiers Deploying to Bolster Fight Against ISIS in Iraq |url=http://www.military.com/daily-news/2016/08/08/101st-soldiers-deploying-to-bolster-fight-against-isis-in-iraq.html |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Military.com |date=8 August 2016 |language=en |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019001248/http://www.military.com/daily-news/2016/08/08/101st-soldiers-deploying-to-bolster-fight-against-isis-in-iraq.html |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The U.S. deployed [[HIMARS]] rocket launchers and [[M777 howitzer]]s, manned by the 101st's 2nd Brigade Combat Team and the Golf Company, 526th Brigade Support Battalion. The French army deployed four [[CAESAR self-propelled howitzer|CAESAR]] howitzers and 150 to 200 soldiers at Qayyarah, with 600 more French troops announced at the end of September.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Chapleau |first1=Philippe |title=Les quatre Caesar de Qayyarah ont d\u00e9j\u00e0 donn\u00e9 de la voix |url=http://lignesdedefense.blogs.ouest-france.fr/archive/2016/09/29/les-caesar-de-qayyarak-ont-tonne-les-20-27-et-29-septembre-16885.html |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Ouest-France |date=29 September 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018210759/http://lignesdedefense.blogs.ouest-france.fr/archive/2016/09/29/les-caesar-de-qayyarak-ont-tonne-les-20-27-et-29-septembre-16885.html |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> An additional 150 French soldiers are in [[Erbil]], east of Mosul, training Peshmerga.<ref name=\"lobs1017\">{{cite news |title=Bataille de Mossoul : qui participe \u00e0 la reconqu\u00eate ? |url=http://tempsreel.nouvelobs.com/monde/20161017.OBS9927/bataille-de-mossoul-qui-participe-a-la-reconquete.html |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=L'Observer |date=17 October 2016 |language=fr-FR |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018231500/http://tempsreel.nouvelobs.com/monde/20161017.OBS9927/bataille-de-mossoul-qui-participe-a-la-reconquete.html |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The aircraft carrier ''[[French aircraft carrier Charles de Gaulle|Charles de Gaulle]]'', with a squadron of 24 [[Dassault Rafale|Rafale M jets]], was deployed from [[Toulon]] to the Syrian coast to support the operation against ISIL through airstrikes and reconnaissance missions; 12 other Rafale jets are operating out of [[French Air Force]] bases in Jordan and the [[United Arab Emirates]] (UAE).<ref>{{cite news |last1=Licourt |first1=Julien |title=Premi\u00e8res op\u00e9rations depuis le Charles-de-Gaulle avant l'offensive sur Mossoul |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/international/2016/09/30/01003-20160930ARTFIG00055-irak-la-coalition-debute-son-offensive-sur-mossoul.php |accessdate=19 October 2016 |work=Le Figaro |date=30 September 2016 |language=fr-FR |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020035332/http://www.lefigaro.fr/international/2016/09/30/01003-20160930ARTFIG00055-irak-la-coalition-debute-son-offensive-sur-mossoul.php |archivedate=20 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"cnncdg\">{{cite news |last1=Pleitgen |first1=Fred |title=On board the French nuclear carrier battling ISIS |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/17/middleeast/france-nuclear-carrier-mosul-iraq-isis/ |accessdate=19 October 2016 |publisher=CNN |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019044158/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/17/middleeast/france-nuclear-carrier-mosul-iraq-isis/ |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> 80 [[Special Operations Command (Australia)|Australian special forces]] soldiers and 210 [[Canadian Special Operations Forces Command]] (CANSOFCOM) soldiers were also deployed to assist the Peshmerga. In addition, the [[Canadian Forces]] [[21 Electronic Warfare Regiment]] was also reported to be in the area, working to intercept and relay ISIL communications, while a Role 2 [[Canadian Forces Health Services Group|Canadian Army field hospital]] with 60 personnel has been set up to treat Peshmerga casualties.<ref name=\"Okra\">{{cite web |last1=Greene |first1=Andrew |title=Islamic State: Australia's special forces to assist Iraq military in battle for Mosul |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-10-17/australian-special-forces-to-assist-military-operation-to-retak/7939556 |website=ABC News |publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation |accessdate=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017131032/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-10-17/australian-special-forces-to-assist-military-operation-to-retak/7939556 |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"CANSOFCOM\">{{cite web |last1=Chase |first1=Steven |title=Canadian forces providing crucial support in battle to recapture Mosul |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/politics/canadian-forces-providing-crucial-support-in-battle-to-recapture-mosul/article32403507/ |website=The Globe and Mail |accessdate=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018235608/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/politics/canadian-forces-providing-crucial-support-in-battle-to-recapture-mosul/article32403507/ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n[[File:An Iraqi soldier attending a course on chemical, biological, radiological and nuclear defense training at Camp Taji.jpg|thumb|An Iraqi soldier during a course on chemical, biological, radiological and nuclear defense training at [[Camp Taji]]. Coalition forces expressed fears ISIL may use chemical weapons during the Battle of Mosul.]]\nThe [[Arab Socialist Ba'ath Party \u2013 Iraq Region|Ba'ath loyalists]] group, known to be led by [[Saddam Hussein]]'s former vice president [[Izzat Ibrahim al-Douri]], issued a statement before the start of operations calling for the people of the city to start an uprising against ISIL and announced that they will fight the \"terrorist organization.\"<ref name=\"Naqshabandi \u2013 Bawwabat Al-Arab\">{{cite web |title=\u062a\u062d\u0631\u064a\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0648\u0635\u0644.. \u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0642\u0634\u0628\u0646\u062f\u064a\u0629 \u064a\u0646\u0641\u064a \u0627\u0634\u062a\u0628\u0627\u0643 \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0634\u0645\u0631\u0643\u0629 \u0645\u0639 \"\u062f\u0627\u0639\u0634\" |url=https://www.albawabhnews.com/2168253 |website=Bawwabat Al-Arab |accessdate=20 October 2016 |language=Arabic |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021013000/http://www.albawabhnews.com/2168253 |archivedate=21 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Naqshabandi \u2013 Azzaman\">{{cite web |title=\u0627\u0644\u0647\u062c\u0648\u0645 \u064a\u0646\u062c\u0632 \u0623\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0641\u0647 \u0641\u064a \u0633\u0647\u0644 \u0646\u064a\u0646\u0648\u0649 |url=http://www.azzaman.com/?p=180750 |website=Azzaman |accessdate=20 October 2016 |language=Arabic |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018180406/http://www.azzaman.com/?p=180750 |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n== The battle ==\n{{Main|Timeline of the Battle of Mosul (2016\u201317): Phase One|Timeline of the Battle of Mosul (2016\u201317): Phase Two|Timeline of the Battle of Mosul (2016\u201317): Phase Three}}\n=== October: Phase One and initial advances ===\n[[File:M109A6 Paladin at Qayyarah October 2016.jpg|thumb|upright=1.3636364|A U.S. Army [[M109A6 Paladin]] conducts a fire mission at [[Qayyarah Airfield West]], in support of the Iraqi security forces' push toward Mosul, 17 October 2016.]]\nOn 16 October 2016, Iraqi Prime Minister Haider al-Abadi declared the beginning of the assault to recapture the city of Mosul.<ref name=\"cnn1016\"/> Officials reported howitzers firing on ISIL targets later that day.<ref name=\"ibt1016\"/> The main assault began on 17 October at approximately 6{{nbsp}}a.m., local time,<ref name=\"nyt1017\"/> with shelling and the arrival of armored vehicles to the front lines.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/17/world/middleeast/in-isis-held-mosul-beheadings-and-hints-of-resistance-as-battle-nears.html Iraqi Forces Attack Mosul, Seeking to Dislodge Islamic State {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170125101753/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/17/world/middleeast/in-isis-held-mosul-beheadings-and-hints-of-resistance-as-battle-nears.html |date=25 January 2017}} ''The New York Times'' (16 October 2016)</ref> The Peshmerga in the Khazir region, east of Mosul, started the ground assault by advancing on ISIL-held villages from three fronts, while Iraqi security forces advanced from the south.<ref>[http://www.deccanchronicle.com/world/middle-east/171016/iraqs-kurdish-forces-launch-fresh-push-east-of-mosul.html Iraq's Kurdish forces launch fresh push east of Mosul] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018001849/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/world/middle-east/171016/iraqs-kurdish-forces-launch-fresh-push-east-of-mosul.html |date=18 October 2016}} ''Deccan Chronicle'' (17 October 2016)</ref> Iraqi troops advanced on the [[Bartella]] area east of Mosul while ISIL fighters fired mortars at Peshmerga.<ref name=\"wsj1017\">{{cite news |last1=El-Ghobashy |first1=Tamer |last2=Nabhan |first2=Ali A. |last3=Kesling |title=Iraq Forces Begin Battle to Dislodge ISIS From Mosul |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/islamic-state-braces-as-iraq-prepares-mosul-offensive-1476642193 |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=[[The Wall Street Journal]] |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017003332/http://www.wsj.com/articles/islamic-state-braces-as-iraq-prepares-mosul-offensive-1476642193 |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The President of KRG, [[Massoud Barzani]], said that Peshmerga and Iraqi government fighters retook 200 square kilometers (80 square miles) from ISIL on the first day of fighting.<ref name=\"aj1017\">{{cite news |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraqi forces claim gains against ISIL |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/10/battle-mosul-iraqi-forces-claim-gains-isil-161017125543255.html |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=Al Jazeera |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018001559/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/10/battle-mosul-iraqi-forces-claim-gains-isil-161017125543255.html |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi government officials reported inflicting severe casualties and destruction of equipment on ISIL forces in the Hamdaniya district southeast of Mosul. Wounded ISIL fighters reported to have been transferred to their de facto capital [[Raqqa]], in Syria, for medical aid.<ref name=\"cnn1017\"/> Some ISIL fighters were reported shaving their beards and getting rid of their Afghan uniforms.<ref>{{cite news |title=ISIS families flee Mosul amid intense aerial bombing |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/isis-families-flee-mosul-amid-intense-aerial-bombing/ |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=Iraqi News |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018071546/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/isis-families-flee-mosul-amid-intense-aerial-bombing/ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Mosul's \"Freedom Bridge\" was destroyed in the fighting.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hennessy-Fiske |first1=Molly |title=A 'decisive battle': Determination energizes Iraqi forces in fight to retake Mosul from Islamic State |url=https://www.latimes.com/world/middleeast/la-fg-iraq-mosul-20161017-snap-story.html |accessdate=4 November 2016 |work=Los Angeles Times |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105160849/http://www.latimes.com/world/middleeast/la-fg-iraq-mosul-20161017-snap-story.html |archivedate=5 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Battle of Mosul - Iraqi security forces transport combat equipment 2.jpg|thumb|Iraqi security forces transport two [[BMP-1]] infantry fighting vehicles to tactical assembly areas with assistance from the 313th Movement Control Battalion forward element, on 18 October 2016, near [[Makhmur, Iraq]]]]\nOn 18 October, the Iraqi government declared to have captured 20 villages from ISIL within 24 hours of fighting.<ref>{{cite news |last=Chmaytelli |first=Maher |date=18 October 2016 |title=Iraqi forces announce progress in Mosul offensive |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKBN12I0A6 |newspaper=Reuters |location=Baghdad |access-date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018065946/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKBN12I0A6 |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On the southern front, Iraqi troops retook several villages near [[Qayyarah]], including al-Sirt, Bajwaniya, al-Hud and al-Mashraf, and parts of the al-Hamdaniya District southeast of Mosul,<ref name=\"liberate new villages\" /> as well as the al-Shura District.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi forces liberate al-Shura district south of Mosul |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-forces-liberate-al-shura-district-south-mosul/ |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Iraqi News |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019152529/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-forces-liberate-al-shura-district-south-mosul/ |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[Iraqi Federal Police]] also regained control of 56 oilfields in the Qayyarah district.<ref name=\"liberate new villages\">{{cite news |last1=Goran |first1=Baxtiyar |title=Iraqi army liberate new villages in second day of Mosul operation |url=http://www.kurdistan24.net/en/news/620fd9a5-43c2-437f-98b8-5b234e130eee/iraqi-army-liberate-new-villages-in-second-day-of-mosul-operation- |accessdate=20 October 2016 |publisher=Kurdistan 24 |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021004103/http://www.kurdistan24.net/en/news/620fd9a5-43c2-437f-98b8-5b234e130eee/iraqi-army-liberate-new-villages-in-second-day-of-mosul-operation- |archivedate=21 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> According to reports, the Peshmerga met little resistance on the eastern front, while Iraqi and PMF fighters coming from the south faced tougher resistance from ISIL.<ref name=\"guardian1018\">{{cite news |last1=Chulov |first1=Martin |last2=Hawramy |first2=Fazel |last3=Borger |first3=Julian |last4=Wintour |first4=Patrick |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraqi forces converge in decisive battle against Isis |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/oct/17/kurds-lead-advance-on-mosul-in-decisive-battle-for-iraqs-second-city |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018000353/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/oct/17/kurds-lead-advance-on-mosul-in-decisive-battle-for-iraqs-second-city |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi Army forces stormed Qaraqosh ([[Bakhdida]]), once the largest Assyrian town in Iraq, and fought with ISIL fighters who remained holed up, while also nearing Hammam al-'Alil.<ref name=\"straightstimes\">{{cite news |title=Iraqi forces make gains in bid to retake ISIS-held Mosul, France to host international talks |url=http://www.straitstimes.com/world/middle-east/iraqi-forces-ahead-of-schedule-in-operation-to-retake-mosul-from-isis-pentagon |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=The Straits Times |agency=AFP/Reuters |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019050753/http://www.straitstimes.com/world/middle-east/iraqi-forces-ahead-of-schedule-in-operation-to-retake-mosul-from-isis-pentagon |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Mareschal |first1=Edouard de |title=L'arm\u00e9e irakienne reprend le contr\u00f4le partiel de Qaraqosh la chr\u00e9tienne |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/international/2016/10/18/01003-20161018ARTFIG00331-l-armee-irakienne-reprend-le-controle-partiel-de-qaraqosh-la-chretienne.php |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Le Figaro |date=18 October 2016 |language=fr-FR |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019142956/http://www.lefigaro.fr/international/2016/10/18/01003-20161018ARTFIG00331-l-armee-irakienne-reprend-le-controle-partiel-de-qaraqosh-la-chretienne.php |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"rudaw1018\">{{cite news |title=LIVE UPDATES MOSUL BATTLE: Day 2 |url=http://rudaw.net/english/kurdistan/18102016 |accessdate=18 October 2016 |agency=[[Rudaw Media Network]] |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021233134/http://rudaw.net/english/kurdistan/18102016 |archivedate=21 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Displaced Christians celebrate as Iraq's military forces enter town near Mosul |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/world/world-news/displaced-christians-celebrate-as-iraqs-military-forces-enter-town-near-mosul-3090837/ |accessdate=19 October 2016 |work=The Indian Express |agency=AFP |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019214634/http://indianexpress.com/article/world/world-news/displaced-christians-celebrate-as-iraqs-military-forces-enter-town-near-mosul-3090837/ |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The Iraqi and Peshmerga advance had been slowed down during the same day due to suicide bombers, roadside [[Improvised explosive devices|IEDs]] and oil fires, and the allied forces were carrying out street-by-street search operations to clear out ISIL forces from the outskirts of Mosul city.<ref>{{cite news |title=Suicide bomber slams into Iraqi troops advancing on Mosul |url=http://www.9news.com.au/world/2016/10/18/07/29/suicide-bomber-slams-into-iraqi-column |accessdate=18 October 2016 |agency=9News.com.au |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019013714/http://www.9news.com.au/world/2016/10/18/07/29/suicide-bomber-slams-into-iraqi-column |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Kurds planning fresh push to recapture Mosul |url=https://news.sky.com/story/kurds-planning-fresh-push-to-recapture-mosul-10621939 |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Sky News |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018222641/https://news.sky.com/story/kurds-planning-fresh-push-to-recapture-mosul-10621939 |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The Peshmerga later paused their advance while the Iraqi Army continued its advance.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kurds pause in Mosul offensive, say Iraqi Army will advance |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/international/kurds-pause-in-mosul-offensive-say-iraqi-army-will-advance/article9234288.ece |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=The Hindu |date=18 October 2016}}</ref>\n\nAt this point in time, the Coalition strategy was reported to be to encircle Mosul completely, after which Iraqi troops would advance into the city center.<ref name=\"bbcnews1018\">{{cite news |title=Mosul battle: EU 'should expect influx of jihadists' |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37689210 |accessdate=18 October 2016 |publisher=BBC News |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018135845/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37689210 |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> As the Iraqi Army advanced on Mosul, rebellion against ISIL broke out in the city, though ISIL forces put down the revolts within a couple of days.<ref>{{cite news |title=Baghdadi survives coup attempt by ISIS Islamic Police in Mosul |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/baghdadi-survives-coup-attempt-isis-islamic-police-mosul/ |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Iraqi News |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019020800/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/baghdadi-survives-coup-attempt-isis-islamic-police-mosul/ |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Rebellious youths storm ISIS headquarters in Mosul, raise Iraqi flag |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/rebellious-youths-storm-isis-headquarters-mosul/ |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Iraqi News |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019152328/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/rebellious-youths-storm-isis-headquarters-mosul/ |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Armed uprising against ISIS begins in Mosul |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/armed-uprising-isis-begins-mosul/ |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Iraqi News |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019145804/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/armed-uprising-isis-begins-mosul/ |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe Iraqi Army resumed fighting on 19 October, surrounding Qaraqosh, while ISIL deployed snipers and car bombs.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mosul battle: Iraqi army 'besieges' Christian town of Qaraqosh |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37691830 |accessdate=19 October 2016 |publisher=BBC News |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018235507/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37691830 |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Les forces irakiennes s'appr\u00eatent \u00e0 reprendre une ville chr\u00e9tienne proche de Mossoul (Iraqi forces ready to retake Christian village near Mosul) |url=http://www.lorientlejour.com/article/1013499/les-forces-irakiennes-sappretent-a-reprendre-une-ville-chretienne-proche-de-mossoul.html |accessdate=19 October 2016 |work=L'Orient-Le Jour |agency=AFP |date=19 October 2016 |language=fr |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019213046/http://www.lorientlejour.com/article/1013499/les-forces-irakiennes-sappretent-a-reprendre-une-ville-chretienne-proche-de-mossoul.html |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Lt. Gen. Qassim al-Maliki declared that Iraqi forces had captured 13 villages north and northeast of Al Quwayr, south of Mosul, and the Iraqi Army was reported to be within {{convert|6|km|mi}} of the outskirts of Mosul city.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Damon |first1=Arwa |last2=Walsh |first2=Nick Paton |last3=Hume |first3=Tim |last4=McKirdy |first4=Euan |title=Iraqi forces closing in on Mosul for key ISIS battle |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/19/middleeast/mosul-isis-operation-iraq/index.html |accessdate=19 October 2016 |publisher=CNN |date=19 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019092506/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/19/middleeast/mosul-isis-operation-iraq/index.html |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The village of Kani Harami was captured after heavy fighting in the morning with the militants retreating to Abbasiyah.<ref name=\"rudaw1019\">{{cite news |title=LIVE Updates Mosul Battle: Day 3 |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/19102016 |accessdate=19 October 2016 |publisher=[[Rudaw Media Network]] |date=19 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019215412/http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/19102016 |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> A total of 22 towns were reported to have been captured, with 12 by the Peshmerga and 10 by the ISF.<ref>{{cite news |title=VIDEO. Irak : avec les combattants kurdes sur la route de Mossoul |url=http://www.leparisien.fr/politique/sur-la-route-de-mossoul-19-10-2016-6225651.php |accessdate=19 October 2016 |work=Le Parisien |date=19 October 2016}}</ref> Nofal Hammadi, governor of the [[Nineveh Governorate]], declared that 40% of the province had been retaken from ISIL.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0645\u062d\u0627\u0641\u0638 \u0646\u064a\u0646\u0648\u0649 \u064a\u0639\u0644\u0646 \u062a\u062d\u0631\u064a\u0631 40% \u0645\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u062d\u0627\u0641\u0638\u0629 (Nineveh Governor Announces Liberation of 40% of the Province) |url=http://www.alsumaria.tv/news/183211/%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B8-%D9%86%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%88%D9%89-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B1-40-%D9%85%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B8%D8%A9/ |accessdate=19 October 2016 |work=Al Sumaria |date=19 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020035714/http://www.alsumaria.tv/news/183211/%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B8-%D9%86%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%88%D9%89-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B1-40-%D9%85%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B8%D8%A9/ |archivedate=20 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe offensive to retake the town of [[Bashiqa]] northeast of Mosul was delayed due to lack of logistical support.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0627\u0644\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0627\u0642\u064a\u0629 \u062a\u0624\u062c\u0644 \u0647\u062c\u0648\u0645\u0647\u0627 \u0645\u0646 \u0645\u062d\u0648\u0631 \u0628\u0639\u0634\u064a\u0642\u0629 (Iraqi Forces Postpone Offensive in Bashiqah) |url=http://www.aljazeera.net/news/arabic/2016/10/19/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%AA%D8%A4%D8%AC%D9%84-%D9%87%D8%AC%D9%88%D9%85%D9%87%D8%A7-%D9%85%D9%86-%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%B1-%D8%A8%D8%B9%D8%B4%D9%8A%D9%82%D8%A9 |accessdate=19 October 2016 |publisher=[[Al Jazeera]] |date=19 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161022152702/http://www.aljazeera.net/news/arabic/2016/10/19/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%AA%D8%A4%D8%AC%D9%84-%D9%87%D8%AC%D9%88%D9%85%D9%87%D8%A7-%D9%85%D9%86-%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%88%D8%B1-%D8%A8%D8%B9%D8%B4%D9%8A%D9%82%D8%A9 |archivedate=22 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Kurdish Peshmerga Prepare to Seize Bashiqa |url=http://aranews.net/2016/10/kurdish-peshmergas-prepare-major-operation-retake-bashiqa-isis/ |accessdate=19 October 2016 |work=ARA News |date=19 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020041326/http://aranews.net/2016/10/kurdish-peshmergas-prepare-major-operation-retake-bashiqa-isis/ |archivedate=20 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The international coalition's commander Gary Voelsky also stated that a majority of ISIL leaders were fleeing Mosul, and predicted that foreign fighters would form the majority of militants remaining in the city.<ref>{{cite news |title=US general says IS leaders abandoning Mosul |url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/us-general-claims-leaders-abandoning-mosul-161514664.html |accessdate=20 October 2016 |agency=AFP |date=19 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020174202/https://www.yahoo.com/news/us-general-claims-leaders-abandoning-mosul-161514664.html |archivedate=20 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"theguardian1020\">{{cite news |title=Iraqi special forces launch 'large-scale' operation to retake Mosul |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/oct/20/mosul-attack-kurdish-forces-launch-large-scale-operation-against-isis-in-iraq |accessdate=20 October 2016 |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=20 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020174721/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/oct/20/mosul-attack-kurdish-forces-launch-large-scale-operation-against-isis-in-iraq |archivedate=20 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe fighting intensified on 20 October.<ref name=\"cnn1020\">{{cite news |last1=Wedeman |first1=Ben |last2=Dewan |first2=Angela |last3=McKirdy |first3=Euan |title=Mosul: Most intense day of fighting since offensive began |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/20/middleeast/mosul-isis-operation-iraq/ |accessdate=20 October 2016 |publisher=CNN |date=20 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021070924/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/20/middleeast/mosul-isis-operation-iraq/ |archivedate=21 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> A large convoy of [[Iraqi Special Operations Forces|Golden Division]] arrived at positions retaken by the Peshmerga forces,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ramsay |first1=Stuart |title=Elite troops strengthen battle for Mosul |url=https://news.sky.com/story/us-trained-iraqi-special-forces-strengthen-battle-for-mosul-10623884 |accessdate=20 October 2016 |publisher=Sky News |date=20 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020153554/https://news.sky.com/story/us-trained-iraqi-special-forces-strengthen-battle-for-mosul-10623884 |archivedate=20 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> and they also captured [[Bartella]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Baghdad's Finest: A look at Iraq's vaunted special forces |url=http://www.wbal.com/article/197492/130/baghdads-finest-a-look-at-iraqs-vaunted-special-forces |accessdate=20 October 2016 |agency=Associated Press |date=20 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021002249/http://www.wbal.com/article/197492/130/baghdads-finest-a-look-at-iraqs-vaunted-special-forces |archivedate=21 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> According to Maj. Gen. Maan al-Saadi of the Iraqi Army, 200 ISIL fighters were killed in the fight for Bartella.<ref name=\"cnn1020\" /> The Peshmerga and NPF announced a \"large-scale operation\" to the north and northeast of Mosul, to retake the Assyrian towns of [[Tesqopa]] and [[Bashiqa]].<ref name=\"theguardian1020\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Battle begins to liberate Christian towns seized by ISIS in 2014 |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/isis-terror/battle-mosul-forces-seek-free-isis-held-christian-towns-n669971 |accessdate=20 October 2016 |work=NBC News |date=20 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021040916/http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/isis-terror/battle-mosul-forces-seek-free-isis-held-christian-towns-n669971 |archivedate=21 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> During the day, the Peshmerga captured 6 villages, including 4 on the Bashiqa front line and 2 on the Nawaran front, while entering another 4 villages. The Peshmerga briefly captured the village of Tiz Khirab but were forced to withdraw.<ref name=\"rudaw1020\">{{cite news |title=Live Updates Mosul Battle: Day 4 |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/20102016 |accessdate=20 October 2016 |publisher=[[Rudaw Media Network]] |date=20 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020223353/http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/20102016 |archivedate=20 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On the southern front, Iraqi forces resumed their push north after a brief pause<ref name=\"wsj1020\">{{cite news |last1=Kesling |first1=Ben |last2=El-Ghobashy |first2=Tamer |title=Iraq Captures Key Town Near Mosul |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/new-front-opened-in-battle-for-mosul-1476956086 |accessdate=20 October 2016 |work=[[The Wall Street Journal]] |date=20 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021001000/http://www.wsj.com/articles/new-front-opened-in-battle-for-mosul-1476956086 |archivedate=21 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> and recaptured six villages east of [[Qayyarah]].<ref name=\"rudaw1020\" />\n\nISIL also set Al-Mishraq sulfur plant on fire, causing two deaths and nearly 1,000 hospitalizations from sulfur fume inhalation.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-chemicals-idUSKCN12M08G |title=Burning sulfur near Mosul sends hundreds to hospital, U.S. troops don masks |last=Dehghanpisheh |first=Babak |date=2016-10-22 |newspaper=Reuters|access-date=2016-10-26 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161025173049/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-chemicals-idUSKCN12M08G |archivedate=25 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The group was also reported to be digging trenches to slow the advancement of coalition troops.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/27/world/middleeast/iraq-mosul-isis-car-bombs.html?_r=0 |title=ISIS Sent Four Car Bombs. The Last One Hit Me. |last=Denton |first=Bryan |date=2016-10-26 |newspaper=The New York Times|access-date=2016-10-28 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161030061612/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/27/world/middleeast/iraq-mosul-isis-car-bombs.html?_r=0 |archivedate=30 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 October, ISIL launched multiple attacks in [[Kirkuk]] to divert military resources. Multiple explosions and gun battles were reported in the city, mostly centered on a government compound, and a senior Peshmerga commander said that the attackers had entered by posing as [[internally displaced person|IDPs]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Isil launches bomb and gunfire attacks in Iraqi oil city to divert attention from Mosul battle |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/21/isil-launches-bomb-and-gunfire-attacks-in-iraqi-oil-city-to-dive/ |accessdate=21 October 2016 |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=21 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021095248/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/21/isil-launches-bomb-and-gunfire-attacks-in-iraqi-oil-city-to-dive/ |archivedate=21 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Meanwhile, Iraqi government forces reported that they had retaken 2 more villages south of Mosul and killed 15 militants.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-37725108 |title=Mosul battle: IS launches Iraq counter-attack at Kirkuk |date=2016-10-21 |newspaper=BBC News |language=en-GB|access-date=2016-10-21 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021062733/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-37725108 |archivedate=21 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Local boys observing cityscape of Qayyarah town on fire.The Mosul District, Northern Iraq, Western Asia. 09 November, 2016.jpg|thumb|Local boys observing cityscape of [[Qayyarah]] town on fire]]\nOn 22 October, Iraqi police declared that ISIL's attack on Kirkuk had been repelled and that all the attackers had been killed or had blown themselves up.<ref name=\"abc1022\" /> Iraqi officials also stated that 80 people were killed in Kirkuk, primarily Kurdish security forces, and about 170 wounded; 56 ISIL militants were also killed.<ref>{{cite news |last=Bulos |first=Nabih |title='This is our land': Christians return to Iraqi town recaptured from Islamic State |url=https://www.latimes.com/world/la-fg-iraq-bartella-20161022-snap-story.html |accessdate=22 October 2016 |work=Los Angeles Times |date=22 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161023051958/http://www.latimes.com/world/la-fg-iraq-bartella-20161022-snap-story.html |archivedate=23 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> A reporter of [[T\u00fcrkmeneli TV]] also died in the attack,<ref name=\"abc1022\">{{cite news |title=The Latest: Abadi: Kirkuk Nearly Secured After IS Attack |url=http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/latest-iraqi-army-launches-push-town-mosul-42982676 |accessdate=22 October 2016 |publisher=ABC News |date=22 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161023050742/http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/latest-iraqi-army-launches-push-town-mosul-42982676 |archivedate=23 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> while at least seven journalists were wounded.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi journalist killed in Kirkuk fighting \u2013 Committee to Protect Journalists |url=https://cpj.org/2016/10/iraqi-journalist-killed-in-kirkuk-fighting.php |accessdate=22 October 2016 |publisher=Committee to Protect Journalists |date=21 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161022220421/https://cpj.org/2016/10/iraqi-journalist-killed-in-kirkuk-fighting.php |archivedate=22 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On the same day, Iraqi forces launched a large-scale offensive began to retake the Assyrian town of Bakhdida, which had remained under ISIL control after several days of fighting.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kalin |first1=Stephen |title=Church bells peal in town retaken by Iraqi troops from Islamic State |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-bartella-idUSKCN12L2HU |agency=Reuters |accessdate=22 October 2016 |date=22 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161022015146/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-bartella-idUSKCN12L2HU |archivedate=22 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi troops also advanced on the town of [[Tel Keppe]], to the north of Mosul.<ref name=\"cnn1022\">{{cite news |last1=Alkhshali |first1=Hamdi |last2=Smith-Spark |first2=Laura |last3=Lister |first3=Tim |title=ISIS kills hundreds in Mosul area, source says |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/22/middleeast/iraq-isis-mosul/ |accessdate=22 October 2016 |publisher=CNN |date=22 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161022102230/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/22/middleeast/iraq-isis-mosul/ |archivedate=22 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 23 October, the Peshmerga General Command also stated that the Peshmerga had cordoned off 8 villages and had secured a significant stretch of the Bashiqa-Mosul highway, coming within {{convert|9|km|mi}} of the city.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Goran |first1=Baxtiyar |title=Peshmerga declares victory in northeast Mosul operation |url=http://www.kurdistan24.net/en/news/a35e4330-be98-4ba3-b489-b61ff79a1672/Peshmerga-declares-victory-in-northeast-Mosul-operation |accessdate=23 October 2016 |publisher=Kurdistan 24 |date=23 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161024022926/http://www.kurdistan24.net/en/news/a35e4330-be98-4ba3-b489-b61ff79a1672/Peshmerga-declares-victory-in-northeast-Mosul-operation |archivedate=24 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> ISIL increased its counterattacks in order to distract the pro-government advancing towards Mosul. In addition to the attack on Kirkuk on 21 October, ISIL fighters struck [[Ar-Rutbah]] in [[Al-Anbar Governorate|Anbar Province]], as well as [[Sinjar]].<ref name=\"reuters1024\">{{cite news |title=Islamic State steps up counter-attacks as fighting edges closer to Mosul |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-cris-iraq-mosul-idUSKCN12N0CA |accessdate=25 October 2016 |agency=Reuters |date=24 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161024201511/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-cris-iraq-mosul-idUSKCN12N0CA |archivedate=24 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:US and Iraqi leaders discuss battle plans at Q-West.jpg|thumb|U.S. Army and Iraqi military leaders discuss battle plans at Qayyarah Airfield West, 25 October.]]\nBy 24 October, Nearly 800 ISIL fighters had been killed while 78 villages were reported to have been retaken from the group.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/24/middleeast/iraq-mosul-isis-tactics/index.html |title=Battle for Mosul: How ISIS is fighting back |last=Hume |first=Tim |date=2016-10-25 |website=CNN |access-date=2016-10-26 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026065257/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/24/middleeast/iraq-mosul-isis-tactics/index.html |archivedate=26 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The attack on Kirkuk was also brought to an end on the same day, with 74 militants being killed and others, including the leader of the attackers, being arrested.<ref>{{cite news |title=Attack in Iraq's Kirkuk over, 74 IS jihadists killed: Governor |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/world/2016/oct/24/attack-in-iraqs-kirkuk-over-74-is-jihadists-killed-governor-1531308.html |accessdate=24 October 2016 |work=The New Indian Express |date=24 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161024221246/http://www.newindianexpress.com/world/2016/oct/24/attack-in-iraqs-kirkuk-over-74-is-jihadists-killed-governor-1531308.html |archivedate=24 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 25 October, Iraqi Special Operations Forces came within {{convert|2|km|mi}} of the city and paused their advance to wait for reinforcements.<ref name=\"reuters1025\">{{cite news |title=Iraqi army's elite force pauses advance near Mosul |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKCN12P1KT |accessdate=25 October 2016 |agency=Reuters |date=25 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161025201800/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKCN12P1KT |archivedate=25 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 26 October, Iraqi forces faced heavy resistance from ISIL as they attempted to clear the militants from villages in Shora, south of Mosul.<ref name=\"reuters1026\">{{cite news |last1=Dehghanpisheh |first1=Babak |last2=Chmaytelli |first2=Maher |title=Islamic State holds up Iraqi army south of Mosul |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-idUSKCN12Q1FP |accessdate=26 October 2016 |agency=Reuters |date=26 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026202001/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-idUSKCN12Q1FP |archivedate=26 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Hundreds of ISIL suicide bombers were also reported to have been sent from Syria to defend Mosul.<ref name=\"cnn1026\">{{cite news |last1=Tawfeeq |first1=Mohammed |last2=Dewan |first2=Angela |title=Mosul: ISIS sends 'suicide squads' to Iraqi stronghold |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/26/middleeast/mosul-offensive-isis-suicide-squads/ |accessdate=26 October 2016 |publisher=CNN |date=26 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161027123739/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/26/middleeast/mosul-offensive-isis-suicide-squads/ |archivedate=27 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Meanwhile, Peshmerga forces captured the village of Derk, {{convert|12|km}} northeast of Mosul, where they discovered a large ISIL tunnel containing a large cache of weapons.<ref name=\"rudaw1026\">{{cite news |title=UPDATES: Mosul offensive day 10 |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/26102016 |accessdate=26 October 2016 |publisher=Rudaw Media Network |date=26 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161027060448/http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/26102016 |archivedate=27 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 27 October, the head of the [[United States Central Command]], Gen. [[Joseph Votel]], estimated that 800\u2013900 ISIL militants had been killed in the battle.<ref name=\"bbc1027\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37786661 |title=Mosul battle: IS 'loses hundreds of fighters' \u2013 US generals |date=27 October 2016 |publisher=BBC News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161027173952/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37786661 |archivedate=27 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 28 October, Iraqi forces recaptured the town of Al-Shura, south of Mosul,<ref name=\"cnn1028\">{{cite news |last1=Smith-Spark |first1=Laura |last2=Tawfeeq |first2=Mohammed |title=UN: ISIS 'executes' 232 near Mosul |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/28/middleeast/iraq-mosul-isis/index.html |accessdate=28 October 2016 |publisher=CNN |date=28 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161028113211/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/28/middleeast/iraq-mosul-isis/index.html |archivedate=28 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> while joint Iraqi-Peshmerga forces captured Fadiliya, which lies just 4&nbsp;km away from Mosul.<ref>{{cite news |title=ISIL pushed out of town near Mosul as advance continues |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/10/isil-pushed-town-mosul-advance-continues-161028094311805.html |accessdate=28 October 2016 |publisher=Al Jazeera |date=28 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161029044955/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/10/isil-pushed-town-mosul-advance-continues-161028094311805.html |archivedate=29 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Meanwhile, the UN stated that ISIL had taken tens of thousands of civilians to use as human shields in Mosul, including at least 5,000 families from around Al-Shura and 2,210 families from the Nimrud area of Hamdaniya. Those who refused to go were executed<ref name=\"cnn1028\" /><ref>{{cite news |last1=Kesling |first1=Ben |title=ISIS Herds Civilians to Mosul as Human Shields |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/isis-herds-civilians-to-mosul-as-human-shields-1477675640 |accessdate=28 October 2016 |work=Wall Street Journal |date=28 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161029050017/http://www.wsj.com/articles/isis-herds-civilians-to-mosul-as-human-shields-1477675640 |archivedate=29 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 October, the PMF launched an offensive towards the west of Mosul, with the aim of capturing the villages west of Mosul and reaching the town of [[Tal Afar]], in order to prevent ISIL fighters from retreating into neighboring Syria or reinforcing their defense of Mosul. The PMF had been tasked with recapturing around 14,000&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> of territory from ISIL,<ref>{{cite news |title=Shi'ite militias have launched an offensive on the western part of Mosul |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/isis-terror/shi-ite-militias-launch-offensive-seal-western-mosul-n674986 |accessdate=29 October 2016 |publisher=NBC News |date=29 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161030074509/http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/isis-terror/shi-ite-militias-launch-offensive-seal-western-mosul-n674986 |archivedate=30 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Arango |first1=Tim |title=Tal Afar, West of Mosul, Becomes Center of Battle for Influence in Iraq |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/30/world/middleeast/tal-afar-iraq-isis.html |accessdate=29 October 2016 |work=The New York Times |date=29 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161030060935/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/30/world/middleeast/tal-afar-iraq-isis.html |archivedate=30 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"rudaw1029\">{{cite news |title=Live Updates Mosul Offensive: Day 13 |url=http://rudaw.net/english/kurdistan/291020163 |accessdate=1 November 2016 |publisher=Rudaw Media Network |date=29 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161101104554/http://rudaw.net/english/kurdistan/291020163 |archivedate=1 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> though they stated that they would not enter Mosul city itself.<ref>{{cite news |title=The Latest: Iraqi forces push into town south of Mosul |url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2016/10/29/latest-iraqi-forces-push-into-town-south-mosul.html |accessdate=31 October 2016 |agency=Associated Press |date=29 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161030134315/http://www.foxnews.com/world/2016/10/29/latest-iraqi-forces-push-into-town-south-mosul.html |archivedate=30 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Meanwhile, Iraqi Army and PMF captured 15 villages from ISIL.<ref name=\"rudaw1029\" />\n\nOn 30 October, the Peshmerga had captured six more villages to north and east of Mosul, and had seized control of several major roads and landmarks,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bacon |first1=John |title=Battle for Mosul intensifies as Shiite militias join fray |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2016/10/30/battle-mosul-intensifies-shiite-militias-join-fray/93017632/ |accessdate=30 October 2016 |work=USA Today |date=30 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031014644/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2016/10/30/battle-mosul-intensifies-shiite-militias-join-fray/93017632/ |archivedate=31 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> and they declared to have captured 500 square kilometers of territory since the operation began.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mosul Offensive Day 14: Live Updates |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/301020163 |accessdate=30 October 2016 |publisher=Rudaw Media Network |date=30 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031090009/http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/301020163 |archivedate=31 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On the same day, the PMF stated that they had captured eight more villages to the southwest of Mosul.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mosul Offensive Day 14: Live Updates |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/301020163 |accessdate=1 November 2016 |publisher=Rudaw Media Network |date=30 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031145856/http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/301020163 |archivedate=31 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 31 October, a major Iraqi operation was launched on Bazwaya, to the east of Mosul, capturing the town along with several nearby villages, after coming under heavy fire.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Pagani |first1=Arianna |last2=Al Shamary |first2=Ammar |title='Iraqi army saved us,' residents outside Mosul say |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2016/10/31/iraqi-army-saved-us-residents-outside-mosul-say/93085196/ |accessdate=31 October 2016 |work=USA Today |date=31 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103115747/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2016/10/31/iraqi-army-saved-us-residents-outside-mosul-say/93085196/ |archivedate=3 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> After capturing Bazwaya, ISOF were less than {{convert|1|mi|km}} from Mosul.<ref name=\"abc1031\">{{cite news |title=The Latest: Iraq Premier Urges IS in Mosul to Surrender |url=http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/latest-iraq-forces-enter-village-east-mosul-43188332 |accessdate=31 October 2016 |work=ABC News |date=31 October 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161101103142/http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/latest-iraq-forces-enter-village-east-mosul-43188332 |archivedate=1 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Several Iraqi military officials stated that ISOF would soon begin its push into Mosul city.<ref>{{cite web |title=Rudaw English on Twitter |url=https://twitter.com/RudawEnglish/status/793076430997450752 |website=Twitter |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161229093800/https://twitter.com/RudawEnglish/status/793076430997450752 |archivedate=29 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Iraqi Army |title=Iraqi commander speaks to media (video) |url=https://twitter.com/ArmY_Iq/status/793125014585434112 |website=Twitter |accessdate=31 October 2016 |language=arabic |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161229093850/https://twitter.com/ArmY_Iq/status/793125014585434112 |archivedate=29 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Tawfeeq |first1=Mohammed |last2=Dewan |first2=Angela |title=Iraqi troops to enter Mosul in 'matter of hours' |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/31/middleeast/iraq-mosul-advance/ |accessdate=31 October 2016 |publisher=CNN |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031150656/https://www.cnn.com/2016/10/31/middleeast/iraq-mosul-advance |archivedate=31 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Meanwhile, the U.S.-led coalition stated that they would target ISIL militants from the air if they attempted to flee the city, though The US Department of Defense stated that hundreds of militants were believed to have already escaped.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Michaels |first1=Jim |title=U.S. aircraft to block ISIL militants fleeing Mosul in Iraq |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2016/10/31/us-aircraft-block-isil-militants-fleeing-mosul-iraq/93075108/ |accessdate=31 October 2016 |work=USA Today |date=31 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103111652/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2016/10/31/us-aircraft-block-isil-militants-fleeing-mosul-iraq/93075108/ |archivedate=3 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi Prime Minister Haider al-Abadi meanwhile called on ISIL fighters in Mosul to surrender.<ref name=\"abc1031\" />\n\n=== November: Entering East Mosul, reaching Tal Afar ===\nOn 1 November, the operation to enter Mosul city began at dawn. The allied forces began their assault in Mosul's eastern Karama district, with artillery, tank and machine-gun fire on ISIL positions as they prepared the larger push into the city.<ref>{{cite news |last1=King |first1=Laura |title=Iraqi forces launch assault on Mosul |url=https://www.latimes.com/world/middleeast/la-fg-iraq-mosul-20161031-story.html |accessdate=1 November 2016 |work=Los Angeles Times |date=1 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161102161555/http://www.latimes.com/world/middleeast/la-fg-iraq-mosul-20161031-story.html |archivedate=2 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Airstrikes by the U.S.-led coalition targeted ISIL positions, and ISIL started tire fires to reduce visibility.<ref name=\"rferl1101\"/> Heavy fighting occurred in the Gogjali district, at the gate of the entrance to eastern Mosul, where ISIL militants used car bombs and sniper fire to try to halt the advance.<ref name=\"rudaw1101\">{{cite news |title=Mosul Offensive Day 16: Live Updates |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/01112016 |accessdate=1 November 2016 |publisher=Rudaw Media Network |date=1 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161101170124/http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/01112016 |archivedate=1 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The Golden Division entered Mosul's city limits that afternoon, engaging in street fights with ISIL militants.<ref name=\"rudaw1101\" /> Shortly afterward, the Iraqi Army announced that they had captured Mosul's state television building on the city's left bank.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi General Says Special Forces Have Taken Mosul's State TV Building in an Eastern Neighborhood of the City |url=http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/iraqi-general-special-forces-mosuls-state-tv-building-43212397 |accessdate=2 November 2016 |agency=Associated Press |date=1 November 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104000843/http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/iraqi-general-special-forces-mosuls-state-tv-building-43212397 |archivedate=4 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Mosul battle: Iraqi special forces enter city |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37832819 |accessdate=2 November 2016 |publisher=BBC News |date=1 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161101141155/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37832819 |archivedate=1 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The Gogjali district was reported to be under Iraqi government control by the evening, while the Iraqi Army's 9th Division and 3rd Brigade had entered the neighborhood of Judaydat al-Mufti on the left bank. The [[Iraqi war media office]] stated that Iraqi government forces suffered no casualties during the assault.<ref name=\"rudaw1101\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Mosul battle: Iraqi special forces 'break front line' |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37843431 |accessdate=2 November 2016 |publisher=BBC News |date=2 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104005412/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37843431 |archivedate=4 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Meanwhile, Iraqi government forces captured two villages on the northern front.<ref name=\"rudaw1101\" />\n\nOn 2 November, ISOF continued fighting the remaining ISIL fighters in the eastern section of Gogjali,<ref name=\"rudaw1102\">{{cite news |title=Mosul Offensive, Day 17: Live Updates |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/021120162 |accessdate=2 November 2016 |publisher=rudaw |date=2 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104024202/http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/021120162 |archivedate=4 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> though Iraqi troops were forced to hold their positions in eastern Mosul, as poor weather conditions were limiting visibility for drones and aircraft, preventing them from advancing.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi army halt operations in Mosul |url=http://www.skynews.com.au/news/top-stories/2016/11/02/iraqi-army-halt-operations-in-mosul.html |accessdate=2 November 2016 |publisher=Sky News Australia |date=2 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103140418/http://www.skynews.com.au/news/top-stories/2016/11/02/iraqi-army-halt-operations-in-mosul.html |archivedate=3 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Meanwhile, eight militants were killed in Mosul by Iraqi forces.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi forces kill 8 ISIS militants in Mosul as civilians cleared out |url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2016/11/02/iraqi-forces-kill-8-isis-militants-in-mosul-as-civilians-cleared-out.html |accessdate=2 November 2016 |agency=Associated Press |date=2 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161102195300/http://www.foxnews.com/world/2016/11/02/iraqi-forces-kill-8-isis-militants-in-mosul-as-civilians-cleared-out.html |archivedate=2 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On the same day, the PMU announced that it had captured 115&nbsp;km\u00b2 that day after fierce fighting with ISIL, including six villages, and had surrounded three ISIL-held villages. They also claimed that they had reached a highway to the southwest of Mosul and had cut the first supply line to Mosul from [[Raqqa]].<ref name=\"rudaw1102\" /> In the southern front, the Iraqi Army launched an offensive in the morning to recapture [[Hamam al-Alil]] and engaged in heavy fighting with ISIL,<ref>{{cite news |title=Mosul Op: Fighting in Hammam Al-Alil |url=https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20161102-mosul-op-fighting-in-hammam-al-alil/ |accessdate=2 November 2016 |work=Middle East Monitor |date=2 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103140637/https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20161102-mosul-op-fighting-in-hammam-al-alil/ |archivedate=3 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> while, Iraqi Federal Police captured two villages in the south.<ref name=\"rudaw1102\" />\n\nOn 3 November, the Iraqi Army's 9th Armored Division was reported to have entered the neighborhood of al-Intisar in eastern Mosul.<ref name=\"cnn1103\">{{cite news |last1=Lister |first1=Tim |last2=Tawfeeq |first2=Mohammed |last3=Dewan |first3=Angela |title=Iraqi forces fight ISIS on Mosul streets |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/11/03/middleeast/mosul-offensive-iraq-troops-in/index.html |accessdate=3 November 2016 |publisher=CNN |date=3 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103185148/http://www.cnn.com/2016/11/03/middleeast/mosul-offensive-iraq-troops-in/index.html |archivedate=3 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> while Mosul's [[Fifth Bridge]], located over the Tigris river, was destroyed by airstrikes.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mosul Eye \u0639\u064a\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0648\u0635\u0644 on Twitter |url=https://twitter.com/MosulEye/status/794085486264516608 |accessdate=4 November 2016 |publisher=Twitter |date=3 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161229093638/https://twitter.com/MosulEye/status/794085486264516608 |archivedate=29 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> U.S. and Iraqi authorities stated the offensive was \"ahead of schedule\", while Brigadier Saad Maan stated that the priority of protecting civilian lives and infrastructure would possibly slow their advance into the city.<ref>{{cite news |last1=MacDiarmid |first1=Campbell |title=Operation to drive ISIL from Mosul 'ahead of schedule' |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/11/03/operation-to-drive-isil-from-mosul-ahead-of-schedule/ |accessdate=3 November 2016 |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=3 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104144758/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/11/03/operation-to-drive-isil-from-mosul-ahead-of-schedule/ |archivedate=4 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 4 November, the Iraqi Army recaptured six districts in Mosul, including 90% of the eastern district of al-Zahra. However, they were forced to withdraw from Karama district because of heavy resistance.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mosul battle: Iraqi army fights its way into new suburb |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37872392 |accessdate=4 November 2016 |publisher=BBC News |date=4 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104135350/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37872392 |archivedate=4 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Clashes continued into 5 November, with clashes being the most intense in the neighborhood of al-Bakr.<ref name=\"ap1105\">{{cite news |title=Iraqi Units Clear Mosul Buildings After Advances, IS Attacks |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-11-05/iraqi-units-clear-mosul-buildings-after-advances-is-attacks |accessdate=5 November 2016 |agency=Associated Press |date=5 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105224322/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-11-05/iraqi-units-clear-mosul-buildings-after-advances-is-attacks |archivedate=5 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The eastern neighborhoods of Kirkukli and al-Zahra in the east and Al-Tahrir in the northeast were under Iraqi control, while the southern neighborhoods of Qudes and Karama reportedly remained under ISIL control.<ref name=\"cnn1105\">{{cite news |last1=Tawfeeq |first1=Mohammed |last2=Smith-Spark |first2=Laura |title=Iraqi troops storm town southeast of Mosul |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/11/05/middleeast/iraq-mosul-isis-offensive/index.html |accessdate=5 November 2016 |publisher=CNN |date=5 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105185136/http://www.cnn.com/2016/11/05/middleeast/iraq-mosul-isis-offensive/index.html |archivedate=5 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Fighting resumed in the Gogjali district, after ISIL militants emerged from tunnels during the night.<ref name=\"rudaw1105\">{{cite news |title=Live Updates: The fight for Mosul day 20 |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/05112016 |accessdate=5 November 2016 |publisher=Rudaw Media Network |date=5 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105230719/http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/05112016 |archivedate=5 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The Iraqi Army continued its assault on three fronts to [[Hamam al-Alil]],<ref name=\"cnn1105\" /> with Iraqi forces retaking the town by nighttime, though fighting would continue for another two days.<ref name=\"rudaw1105\" /> On 6 November, Iraqi forces in the southwestern front stated that they were {{convert|4|km}} from [[Mosul International Airport]], after taking control of [[Hamam al-Alil]] on the previous day.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dehghanpisheh |first1=Babak |last2=Rasheed |first2=Ahmed |title=Iraqi forces are 4&nbsp;km from Mosul airport |url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2016/11/06/Iraqi-forces-are-4-km-from-Mosul-airport.html |accessdate=6 November 2016 |agency=Reuters |date=6 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107010144/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2016/11/06/Iraqi-forces-are-4-km-from-Mosul-airport.html |archivedate=7 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> They also stormed the Al-Sada district, their first entrance into northern Mosul.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraq forces storm northern Mosul amid anti-Daesh op. |url=http://aa.com.tr/en/middle-east/iraq-forces-storm-northern-mosul-amid-anti-daesh-op/679594 |accessdate=6 November 2016 |agency=Anadolu Agency |date=6 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161106185404/http://aa.com.tr/en/middle-east/iraq-forces-storm-northern-mosul-amid-anti-daesh-op/679594 |archivedate=6 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 November, the Peshmerga, backed by coalition airstrikes, launched an offensive from three fronts in the morning to take the town of [[Bashiqa]], which was still held by ISIL and had been surrounded for about two weeks.<ref name=\"rudaw1107\">{{cite news |title=Mosul Offensive Day 22: Peshmerga attack ISIS in Bashiqa |url=http://rudaw.net/english/kurdistan/07112016 |accessdate=7 November 2016 |publisher=Rudaw Media Network |date=7 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107162620/http://rudaw.net/english/kurdistan/07112016 |archivedate=7 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> About 100 to 200 ISIL militants were estimated to be left in the town.<ref>{{cite news |title=Peshmerga in heavy gun battle with ISIL near Mosul |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/11/peshmerga-heavy-gun-battle-isil-mosul-161107073529611.html |accessdate=7 November 2016 |publisher=Al Jazeera |date=7 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107161033/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/11/peshmerga-heavy-gun-battle-isil-mosul-161107073529611.html |archivedate=7 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> In the early afternoon, the Iraqi troops also advanced on the town of [[Tel Keppe]], north of Mosul, besieging the town. The town of Bashiqa was reported to be fully under Peshmerga control, though an ISIL pocket remained under siege in the town until the end of the month.<ref name=\"rudaw1107\" /><ref name=\"clear Bashiqa\" /> On the southern front, [[Hamam al-Alil]], was fully captured by pro-government forces, after two days of clearing out the remaining ISIL fighters.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi forces capture key town of Hamam al-Alil from ISIS on southern approach to Mosul |url=http://www.straitstimes.com/world/middle-east/iraqi-forces-capture-key-town-of-hamam-al-alil-from-isis-on-southern-approach-to |accessdate=7 November 2016 |work=The Straits Times |agency=Agence France-Presse |date=7 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107223543/http://www.straitstimes.com/world/middle-east/iraqi-forces-capture-key-town-of-hamam-al-alil-from-isis-on-southern-approach-to |archivedate=7 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> In eastern Mosul, the ISOF surrounded the neighborhoods of Karama, Malayyin al-Salasa, Shquq Khazraa, Zahra, Karkuli, Aden, and Zahabi. The Iraqi Army's 9th armored division and the 3rd Brigade captured the village of Manarat Shabak, east of the city, and made an incursion into the eastern Mosul neighborhoods of Hay Intisar, Judaydah al-Mufti, and Hay Shaima. Meanwhile, the Iraqi Federal Police captured two villages near Hammam Al-Alil.<ref name=\"rudaw1107\" /> On 8 November, on the western front, PMU forces were reported to have advanced to a distance of 25&nbsp;km towards the strategically important [[Tal Afar]] military airbase, south of the city of Tal Afar.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi Shi'ite forces target air base west of Mosul |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-militias-idUSKBN13320L |work=Reuters |date=8 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170518195758/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-militias-idUSKBN13320L |archivedate=18 May 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 9 November, the ISOF captured the majority of the Intisar district in southern Mosul, while ISIL had reportedly deployed armed child soldiers in Mosul.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraq takes part of Intisar district; Islamic State deploys armed children in Mosul |url=http://www.upi.com/Top_News/World-News/2016/11/09/Iraq-takes-part-of-Intisar-district-Islamic-State-deploys-armed-children-in-Mosul/9281478695038/ |accessdate=11 November 2016 |agency=UPI |date=9 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161110161620/http://www.upi.com/Top_News/World-News/2016/11/09/Iraq-takes-part-of-Intisar-district-Islamic-State-deploys-armed-children-in-Mosul/9281478695038/ |archivedate=10 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 10 November, in eastern Mosul, the Golden Division, as well as elements of the 9th Division, were reported to be regrouping and clearing neighborhoods once occupied by ISIL, as well as screening residents fleeing from Mosul for any militants hiding among them.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraq troops slow Mosul advance as they clear neighborhoods |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/iraq-troops-pause-in-advance-on-mosul/2016/11/10/e7b7af8e-a71f-11e6-ba46-53db57f0e351_story.html |work=Washington Post |date=10 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111061733/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/iraq-troops-pause-in-advance-on-mosul/2016/11/10/e7b7af8e-a71f-11e6-ba46-53db57f0e351_story.html |archivedate=11 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On the southern front, pro-government forces advanced towards the ancient city of [[Nimrud]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Battle for Mosul nears ancient Nimrud |url=http://www.news24.com/World/News/battle-for-mosul-nears-ancient-nimrud-20161110 |work=Washington Post |date=10 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111061204/http://www.news24.com/World/News/battle-for-mosul-nears-ancient-nimrud-20161110 |archivedate=11 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 November, Iraqi forces on the southern front were preparing to advance up the western bank of the Tigris River toward [[Mosul International Airport]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi forces preparing advance on south Mosul \u2013 World \u2013 Dunya News |url=http://dunyanews.tv/en/World/360520-Iraqi-forces-preparing-advance-on-south-Mosul |accessdate=11 November 2016 |agency=Reuters |date=11 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161229093755/http://dunyanews.tv/en/World/360520-Iraqi-forces-preparing-advance-on-south-Mosul |archivedate=29 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> In eastern Mosul, Iraqi forces launched a new offensive to regain control of the neighborhood of Karkukli,<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi forces launch new offensive, pushing deeper into Mosul |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/111120163 |accessdate=11 November 2016 |publisher=Rudaw Media Network |date=11 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111204630/http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/111120163 |archivedate=11 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> while Iraqi anti-terror units entered the Qadesiyya neighborhood.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi Counter-terrorism Units Enters into Qadesiyya Neighborhood in Mosul |url=http://english.almanar.com.lb/97315 |accessdate=11 November 2016 |publisher=Al Manar TV |date=11 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161112015148/http://english.almanar.com.lb/97315 |archivedate=12 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 12 November, heavy clashes broke out in the al-Salam neighborhood of east Mosul.<ref name=\"Rudaw Media Network\">{{cite news |title=Iraqi forces face ISIS resistance as they push deeper into Mosul |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/121120163 |accessdate=12 November 2016 |publisher=Rudaw Media Network |date=12 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113040557/http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/121120163 |archivedate=13 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi Army announced that it had captured al-Arbajiya district and was clearing the adjacent al-Qadisiya al-Thaniya district.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-fighting-idUSKBN1370DY |title=Iraqi army says advances in Mosul, despite suicide bombers |publisher=Reuters |date=12 November 2016 |last1=Evans |first1=Dominic |last2=Hameed |first2=Saif |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170508131936/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-fighting-idUSKBN1370DY |archivedate=8 May 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> They also reached the Palestine neighborhood in southeast Mosul and were engaged in battle with ISIL in the Quds neighborhood.<ref name=\"Rudaw Media Network\" /> The PMU announced that the [[Sinjar Resistance Units]] (YB\u015e), an allied group, had started the operation to capture the villages south of [[Sinjar]] from ISIL.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi PMU Ezidi YBS units start operation to liberate villages around Sinjar from ISIS |url=https://twitter.com/pmu_english/status/797388842412056577 |author=Iraqi PMU |publisher=Iraqi PMU English Official Twitter |date=12 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}{{dead link|date=July 2018|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> On 13 November, Iraqi forces recaptured the ancient Assyrian city of [[Nimrud]], as well as the adjacent modern town.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37966657 |title=Nimrud: Iraqi forces 'retake ancient city from IS' |publisher=BBC |date=13 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113162745/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37966657 |archivedate=13 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/11/13/iraqi-forces-retake-ancient-city-of-nimrud/ |title=Iraqi forces retake historical town of Nimrud |publisher=The Telegraph |date=13 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114175129/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/11/13/iraqi-forces-retake-ancient-city-of-nimrud/ |archivedate=14 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi force also captured the Karkojli neighborhood in eastern Mosul.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/anti-terrorism-forces-liberate-karkojli-area-mosul/ |title=Anti-Terrorism forces liberate Karkojli area in Mosul |publisher=Iraqi News |date=13 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114083757/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/anti-terrorism-forces-liberate-karkojli-area-mosul/ |archivedate=14 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 14 November, 30 ISIL fighters, including senior leaders, were killed as PMU forces captured the village of al-Abbas;<ref name=3km>{{cite news |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/30-isis-fighters-killed-security-forces-stand-3km-mosul-airport/ |title=30 ISIS fighters killed as security forces stand 3&nbsp;km from Mosul airport |publisher=Iraqi News |date=15 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161115081720/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/30-isis-fighters-killed-security-forces-stand-3km-mosul-airport/ |archivedate=15 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> the PMU also captured two more villages.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/security-hashed-al-shaabi-liberate-two-villages-east-west-mosul/ |title=Security forces and al-Hashed al-Shaabi liberate 3 villages east and west of Mosul |publisher=Iraqi News |date=14 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161115070744/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/security-hashed-al-shaabi-liberate-two-villages-east-west-mosul/ |archivedate=15 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Pro-government forces on the southern front captured the village of Bo Youssef and were {{convert|3|km|mi}} from Mosul airport.<ref name=3km /> Meanwhile, ISIL launched three mustard gas attacks on Qayyarah, killing seven people.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/video-isis-launches-3-attacks-using-chemical-weapons-qayyarah/ |title=Video: ISIS launches 3 attacks using chemical weapons on Qayyarah |publisher=Iraqi News |date=14 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161115131852/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/video-isis-launches-3-attacks-using-chemical-weapons-qayyarah/ |archivedate=15 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:ISOF APC on the street of Mosul, Northern Iraq, Western Asia. 16 November, 2016.jpg|thumb|ISOF APC on the street of Mosul, 16 November 2016]]\n[[File:2016 Mosul Offensive (Mosul Surrounds).svg|thumb|Map of Mosul control lines around 22 November 2016]]\nOn 15 November, troops of the Golden Division began storming areas in northern and eastern Mosul, including the neighborhoods of al-Akhaa, al-Bakr, and al-Hadbaa.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-forces-storm-3-new-neighborhoods-mosul/ |title=Iraqi forces storm into 3 new neighborhoods in Mosul |publisher=Iraqi News |date=15 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161116015514/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-forces-storm-3-new-neighborhoods-mosul/ |archivedate=16 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On the Western front, the Badr Organization announced that it had captured two villages and advanced 10 kilometers in the western axis of the offensive.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/badr-organization-liberates-2-villages-western-axis-nineveh/ |title=Badr Organization liberates 2 villages in western axis of Nineveh |publisher=Iraqi News |date=15 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161116102349/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/badr-organization-liberates-2-villages-western-axis-nineveh/ |archivedate=16 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 16 November, the PMF took control of [[Tal Afar]] military airbase, to the northwest of Mosul city.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2016/11/16/middleeast/iraq-mosul-zahraa/ |title=Iraqi forces recapture key air base near Mosul |publisher=CNN |date=16 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117144614/http://edition.cnn.com/2016/11/16/middleeast/iraq-mosul-zahraa/ |archivedate=17 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 18 November, the PMU attacked more villages in the vicinity of Tal Afar, in an area infamous for Sunni Islamist militancy and outstanding support for ISIL among the population.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2016/11/18/shiite-militias-are-crashing-the-mosul-offensive/ |title=Shiite Militias Are Crashing the Mosul Offensive |work=Foreign Policy |date=18 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161118233543/http://foreignpolicy.com/2016/11/18/shiite-militias-are-crashing-the-mosul-offensive/ |archivedate=18 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> PMF control had already captured over 16 villages in the surrounding area, during preceding days.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://english.almanar.com.lb/105070 |title=16 Villages Liberated from ISIL in Mosul in Mobilization Forces Operations |publisher=Al Manar TV |date=18 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161119062545/http://english.almanar.com.lb/105070 |archivedate=19 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 22 November, 4 of the 5 Tigris bridges in Mosul were struck by Coalition airstrikes within the past 48 hours.<ref name=baaj>{{cite news |url=http://in.reuters.com/article/mideast-crisis-iraq-idINKBN13H0Z9 |title=U.S. strike destroys bridge, restricts Islamic State in Mosul \u2013 official |publisher=Reuters |date=22 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220105236/http://in.reuters.com/article/mideast-crisis-iraq-idINKBN13H0Z9 |archivedate=20 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On the same day, U.S. Special Forces captured four Islamic State commanders near the town of [[Al-Ba'aj]], far to the west, near the Syrian border.<ref name=\"baaj\" />\n\nOn 23 November, to the west of Tal Afar, the PMF reported cutting the road between [[Sinjar]] and [[Tal Afar]], with their Shi'a component groups advancing from the South linking up with the [[Sinjar Resistance Units]] and [[\u00caz\u00eedxan Women's Units]] to the North, thus completing the encirclement of the Mosul pocket.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-38079602 |title=Mosul battle: Iraq militias 'cut off IS access to city' |publisher=BBC |date=23 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161124021914/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-38079602 |archivedate=24 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 30 November, the PMF said that they captured 12 villages from ISIL in the [[Tal Afar]] area, within the past five days.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2016/11/30/coalition-leaders-plan-to-airdrop-troops-into-is-held-mosul |title=Coalition leaders 'plan to airdrop troops' into IS-held Mosul |work=The New Arab |date=30 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161201125751/https://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2016/11/30/coalition-leaders-plan-to-airdrop-troops-into-is-held-mosul |archivedate=1 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> By 30 November, the Peshmerga had cleared the remaining ISIL snipers from the town, though they continued to clear the mines and explosives left behind by ISIL.<ref name=\"near tears\">{{cite web|url=https://www.stripes.com/clergy-near-tears-after-militants-cleared-from-iraqi-churches-1.438554|title=Clergy near tears after militants cleared from Iraqi churches|author=Chad Garland|publisher=Stars and Stripes|date=9 November 2016|accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"clear Bashiqa\">{{cite web|url=https://www.kurdistan24.net/en/news/0bf385fd-8e64-431c-93fa-b9f6d9126a18/peshmerga-efforts-to-clear-bashiqa-from-mines-continues-|title=Peshmerga efforts to clear Bashiqa from mines continues|author=Baxtiyar Goran|publisher=Kurdistan24|date=30 November 2016|accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref>\n\nAt the end of November, the Iraqi military assessed that it had taken control of 19 neighborhoods in eastern Mosul during the month, about somewhat less than 30 percent of the area of Mosul east of the [[Tigris]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2016/11/30/iraqs-special-forces-have-retaken-19-mosul-neighborhoods.html |title=Iraq's special forces have retaken 19 Mosul neighborhoods |publisher=Fox News |date=30 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161201023108/http://www.foxnews.com/world/2016/11/30/iraqs-special-forces-have-retaken-19-mosul-neighborhoods.html |archivedate=1 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> While the \"Golden Division\" Special Operations Forces persistently advanced into East Mosul, the 9th Division took one neighborhood in the southeast, the 16th Division had not yet breached the Mosul city limits from the north, and the 15th Division, advancing from the southwest, was still several kilometres away from western Mosul.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.middleeasteye.net/news/battle-mosul-how-islamic-state-has-made-life-tough-iraq-s-elite-special-forces-847595856 |title=Battle for Mosul: How IS is making life tough for Iraq's elite forces |work=Middle East Eye |date=30 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161201081353/http://www.middleeasteye.net/news/battle-mosul-how-islamic-state-has-made-life-tough-iraq-s-elite-special-forces-847595856 |archivedate=1 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== December: Advancing towards the Syrian border and launch of Phase Two ===\n[[File:Battle of Mosul as of 7-Dec-2016.png|thumb|Battle situation as of 7 December 2016]]\n20 airstrikes by the US-led coalition were heard on the morning of 6 December, following an assault on the city's strategic main (old) bridge that was held by ISIL. In the overnight hours, ISIL launched a counter-attack in the southeastern area of Mosul, near al-Salam.<ref name=\"NY Times\">{{cite news |url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2016/12/07/is-launches-overnight-attack-against-iraqi-troops-in-mosul.html |title=IS Launches Overnight Attack Against Iraqi Troops in Mosul |work=Associated Press |date=7 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170102082851/http://www.foxnews.com/world/2016/12/07/is-launches-overnight-attack-against-iraqi-troops-in-mosul.html |archivedate=2 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On the same day, the PMU stated that it had captured the southern section of Tal Abta.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/al-hashd-tal-abta-western-mosul/ |title=Al-Hashd al-Shaabi liberate Tal Abta in western Mosul |work=Iraqi News |date=6 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170113165621/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/al-hashd-tal-abta-western-mosul/ |archivedate=13 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Following the overnight ISIL attack, Iraqi forces continued to secure the al-Salam area on 7 December, capturing al-Salam hospital. However, ISIL recaptured the hospital after a counterattack, which destroyed or disabled 20 Iraqi vehicles.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-idUSKBN13X1EI |title=Iraqi troops pull out from Mosul hospital after fierce battle |publisher=Reuters |date=8 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170518174018/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-idUSKBN13X1EI |archivedate=18 May 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 9 December, Iraqi Joint Operations Command announced that they had captured the three east Mosul districts of Saha, Adel, and Tahrir, adding that Iraqi forces had captured 27 districts of Mosul, with clashes ongoing in 4 districts. Lieutenant-General Abdul Ameer Yarallah also stated that three factories making car bombs in Mosul and three weapons warehouses had been destroyed by Iraqi airstrikes.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1022914.shtml |title=Iraqi forces recapture more districts from IS militants in Mosul |work=Global Times |date=9 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161223131921/http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1022914.shtml |archivedate=23 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 11 December, the CTS forces mentioned that they had the al-Nour neighborhood of east Mosul.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-idUSKBN1411FE |title=Iraqi police say ready to join assault on east Mosul |publisher=Reuters |date=12 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170706115057/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-idUSKBN1411FE |archivedate=6 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 December, CTS commander Abdul Wahab al-Saedi stated that there were only 6 districts left to be captured by the CTS forces in East Mosul, and that they had already captured 32 of them.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/commander-six-districts-left-recapture-eastern-mosul/ |title=Commander: six districts left to recapture eastern Mosul |work=Iraqi News |date=13 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161214192402/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/commander-six-districts-left-recapture-eastern-mosul/ |archivedate=14 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> While the PMF to the west continued clearing villages in the desert region of the ISIL heartland in the [[Nineveh Governorate]], it was reported on the same day that the Badr militia was targeting villages around Tal Afar to \"surround Daesh and tighten the noose around them\", while Kata'ib Hezbollah advanced further west towards the Syrian border.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-idUSKBN1421TS |title=Iraqi Shi'ite forces aim to clear border strip with Syria |publisher=Reuters |date=13 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170212045346/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-idUSKBN1421TS |archivedate=12 February 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Later in the day, CTS forces captured the al-Falah Oula and al-Falah Thaniya districts, while the PMU captured 7 villages near Tal Afar.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1023586.shtml |title=Iraqi forces retake control of 2 districts, 7 villages from IS in Mosul |date=14 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220144952/http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1023586.shtml |archivedate=20 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 15 December, CTS commander Abdul Ghani al-Assadi announced that the first phase of retaking the eastern shores of the city was completed, with CTS forces capturing 40 out of the 56 eastern districts.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/40-56-eastern-mosul-districts-liberated-army-commander/ |title=40 out of 56 eastern Mosul districts liberated: army commander |work=Iraqi News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161216170059/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/40-56-eastern-mosul-districts-liberated-army-commander/ |archivedate=16 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 December, the PMF captured the Tel Abtah district, home to almost 50,000 people and a major stretegic ISIL stronghold, and advanced on more villages to the south and southwest of [[Tal Afar]].<ref name=\"STRATFOR\">{{cite web |url=https://www.stratfor.com/analysis/anti-islamic-state-forces-concentrate-east-mosul |title=Anti-Islamic State Forces Concentrate On East Mosul |publisher=STRATFOR |date=16 December 2016}}</ref> On 18 December, the 9th Division, with the assistance of CTS, started attacking al-Wehda district of east Mosul, in order to regain control of al-Salam hospital.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-army-attack-locations-mosul-neighborhood/ |title=Iraqi army attack IS locations in Mosul neighborhood |work=Iraqi News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161222135442/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-army-attack-locations-mosul-neighborhood/ |archivedate=22 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 19 December, Iraqi forces stormed into the al-Mazare' area, after retaking large parts of al-Wahda in southeastern Mosul, and also killed 14 ISIL fighters, including 4 suicide bombers.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-forces-kill-14-members-east-mosul/ |title=Iraqi forces kill 14 IS members east of Mosul |work=Iraqi News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161222190017/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-forces-kill-14-members-east-mosul/ |archivedate=22 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 21 December, U.S. Air Force Brigadier General Matthew Isler announced that pro-government forces had entered a planned operational refit, which included repairing vehicles, re-supplying ammunition and preparing for the next stage of the battle. He also stated that they had captured more than a quarter of the city.<ref>{{cite web |date=21 December 2016 |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN14A197 |title=Iraqi forces in Mosul mostly in refit mode: U.S. general |publisher=Reuters}}</ref>\n\n[[File:24 December 2016 CJCS USO Holiday Tour PT. 2 161224-D-PB383-080 (31850877755).jpg|thumb|Iraqis present Marine Gen. [[Joseph Dunford]] with the ISIL flag upside down]]\nOn 23 December, the Iraqi Army captured the Mosul Police Academy headquarters in Al-Qahira district, which was their first major advance since the suspension of military operations a week earlier.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://aa.com.tr/en/middle-east/iraqi-forces-recapture-mosul-police-station-from-daesh/713002 |title=Iraqi forces recapture Mosul police station from Daesh |agency=Anadolu Agency |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161224032410/http://aa.com.tr/en/middle-east/iraqi-forces-recapture-mosul-police-station-from-daesh/713002 |archivedate=24 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 24 December, U.S. Army Colonel Brett G. Sylvia stated that American soldiers assisting Iraqi forces would be embedded more extensively and would partner with additional formations.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN14C1RW |title=U.S. forces embedding more to help Iraqis retake Mosul: commander |work=Reuters}}</ref> Iraqi Prime Minister Haider al-Abadi stated that Iraqi forces were in control of over a third of Mosul, while Iraqi Joint Operations Command spokesperson Yahia Rasoul stated that Iraqi forces controlled 44% of Nineveh Governate. He added that CTS forces controlled 40 districts in east Mosul, while the Iraqi Army's 9th Battalion held six districts.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-security-controls-44-nineveh-mosul-battles-resume-spokesman/ |title=Iraqi security controls 44% of Nineveh as Mosul battles resume: spokesman |work=Iraqi News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161224163144/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-security-controls-44-nineveh-mosul-battles-resume-spokesman/ |archivedate=24 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 25 December, the CTS reportedly stormed into the Al-Quds district, later in the day.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/cts-storms-quds-neighborhood-clashes/ |title=CTS storms into Quds neighborhood after clashes with IS |work=Iraqi News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161226004330/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/cts-storms-quds-neighborhood-clashes/ |archivedate=26 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 26 December, Commander of Nineveh Operations Major General Najim al-Jabouri announced that new military reinforcements had arrived in the Mosul neighborhoods retaken by Iraqi forces.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/reinforcements-arrive-mosul/ |title=Commander: Military reinforcements arrive in Mosul |work=Iraqi News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161227042447/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/reinforcements-arrive-mosul/ |archivedate=27 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 27 December, the ISIL-run Amaq News Agency stated that the anti-ISIL coalition had destroyed the Old Bridge, the last functioning bridge in Mosul. The US-led Coalition stated that it had disabled a Mosul bridge with airstrikes, without providing further details.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-38442811 |title=Mosul battle: Last bridge 'disabled by air strike' |publisher=BBC |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161227153315/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-38442811 |archivedate=27 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 December, Iraqi forces launched the second phase of the battle, pushing from three directions into the remaining eastern Mosul districts. Iraqi soldiers and Federal Police entered about half a dozen southeastern districts, while the CTS advanced in the al-Quds and Karama districts. In the third front, Iraqi soldiers also pushed toward the northern city limits.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/iraqi-forces-launch-second-phase-of-mosul-offensive-against-islamic-state/article33447664/ |title=Iraqi forces launch second phase of Mosul offensive against Islamic State |first1=Isabel |last1=Coles |first2=Stephen |last2=Kalin |agency=Reuters |work=The Globe and Mail |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161229164444/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/iraqi-forces-launch-second-phase-of-mosul-offensive-against-islamic-state/article33447664/ |archivedate=29 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> An ISIL headquarters in al-Thobat district was reportedly destroyed in coalition airstrikes, killing 12 militants.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/coalition-airstrike-kills-militants-mosul/ |title=Coalition airstrike kills 12 IS militants in eastern Mosul |first=Loaa |last=Adel |publisher=Iraqi News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161229181654/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/coalition-airstrike-kills-militants-mosul/ |archivedate=29 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Later in the day, the commander of the operation declared that they had captured 2 villages to the north of Mosul, killing 70 militants.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/joint-forces-liberate-2-villages-kill-70-members-northern-mosul/ |title=Joint forces liberate 2 villages, kill 70 IS members in northern Mosul |first=Loaa |last=Adel |publisher=Iraqi News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161230002145/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/joint-forces-liberate-2-villages-kill-70-members-northern-mosul/ |archivedate=30 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi forces had captured half of the al-Quds district by early afternoon.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2016/12/29/Iraqi-forces-launch-fresh-advance-against-ISIS-inside-Mosul.html |title=Iraq forces capture half of Quds in fresh push |publisher=Al-Arabiya |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170102172051/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2016/12/29/Iraqi-forces-launch-fresh-advance-against-ISIS-inside-Mosul.html |archivedate=2 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The Iraqi Army later announced that they had killed more than 200 militants during the day.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1026495.shtml |title=Iraqi forces regain ground, kill 200 IS militants in new push to free Mosul |work=Global Times |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170101161308/http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1026495.shtml |archivedate=1 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 30 December, Iraqi security forces advanced in several areas. In the northern front, the 16th Division stormed the Habdaa district while also trying to cut off the supply lines to Tel Kayf.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN14J14I |title=Iraqi forces face fierce Islamic State combat in south Mosul |author=Isabel Coles |publisher=Reuters}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/iraqs-resumed-assault-on-is-in-mosul-makes-gains/2016/12/30/a6fa94c6-cea1-11e6-85cd-e66532e35a44_story.html |title=Iraq's resumed assault on IS in Mosul makes gains |agency=Associated Press |work=The Washington Post |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161231074905/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/iraqs-resumed-assault-on-is-in-mosul-makes-gains/2016/12/30/a6fa94c6-cea1-11e6-85cd-e66532e35a44_story.html |archivedate=31 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Ammar al-Haweidi, who was an elite leader of ISIL, was reported to have been killed by the Iraqi Federal Police.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/federal-police-kills-elite-leader-eastern-mosul/ |title=Federal Police kills IS elite leader in eastern Mosul |first=Loaa |last=Adel |publisher=Iraqi News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161231175419/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/federal-police-kills-elite-leader-eastern-mosul/ |archivedate=31 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 31 December, heavy clashes occurred at the southeastern and northern fronts of Mosul. An Iraqi Army officer deployed in the southeastern front reported that their advances had slowed down, due to heavy clashes and difficulty in differentiating between civilians and militants. Iraqi forces on the northern front advanced towards the periphery of Mosul, with an officer stating that heavy clashes were ongoing in the Argoob area.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idINKBN14K06T |title=Baghdad blasts kill 29 as Mosul fighting intensifies |first1=Kareem |last1=Raheem |first2=Ahmed |last2=Rasheed |publisher=Reuters}}</ref> The CTS destroyed four VBIEDs, when ISIL tried to attack them in the street linking al-Ta'mim neighborhood and the garage area in east Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/cts-destroys-4-car-bombs-eastern-mosul/ |title=CTS destroys 4 car bombs in eastern Mosul |first=Loaa |last=Adel |publisher=Iraqi News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170101000322/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/cts-destroys-4-car-bombs-eastern-mosul/ |archivedate=1 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== January: Capturing east Mosul ===\nIraqi forces continued their advance on 1 January 2017, capturing a part of the Karama district, taking near complete control of Intissar and Siha districts, and clearing the Salam district.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN14L0X3 |title=Islamic State attacks Iraqi police near Najaf, kills seven |first1=Isabel |last1=Coles |first2=Ali |last2=al-Rubaie |publisher=Reuters |date=1 January 2017 |accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref> The CTS linked up with Rapid Response Division during the day at the edge of al-Intissar and al-Quds, capturing more than 60% of east Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/iraq-forces-retaken-over-60-east-mosul-commander-160049845.html?bcmt=1 |title=Iraq forces have retaken over 60% of east Mosul: commander |agency=Agence France-Presse |publisher=Yahoo! News |date=1 January 2017 |accessdate=1 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170102083526/https://www.yahoo.com/news/iraq-forces-retaken-over-60-east-mosul-commander-160049845.html?bcmt=1 |archivedate=2 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Later that day, Iraqi forces captured the Yunus al-Sabaawi and Yafa districts in the southeastern part of the city, and also completely captured al-Intissar,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-forces-recapture-districts-eastern-mosul-kill-19-militants/ |title=Iraqi forces recapture more districts in eastern Mosul, kill 19 militants |first=Mohamed |last=Mostafa |publisher=Iraqi News |date=1 January 2017 |accessdate=1 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170101151309/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-forces-recapture-districts-eastern-mosul-kill-19-militants/ |archivedate=1 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> as well as the districts of al-Malayeen, al-Kindi, and al-Arabi al-Thania.<ref name=\"three Mosul districts recaptured\">{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/three-mosul-districts-recaptured-army-officer/ |title=Updated: 3 Mosul districts, strategic street recaptured: army, police |first=Mohamed |last=Mostafa |publisher=Iraqi News |date=1 January 2017 |accessdate=9 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170102180004/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/three-mosul-districts-recaptured-army-officer/ |archivedate=2 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi Federal Police also captured the Gogjali-Intsar road<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/federal-police-liberates-gogjali-intsar-road-near-mosul/ |title=Federal Police liberates Gogjali-Intsar road near Mosul |first=Loaa |last=Adel |publisher=Iraqi News |date=1 January 2017 |accessdate=2 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170101235934/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/federal-police-liberates-gogjali-intsar-road-near-mosul/ |archivedate=1 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> and the strategic No. 60 Street to the southeast of Mosul.<ref name=\"three Mosul districts recaptured\" /> On 3 January, Iraqi forces stormed three districts.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-forces-storm-industrial-district-eastern-mosul/ |title=UPDATED: Iraqi forces storm 3 districts in eastern Mosul, kill 50 militants |first=Mohamed |last=Mostafa |publisher=Iraqi News |date=3 January 2017 |accessdate=3 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170103164047/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-forces-storm-industrial-district-eastern-mosul/ |archivedate=3 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi Air Force airstrikes destroyed the office of ISIL's [[hisbah]] police located on Mosul-Tel Afar road, and several warfare utilities of the group.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-airstrikes-destroy-quarters-equipment-eastern-mosul/ |title=Iraqi airstrikes destroy IS quarters, equipment in eastern Mosul |first=Mohamed |last=Mostafa |publisher=Iraqi News |date=3 January 2017 |accessdate=3 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170103164053/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-airstrikes-destroy-quarters-equipment-eastern-mosul/ |archivedate=3 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The Iraqi Federal Police also destroyed the headquarters of Jund al-Khilafa (Soldiers of the Caliphate), an ISIL explosives factory, and a drone headquarters in al-Mithaq district.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/federal-police-destroy-jund-al-khilafa-headquarters-mosul/ |title=Federal Police forces destroy Jund al-Khilafa headquarters near Mosul |first=Loaa |last=Adel |publisher=Iraqi News |date=3 January 2017 |accessdate=3 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170103163104/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/federal-police-destroy-jund-al-khilafa-headquarters-mosul/ |archivedate=3 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Later that day, the CTS captured the Karama industrial neighborhood, the Industrial district, the Karama Silo (a flour mill), and a Mercedes Company building.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nrttv.com/EN/Details.aspx?Jimare=11883 |title=IRAQI FORCES SECURE MORE NEIGHBORHOODS IN MOSUL |publisher=NRT TV |date=3 January 2017 |accessdate=3 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170104145634/http://www.nrttv.com/EN/Details.aspx?Jimare=11883 |archivedate=4 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi forces later captured the area of exhibitions and the commercial complex to the south of the Ta'mim district,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/cts-liberates-exhibitions-commercial-complex-areas-mosul/ |title=CTS liberates exhibitions and commercial complex areas in Mosul |first=Loaa |last=Adel |publisher=Iraqi News |date=3 January 2017 |accessdate=3 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170103224403/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/cts-liberates-exhibitions-commercial-complex-areas-mosul/ |archivedate=3 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> along with the Al-Hay al-Senai and al-Mithaq districts, as well as the Maaridh area to the east of Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://aa.com.tr/en/middle-east/iraqi-forces-capture-strategic-districts-of-mosul/719643 |title=Iraqi forces capture strategic districts of Mosul |first1=Ahmed |last1=Qassem |first2=Ibrahim |last2=Saleh |publisher=Anadolu Agency |date=3 January 2017 |accessdate=3 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170104090721/http://aa.com.tr/en/middle-east/iraqi-forces-capture-strategic-districts-of-mosul/719643 |archivedate=4 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 4 January, Iraqi forces cleared the Mithaq district and advanced in al-Wahda.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/thousands-iraqis-flee-mosul-military-advances/ |title=Thousands more Iraqis flee Mosul as military advances |first=Loaa |last=Adel |publisher=Iraqi News |date=4 January 2017 |accessdate=4 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170104172358/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/thousands-iraqis-flee-mosul-military-advances/ |archivedate=4 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The United Nations stated that civilian casualties had started increasing as Iraqi forces advanced in the city.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-idUSKBN14O150 |title=More than 2,000 Iraqis a day flee Mosul as military advances |first1=Stephen |last1=Kalin |first2=Isabel |last2=Coles |publisher=Reuters |date=4 January 2017 |accessdate=4 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170104162423/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-idUSKBN14O150 |archivedate=4 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The Federal Police and 9th Division captured Wahda after heavy clashes, bringing them closer to the city center, while ISIL counter-attacks in southeastern Mosul were repelled. Iraqi forces also advanced in al-Salam, Palestine, al-Shaimaa, Domiez, and Sumer districts, amid heavy clashes;<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1027221.shtml |title=Iraqi forces advance closer to Mosul city center after recapturing new areas |agency=Xinhua |work=Global Times |date=4 January 2017 |accessdate=4 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170106010955/http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1027221.shtml |archivedate=6 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi forces later captured the al-Moallemin and Sumer districts, as well as the Mosul-Kirkuk road.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kuna.net.kw/ArticleDetails.aspx?id=2584584&language=en |title=Iraqi police kill IS leader in Mosul |publisher=Kuwait News Agency |date=4 January 2017 |accessdate=4 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170105180819/http://www.kuna.net.kw/ArticleDetails.aspx?id=2584584&language=en |archivedate=5 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On the same day, the [[United States Department of Defense]] and the anti-ISIL Coalition stated that American advisers had entered Mosul with Iraqi forces.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/business/wall-street-journal/us-troops-enter-frontline-fight-for-mosul-as-offensive-bogs-down/news-story/6d3b37d5d80683954f34cfe0f5d68512 |title=US troops enter frontline fight for Mosul as offensive bogs down |work=Wall Street Journal |via=''The Australian'' |date=4 January 2017 |accessdate=5 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 January, Lt.-Gen. Talib Shaghati stated that Iraqi forces had captured about 65\u201370% of east Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN14P0ZT |title=Iraqi general says 70 percent of east Mosul retaken from Islamic State |first1=Stephen |last1=Kalin |first2=Isabel |last2=Coles |publisher=Reuters |date=5 January 2017 |accessdate=5 January 2017}}</ref> An ISIL attack on the PMU near Tal Afar was repelled.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/drones-shot-35-militants-killed-mosul/ |title=Drones shot down, 35 militants killed in Mosul |first=Mohamed |last=Mostafa |publisher=Iraqi News |date=5 January 2017 |accessdate=5 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170105171536/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/drones-shot-35-militants-killed-mosul/ |archivedate=5 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The Federal Police announced that 1,700 ISIL fighters had been killed in the second phase. General Raed Shaker Jawdat stated that the group's headquarters in Nineveh province had been destroyed and that Iraqi forces had captured eight districts in the second phase, thus bringing the entire southeastern section of Mosul under their control. He also stated that all the remaining districts in east Mosul had been surrounded and would be stormed soon.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.news.com.au/world/breaking-news/1700-is-fighters-killed-in-a-week-in-mosul/news-story/a4d53f825dfcd756264701f7e9a48ff1 |title=1700 IS fighters killed in a week in Mosul |agency=EFE |publisher=News.com.au |date=5 January 2017 |accessdate=5 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170105141935/http://www.news.com.au/world/breaking-news/1700-is-fighters-killed-in-a-week-in-mosul/news-story/a4d53f825dfcd756264701f7e9a48ff1 |archivedate=5 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 6 January, the CTS stormed the al-Muthanna district, during an overnight raid across the al-Khawsar river,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-forces-mosul-district/ |title=Updated: Iraqi forces recapture eastern Mosul district |publisher=Iraqi News |date=6 January 2017 |accessdate=6 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170107100618/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-forces-mosul-district/ |archivedate=7 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> with the CTS later driving ISIL out of the district.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKBN14Q0ZU |title=Iraqi forces advance against Islamic State in Mosul night raid: spokesman |first1=Saif |last1=Hameed |first2=John |last2=Davison |publisher=Reuters |date=6 January 2017 |accessdate=6 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170106105208/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKBN14Q0ZU |archivedate=6 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> This advance marked the first time that Iraqi forces had entered Mosul from the north.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-idUSKBN14Q1K9 |title=In renewed push, Iraqi forces enter Mosul from north for first time |first1=Isabel |last1=Coles |first2=Saif |last2=Hameed |publisher=Reuters |date=6 January 2017 |accessdate=6 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170106144142/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-idUSKBN14Q1K9 |archivedate=6 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The CTS also launched an assault on the Hadbaa apartment complex on the northern front, sparking heavy clashes.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-rooftop-idUSKBN14R094 |title=Entering Mosul from north, Iraqi army faces gruelling urban combat |first=Isabel |last=Coles |publisher=Reuters |date=7 January 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170107111024/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-rooftop-idUSKBN14R094 |archivedate=7 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 7 January, Iraqi forces came within several hundred meters of the Tigris river. The CTS captured al-Gharfan district (previously known as al-Baath) and entered Wahda district, later capturing a hospital complex in Wahda. Meanwhile, a spokesman of the anti-ISIL coalition stated that ISIL had deliberately damaged the fourth bridge in Mosul as Iraqi forces advanced.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-idUSKBN14R08Q |title=Iraqi forces close in on Tigris river in Mosul: military spokesman |first=John |last=Davison |publisher=Reuters |date=7 January 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170107104316/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-idUSKBN14R08Q |archivedate=7 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi forces also captured ISIL's command center and two prisons,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/security-forces-seize-islamic-state-command-quarters-prisons-eastern-mosul/ |title=Security forces seize IS command quarters, prisons in eastern Mosul |publisher=Iraqi News |date=7 January 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170107181143/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/security-forces-seize-islamic-state-command-quarters-prisons-eastern-mosul/ |archivedate=7 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> as well as Rifaq, the Atibaa 1st and Atibaa 2nd districts, and the Hadbaa residential complex.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/turkish-pm-visits-iraq-amid-spat-over-unauthorized-troops/2017/01/07/1d4c42f2-d4b8-11e6-9651-54a0154cf5b3_story.html |title=Turkish PM visits Iraq amid spat over unauthorized troops |first=Sinan |last=Salaheddin |agency=Associated Press |work=The Washington Post |date=7 January 2017 |accessdate=7 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170107203158/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/turkish-pm-visits-iraq-amid-spat-over-unauthorized-troops/2017/01/07/1d4c42f2-d4b8-11e6-9651-54a0154cf5b3_story.html |archivedate=7 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 8 January, ISIL attacked CTS troops advancing towards the Sukkar and Baladiyat districts, though the attacks were repelled with the help of coalition warplanes, killing dozens of militants.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSL5N1EY0D0 |title=Iraqi forces fight Islamic State near ancient site in Mosul \u2013 Iraqi officer |first=John |last=Davison |publisher=Reuters |date=8 January 2017 |accessdate=9 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170108210643/http://www.reuters.com/article/mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSL5N1EY0D0 |archivedate=8 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The 9th Division and Federal Police had launched an attack on the Sumer and Domiz districts, on the southeastern front.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-forces-charge-new-districts-northeast-southeast-mosul/ |title=Iraqi forces charge at new districts northeast, southeast of Mosul |first=Mohamed |last=Mostafa |publisher=Iraqi News |date=8 January 2017 |accessdate=9 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170108184608/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-forces-charge-new-districts-northeast-southeast-mosul/ |archivedate=8 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The CTS spokesman said that Iraqi forces had reached the Tigris river for the first time in the offensive, advancing towards the eastern side of the fourth bridge. [[Brett McGurk]], USA's envoy to the anti-ISIL coalition, stated that ISIL's defenses in eastern Mosul were showing signs of collapse.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.sky.com/story/battle-for-mosul-iraqi-forces-reach-the-tigris-river-10722594 |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraqi forces reach the Tigris River |first=Sharon |last=Marris |publisher=Sky News |date=8 January 2017 |accessdate=9 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170109083120/https://news.sky.com/story/battle-for-mosul-iraqi-forces-reach-the-tigris-river-10722594 |archivedate=9 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Meanwhile, the PMU repelled an ISIL attack near Adaya, located to the west of Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/militias-say-killed-10-islamic-state-militants-west-mosul/ |title=Militias say killed 10 Islamic State militants west of Mosul |first=Mohamed |last=Mostafa |publisher=Iraqi News |date=8 January 2017 |accessdate=9 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170109185013/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/militias-say-killed-10-islamic-state-militants-west-mosul/ |archivedate=9 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 January, the CTS captured the Baladiyat district on the eastern front, while the Federal Police and Iraqi Army captured the Domiz and Palestine districts on the southeastern front. CTS also carried out operations to clear Furqan and Atiba districts.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1028005.shtml |title=Iraqi forces recapture 3 neighborhoods from IS in Mosul |agency=Xinhua |work=Global Times |date=9 January 2017 |accessdate=10 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170113020845/http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1028005.shtml |archivedate=13 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> ISIL was still in control of the city's water stations, and was reported to have cut the water supply to more than 30 districts that had been captured by Iraqi forces.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/01/10/isil-deliberately-cuts-water-residents-liberated-mosul/ |title=Isil cuts water supply to residents in liberated Mosul |author=Josie Ensor |work=The Telegraph |date=9 January 2017 |accessdate=10 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170111154357/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/01/10/isil-deliberately-cuts-water-residents-liberated-mosul/ |archivedate=11 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Meanwhile, the ISOF surrounded the [[University of Mosul]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.aawsat.com/2017/01/article55365243/iraqi-army-encircles-isis-laboratories-mosul |title=Iraqi Army Encircles ISIS Laboratories in Mosul |work=Asharq al-Awsat |date=9 January 2017 |accessdate=10 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170110191238/http://english.aawsat.com/2017/01/article55365243/iraqi-army-encircles-isis-laboratories-mosul |archivedate=10 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 10 January, CTS forces captured the Sukkar and al-Dhubbat districts, while advancing in the Siddeeq and al-Maliyah districts. Several governmental offices, including the communication complex, provincial electricity department, and a security headquarters were also captured by the CTS. In response to the advances, ISIL blew up two bridges to prevent Iraqi forces from attacking western Mosul. On the southeastern front, the Federal Police and Iraqi Army pushed further into al-Salam, Palestine, Sumer, Yarimja, and Sahiron districts, while on the northern front, the Iraqi Army advanced further into al-Hadbaa while capturing northern part of Sabaa Nisaan.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/11/c_135971391.htm |title=Iraqi forces advance further into IS stronghold in Mosul |publisher=Xinhua |date=11 January 2017 |accessdate=11 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170111141513/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/11/c_135971391.htm |archivedate=11 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 12 January, the CTS captured the 7th Nissan and Sadeeq districts, successfully linking up with Iraqi Army forced advancing in the Hadbaa district. CTS Spokesman al-Numan stated that Iraqi forces were now in control of about 85% of eastern Mosul. Around the same time, the Rapid Response Division advanced in the Sumer and Sahiroun districts,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUKKBN14W0ZF |title=Iraqi forces link up in north Mosul, make gains in southeast |author1=Stephen Kalin |author2=John Davison |publisher=Reuters |date=12 January 2017 |accessdate=12 January 2017}}</ref> capturing those districts later in the day.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kuna.net.kw/ArticleDetails.aspx?id=2585738&language=en |title=Iraqi regulars capture more IS strongholds in Mosul |publisher=Kuwait News Agency |date=12 January 2017 |accessdate=12 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170113162900/http://www.kuna.net.kw/ArticleDetails.aspx?id=2585738&Language=en |archivedate=13 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi forces also captured the al-Salam district. Meanwhile, the PMU captured 3 villages near Tel Abta.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/hashd-militia-liberates-3-villages-near-mosul/ |title=Hashd militia liberates 3 villages near Mosul |author=Loaa Adel |publisher=Iraqi News |date=12 January 2017 |accessdate=12 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170113023026/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/hashd-militia-liberates-3-villages-near-mosul/ |archivedate=13 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Ruins of the Mosque of Yunus.png|thumb|The ruins of the Nabi Yunus mosque after it was captured by Iraqi forces]]\nOn 13 January, the CTS reached the second bridge of the city, also called the \"Freedom Bridge.\" In response, ISIL had destroyed all five bridges of the city, in order to slow the Iraqi advance towards western Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/01/13/middleeast/iraq-mosul-troops-advance/ |title=ISIS destroys Mosul bridges as troops advance |author=Mohammed Tawfeeq |publisher=CNN |date=13 January 2017 |accessdate=13 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116172443/http://edition.cnn.com/2017/01/13/middleeast/iraq-mosul-troops-advance/ |archivedate=16 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/mosul-bridges-are-key-liberating-isis-stronghold-n706566 |title=Mosul Bridges Are Key to Liberating ISIS Stronghold |author=Alexander Smith |publisher=NBC News |date=13 January 2017 |accessdate=13 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170113163514/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/mosul-bridges-are-key-liberating-isis-stronghold-n706566 |archivedate=13 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The CTS later reached the Old Bridge of Mosul, also known as the \"Iron Bridge\", and stormed the University of Mosul, capturing a part of the university complex later in the day.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN14X0P1 |title=Iraqi forces make gains against Islamic State in Mosul |author1=Isabel Coles |author2=John Davison |publisher=NBC News |date=13 January 2017 |accessdate=13 January 2017}}</ref> The CTS also captured the al-Kafa'at district on eastern front as well as al-Sadriya, al-Naser, and al-Faisaliyah in the central part of East Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/14/c_135981007.htm |title=Iraqi forces advance in IS stronghold, recapture Mosul University |publisher=Xinhua |date=13 January 2017 |accessdate=13 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170114203822/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/14/c_135981007.htm |archivedate=14 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi Army forces also captured the Hadbaa district during the day,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/mosul-university-isis-battle-northern-iraq-forces-retake-city-terror-group-jihadis-a7526401.html |title=Fight to take Mosul back from Isis reaches gates of city's university |author=Betham McKernan |work=The Independent |date=13 January 2017 |accessdate=13 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170114192001/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/mosul-university-isis-battle-northern-iraq-forces-retake-city-terror-group-jihadis-a7526401.html |archivedate=14 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> and the CTS captured a government complex, which included the Nineveh Governorate administration and council buildings.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2017/01/13/world/middleeast/ap-ml-iraq.html |title=Iraqi Forces in IS Battle Raise Flag Over Mosul University |agency=The Associated Press |work=The New York Times |date=13 January 2017 |accessdate=13 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170115104318/http://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2017/01/13/world/middleeast/ap-ml-iraq.html |archivedate=15 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 14 January, the Rapid Response Division captured the Yarimja area and a field hospital that ISIL was using. The Federal Police also captured the highway between Mosul and [[Kirkuk]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN14Y08N |title=Iraqi forces fight IS at Mosul University, take areas along Tigris: officials |publisher=Reuters |date=14 January 2017 |accessdate=14 January 2017}}</ref> Iraqi forces later completely captured the University of Mosul, in addition to the eastern side of a third bridge.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dw.com/en/iraqi-forces-retake-mosuls-university-from-islamic-state/a-37135726 |title=Iraqi forces retake Mosul's university from 'Islamic State' |work=Deutsche Welle |date=14 January 2017 |accessdate=14 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170114215033/http://www.dw.com/en/iraqi-forces-retake-mosuls-university-from-islamic-state/a-37135726 |archivedate=14 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 15 January, Iraqi forces carried out a sweeping operation in the University of Mosul to clear out any remaining hiding militants, while continuing their advance along the Tigris river.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN14Z09G |title=Iraqi special forces sweep Mosul University for remaining militants: spokesman |publisher=Reuters |date=15 January 2017 |accessdate=15 January 2017}}</ref> The operation command later announced that the Iraqi Army had captured al-Kafaat Thani (Second) district on the northern front, while CTS had captured Andalus on the eastern front.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/150120171?keyword=Andalus |title=Mosul University: the last straw that broke the ISIS back, major weapon factory lost |publisher=Rudaw |date=15 January 2017 |accessdate=16 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116194642/http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/150120171?keyword=Andalus |archivedate=16 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/16/c_135984430.htm |title=Iraqi forces free 2 neighborhoods from IS militants in Mosul |publisher=Xinhua |date=16 January 2017 |accessdate=16 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116172016/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/16/c_135984430.htm |archivedate=16 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> ON 16 January, clashes occurred in the Shurta and Andalus districts. By this point, Iraqi forces had taken complete control of the river banks in the south.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN15011T |title=Iraqi forces free 2 neighborhoods from IS militants in Mosul |publisher=Reuters |date=16 January 2017 |accessdate=16 January 2017}}</ref> During the day, the Iraqi Army captured the Kindi and Qairawan districts, while the CTS captured Jammasa.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/17/c_135987650.htm |title=Iraqi forces push further into Mosul amid fierce clashes with IS militants |publisher=Xinhua |date=17 January 2017 |accessdate=17 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170117153809/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/17/c_135987650.htm |archivedate=17 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The CTS later captured the Nabi Yunus area, including the [[Mosques and shrines of Mosul#The Mosque of the Prophet Yunus (Jonah)|Nabi Yunus shrine]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.middleeasteye.net/news/battle-mosul-iraq-forces-retake-bombed-jonahs-tomb-854389548 |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraq forces retake IS-bombed 'Jonah's tomb' |publisher=Middle East Eye |date=16 January 2017 |accessdate=16 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170117123347/http://www.middleeasteye.net/news/battle-mosul-iraq-forces-retake-bombed-jonahs-tomb-854389548 |archivedate=17 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Battle of Mosul (17-01-17).png|thumb|The battle situation on 17 January 2017.]]\nOn 17 January, the CTS was in complete control of Shurta and Andalus, as well as the al-Muhandiseen district, and pushed into the Eastern [[Nineveh]] and Souq al-Ghanam districts. The CTS later captured the Nineveh al-Sharqiya, Bab-Shams, and Souq al-Ghanam districts on the eastern front, as well as the Nu'maniya and Uttshana districts, while storming the adjacent al-Jazair district. Meanwhile, on the northern front, the Iraqi Army captured the Kindi military base, the former headquarters of the [[2nd Division (Iraq)|2nd Division]], as well as the nearby al-Kindi facility.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-idUSKBN1511CD |title=Iraqi forces push Islamic State further back in Mosul: militar |publisher=Reuters |date=17 January 2017 |accessdate=17 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170117194023/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-idUSKBN1511CD |archivedate=17 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/17/c_135991115.htm |title=Iraqi forces in near full control of IS stronghold in eastern Mosul |publisher=Xinhua |date=17 January 2017 |accessdate=17 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170118053113/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/17/c_135991115.htm |archivedate=18 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://aa.com.tr/en/middle-east/iraqi-army-announces-fresh-gains-in-battle-for-mosul/729315 |title=Iraqi army announces fresh gains in battle for Mosul |publisher=Anadolu Agency |date=17 January 2017 |accessdate=17 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170118135925/http://aa.com.tr/en/middle-east/iraqi-army-announces-fresh-gains-in-battle-for-mosul/729315 |archivedate=18 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The CTS also captured the Al Jazair, Al Derkazlih, Al Seuis, and Sanharib districts during the day, along with the Grand Mosque of the city.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.heraldo.es/noticias/internacional/2017/01/17/el-pierde-casi-mitad-del-feudo-mosul-tras-tres-meses-ofensiva-1154038-306.html |title=EI loses almost half of Mosul fief after three months of offensive |work=[[Heraldo de Arag\u00f3n]] |date=17 January 2017 |accessdate=17 January 2017 |language=Spanish |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170118142522/http://www.heraldo.es/noticias/internacional/2017/01/17/el-pierde-casi-mitad-del-feudo-mosul-tras-tres-meses-ofensiva-1154038-306.html |archivedate=18 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/security-forces-recapture-3-districts-great-mosque-central-mosul/ |title=Security forces recapture 3 districts, Great Mosque in central Mosul |publisher=Iraqi News |date=17 January 2017 |accessdate=18 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170118004353/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/security-forces-recapture-3-districts-great-mosque-central-mosul/ |archivedate=18 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi forces also succeeded in capturing all five bridges of the city during the day, as well as the Zaraei district.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/170120171 |title=Iraqi forces control all five bridges in Mosul, ISIS 'nearly defeated' in east |publisher=Rudaw |date=17 January 2017 |accessdate=17 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170118140451/http://www.rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/170120171 |archivedate=18 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[United States Air Force]] Colonel John Dorrian stated during the day that Iraqi forces were now in control of 85\u201390% of east Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2017/01/17/iraqi-troops-capture-historic-site-in-mosul-destroyed-by-is.html |title=US military official: 85\u201390 percent of eastern Mosul cleared of ISIS militants |publisher=Fox News |date=17 January 2017 |accessdate=17 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170117190720/http://www.foxnews.com/world/2017/01/17/iraqi-troops-capture-historic-site-in-mosul-destroyed-by-is.html |archivedate=17 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On the same day, Iraqi Prime Minister Haider al-Abadi stated that Iraqi forces had begun moving against ISIL in western Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN1512CK |title=Iraq PM Abadi says Iraqi forces have begun 'moving' in west Mosul: state TV |publisher=Reuters |date=17 January 2017 |accessdate=17 January 2017}}</ref> On 18 January, Lieutenant-General Talib Shaghati announced that the CTS had captured all the districts of east Mosul they were tasked with taking, and that Iraqi forces were almost in complete control of the eastern side, though a few parts of the city in the north had yet to be captured by the Iraqi Army.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idINKBN1521AU |title=Iraq special forces chief says mission accomplished in east Mosul |publisher=Reuters |date=18 January 2017 |accessdate=18 January 2017}}</ref> All five bridges of the city were also under the control of Iraqi forces. During the day, CTS captured the ruins of [[Nineveh]], as well as the adjacent Tal Nirgal area. Meanwhile, the Iraqi Army captured the al-Qadhiyah district and were fighting on the edges of al-Arabi district.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/18/c_135994463.htm |title=Iraqi forces seize main part of eastern Mosul from IS |publisher=Xinhua |date=18 January 2017 |accessdate=18 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170131184906/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/18/c_135994463.htm |archivedate=31 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/edition/world/iraqi-troops-in-mosul-reclaim-ruins-of-jonahs-tomb-0jcpbwvx9 |title=Iraqi troops in Mosul reclaim ruins of Jonah's tomb |author=Richard Spencer |work=The Times |date=18 January 2017 |accessdate=18 January 2017}}</ref> Around the same time, the PMU captured 2 areas in the [[Nineveh plains|Nineveh Plains]] region.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/al-hashd-al-shaabi-liberates-2-areas-nineveh-plain/ |title=Al-Hashd al-Shaabi liberates 2 areas in Nineveh Plain |author=Loaa Adel |publisher=Iraq News |date=18 January 2017 |accessdate=18 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119025729/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/al-hashd-al-shaabi-liberates-2-areas-nineveh-plain/ |archivedate=19 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 19 January, the Iraqi Army captured the town of [[Tel Keppe|Tel Kayf]], to the north of Mosul (after a nearly 3-month-long siege),<ref name=\"Tel Keppe recaptured\">{{cite web |url=http://www.upi.com/Top_News/World-News/2017/01/19/Iraqi-forces-capture-Tel-Kaif-north-of-Mosul-from-Islamic-State/8981484844256/ |title=Iraqi forces capture Tel Kaif, north of Mosul, from Islamic State |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170124023432/http://www.upi.com/Top_News/World-News/2017/01/19/Iraqi-forces-capture-Tel-Kaif-north-of-Mosul-from-Islamic-State/8981484844256/ |archivedate=24 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Tel Kaif\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/190120171 |title=UPDATED: Iraqi forces take full control over Tel Kaif, north of Mosul |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170120090144/http://www.rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/190120171 |archivedate=20 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> as well as the Nineveh Oberoi hotel and the \"Palaces\" area on the eastern bank of the Tigris. Clashes continued in the Al-Arabi District.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN1531XY |title=Most Islamic State commanders in Mosul already killed, Iraqi general says |author=Isabel Coles |publisher=Reuters |date=19 January 2017 |accessdate=19 January 2017}}</ref> The Iraqi Air Force carried out an airstrike in al-Zerai area in Mosul, reportedly killing five ISIL leaders including Abdel Wahed Khodier, assistant to [[Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi]]; the Islamic Police Chief in Nineveh, Ahmed Khodier Sayer al-Juwan and Agriculture Minister in Tal Afar and Mahlabiya, Abdel Karim Khodier Sayer al-Juwan.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/airstrike-kills-two-senior-leaders-islamic-state-central-mosul/ |title=Airstrike kills two senior leaders of Islamic State in central Mosul |author=Loaa Adel |publisher=Iraq News |date=19 January 2017 |accessdate=19 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119202113/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/airstrike-kills-two-senior-leaders-islamic-state-central-mosul/ |archivedate=19 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi Iraqi forces also captured the Fadiliyah district and the Jaber ibn Hayyan military facility,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kuna.net.kw/ArticleDetails.aspx?id=2587872&Language=en |title=Iraqi forces retake new neighborhoods in Mosul |publisher=Kuwait News Agency |date=19 January 2017 |accessdate=19 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170131191451/http://www.kuna.net.kw/ArticleDetails.aspx?id=2587872&Language=en |archivedate=31 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> as well as the Ghabat area.<ref name=major-district>{{cite web |url=http://www.rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/20012017 |title=UPDATE: Iraqi army liberates major district in north of Mosul |publisher=Rudaw |date=20 January 2017 |accessdate=20 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170131191454/http://www.rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/20012017 |archivedate=31 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 20 January, the 9th Division captured the [[free economic zone|free zone]] in the northern sector of Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kuna.net.kw/ArticleDetails.aspx?id=2587966&language=en |title=Iraqi regular forces capture more areas in Mosul |publisher=Kuwait News Agency |date=20 January 2017 |accessdate=20 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170131191513/http://www.kuna.net.kw/ArticleDetails.aspx?id=2587966&language=en |archivedate=31 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi forces also captured a pharmaceutical plant to the north of Mosul, as well as the Al-Arabi 1 district, while clashing with ISIL in the Rashidiyah district. Meanwhile, the CTS started performing clearing operations in the districts they had captured in east Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/21/c_136000915.htm |title=Iraqi forces fight to defeat last IS strongholds in eastern Mosul |publisher=Xinhua |date=20 January 2017 |accessdate=20 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170131191516/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/21/c_136000915.htm |archivedate=31 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=major-district />\n\n[[File:Bataille de Mossoul 25 janvier 2017.svg|thumb|The Battle situation on 25 January 2017 {{small|(full liberation of eastern Mosul)}}]]\nOn 21 January, Iraqi forces continued advancing in the outskirts of the city. The Iraqi Arm captured the al-Arabi district, as well as al-Qousiyat village, killing some 40 militants killed and destroying four car bombs.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/22/c_136002730.htm |title=Iraqi forces continue fighting at last IS strongholds in eastern Mosul |publisher=Xinhua |date=21 January 2017 |accessdate=21 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170131191556/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/22/c_136002730.htm |archivedate=31 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The CJTF\u2013OIR Coalition also announced that between 19 and 21 January, they had targeted a flotilla of 90 boats and three barges being used by ISIL to cross the Tigris and escape the clashes.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2017/01/21/coalition-warplanes-target-islamic-state-fleet-mosul/96877934/ |title=Coalition warplanes take out Islamic State fleet in Mosul |first=Jim |last=Michaels |work=USA Today |date=21 January 2017 |accessdate=21 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170121181757/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2017/01/21/coalition-warplanes-target-islamic-state-fleet-mosul/96877934/ |archivedate=21 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On the same day, Coalition officials stated that the fight for west Mosul was expected to be tougher than the fight for east Mosul.<ref name=\"tougher fight\">{{cite web |url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2017/01/21/iraqi-forces-eye-tougher-fight-in-mosul-west.html |title=Iraqi forces eye tougher fight in Mosul's west |date=21 January 2017 |publisher=Fox News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122011621/http://www.foxnews.com/world/2017/01/21/iraqi-forces-eye-tougher-fight-in-mosul-west.html |archivedate=22 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 22 January, the Iraqi Army captured the Al-Milayeen district and Al-Binaa al-Jahiz area, as well as the Mosul-[[Dohuk]] road. By this point, only the Rashidiyah district was left under ISIL control in eastern Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/iraq-forces-two-more-neighbourhoods-east-mosul-153451700.html |title=Iraq forces take two more areas in east Mosul |first1=Mostafa |last1=Abulezz |first2=Jean-Marc |last2=Mojon |agency=Agence France-Presse |publisher=Yahoo! News |date=22 January 2017 |accessdate=22 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170131191620/https://www.yahoo.com/news/iraq-forces-two-more-neighbourhoods-east-mosul-153451700.html |archivedate=31 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 23 January, the Iraqi Army entered the Rashidiyah district.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN157231 |title=Iraqi forces claim recapture of eastern Mosul after 100 days of fighting |first1=Maher |last1=Chmaytelli |first2=Saif |last2=Hameed |publisher=Reuters |date=23 January 2017 |accessdate=23 January 2017}}</ref> On 24 January, Iraqi troops captured the Rashidiyah district, as well as the villages of Ba'wiza, Shrikhan and Baysan. Following these advances, [[Prime Minister of Iraq|Iraqi Prime Minister]] [[Haider al-Abadi]] later announced the \"full liberation\" of eastern Mosul.<ref name=\"Eastern Mosul liberated\"/>\n\n=== Interlude ===\n[[File:Iraqi soldiers and civilians in eastern Mosul.png|thumb|Iraqi soldiers talk with and are greeted by civilians in eastern Mosul]]\nOn 25 January, the PMU announced that they took over Tel Shana, a strategic hill in [[Saladin Governorate|Salaheddin Province]], after killing dozens of ISIL militants. It added that PMUs also took over the villages of \u0650Arab Leith, Mohamed al-Awad and Ard Mosaltan after intense fights with the extremist group.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/features/pmus-kills-dozens-salahuddin-operations-secure-highways-continue/ |title=PMUs kills dozens of IS in Salahuddin as operations to secure highways continue |publisher=Iraqi News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170125165350/http://www.iraqinews.com/features/pmus-kills-dozens-salahuddin-operations-secure-highways-continue/ |archivedate=25 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 28 January, the PMU's 2nd Brigade repelled an attack launched by ISIL on the al-Kobayrat area, to the west of Mosul, killing 40 militants.<ref>{{cite web |title=Al-Hashd al-Shaabi repels Islamic State attack west of Mosul, 40 militants killed |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/hashd-repels-islamic-state-attack-mosul/ |publisher=Iraqi News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170128150340/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/hashd-repels-islamic-state-attack-mosul/ |archivedate=28 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 February, the PMU captured the villages of Bostan Radif and Um Gharba, as well as the Sherka region of western Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/pmus-recapture-western-mosul-villages-army-holds-off-sneaking-members/ |title=PMUs recapture western Mosul villages, army holds off sneaking IS members |publisher=Iraqi News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170203125303/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/pmus-recapture-western-mosul-villages-army-holds-off-sneaking-members/ |archivedate=3 February 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 13 February, more than 200 ISIL fighters launched an attack on three villages to the west of Tal Afar, with tanks and VBIEDs, to regain access between western Mosul and Raqqa. The attack was repelled by the PMU, resulting in deaths of more than 50 ISIL fighters and the destruction of 17 VBIEDs.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-02/13/c_136053821.htm |title=IS launches tank attack on Iraqi paramilitary units west of Mosul |date=13 February 2017 |publisher=Xinhua |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170214103017/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-02/13/c_136053821.htm |archivedate=14 February 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Another attack on a village to the south of the area was repelled, resulting in deaths of 13 militants according to the Federal Police.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/federal-police-repulses-attack-mosul-militants-killed/ |title=Federal Police repulses IS attack south of Mosul, 13 militants killed |date=13 February 2017 |publisher=Iraqi News |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170220094255/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/federal-police-repulses-attack-mosul-militants-killed/ |archivedate=20 February 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Airstrikes by the anti-ISIL coalition killed Haqi Ismail Hamid al-Emri, a former member of [[al-Qaeda in Iraq]] who played a leadership role of ISIL's security networks in Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/conditions-have-been-set-isis-defeat-west-mosul-us-led-coalition-group-says-1608103 |title='Conditions have been set' for Isis defeat in West Mosul, US-led coalition group says |date=23 February 2017 |publisher=IBTimes |author=Ananya Roy |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170224133106/http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/conditions-have-been-set-isis-defeat-west-mosul-us-led-coalition-group-says-1608103 |archivedate=24 February 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Aftermath ==\n=== Post-victory clashes ===\n;July\nOn 22 July, Iraqi security forces arrested ISIL's minister of agriculture, Falah Rashid, in western Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.basnews.com/index.php/en/news/iraq/365377 |title=IS Minister of Agriculture Arrested in West Mosul |publisher=Basnews |date=22 July 2017 |accessdate=23 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170728160226/http://www.basnews.com/index.php/en/news/iraq/365377 |archivedate=28 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Four police personnel, including a lieutenant general, were killed at al-Maash market after clashing with ISIL militants on 25 July.<ref>{{cite web |title=Four police personnel killed in Islamic State attack in western Mosul market |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/four-police-personnel-killed-islamic-state-attack-western-mosul-market/ |publisher=Iraqi News |accessdate=25 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170725233117/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/four-police-personnel-killed-islamic-state-attack-western-mosul-market/ |archivedate=25 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> ISIL senior leader, Saad Maan, who held the post of \"tribal affairs bureau for southern Mosul\" was arrested in eastern Mosul while crossing the Tigris River carrying a fake ID.<ref>{{cite web |title=Senior Islamic State leader arrested in eastern Mosul: ministry |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/senior-islamic-state-leader-arrested-eastern-mosul-ministry/ |publisher=Iraqi News |accessdate=25 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170725183138/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/senior-islamic-state-leader-arrested-eastern-mosul-ministry/ |archivedate=25 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nMeanwhile, many news outlets reported the end of the battle during the mid-to-late-July period, with the focus of Iraqi forces now being hunting down surviving militants, clearing explosives and dead bodies.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mosul: Corpses, booby traps and snipers are everywhere in devastated city |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2017/07/20/challenge-rebuilding-mosul-isis/488223001/ |work=USA Today |first=Igor |last=Kossov |date=22 July 2017 |quote=Rebuilding after the nine-month offensive that ended in July will take years and billions of dollars, but the priority now is to make the city safe enough for residents to return. That means hunting down Islamic State stragglers, removing thousands of bodies and locating all the bombs that could still go off. |access-date=3 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502060015/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2017/07/20/challenge-rebuilding-mosul-isis/488223001/ |archive-date=2 May 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=After Mosul victory, Iraq mulls future of Shiite militias |url=http://abcnews.go.com/amp/International/wireStory/mosul-victory-iraq-mulls-future-shiite-militias-48810363 |agency=Associated Press |publisher=ABC News |date=24 July 2017 |quote=In the wake of victory against the Islamic State group in Mosul, Iraq's political, religious and military leaders are debating the future of the country's powerful Shiite militias \u2014 the tens of thousands of men who answered a religious call to arms three years ago and played a critical role in beating back the extremists. |access-date=3 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190217142413/https://abcnews.go.com/amp/International/wireStory/mosul-victory-iraq-mulls-future-shiite-militias-48810363 |archive-date=17 February 2019 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"gulf-times.com\">{{cite web |title=Teen girl suspected of fleeing Germany to join IS identified in Iraq |url=http://www.gulf-times.com/story/557484/Teen-girl-suspected-of-fleeing-Germany-to-join-IS- |date=22 July 2017 |quote=Islamic State militants were ousted from Mosul, Iraq's second-largest city, earlier this month following a gruelling US-backed campaign that has left much of the city in ruins. |access-date=3 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190217142309/https://www.gulf-times.com/story/557484/Teen-girl-suspected-of-fleeing-Germany-to-join-IS- |archive-date=17 February 2019 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"gulf-times.com\"/>\n\nNineveh police captain Saeed Najm said on 30 July that three ISIL leaders were killed while escaping western Mosul to the east via Tigris.<ref>{{cite web |title=Three IS leaders killed escaping to eastern Mosul via Tigris |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/three-leaders-killed-escaping-eastern-mosul-via-tigris/ |publisher=Iraqi News |accessdate=30 July 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170730152059/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/three-leaders-killed-escaping-eastern-mosul-via-tigris/ |archive-date=30 July 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n;August\n''[[Sudan Tribune]]'' reported on 5 August that Ali Abdel-Ma'arouf ([[Pseudonym|aka]] Abu al-Asbat Al-Sudani), a Sudanese national, who was ISIL head of prisons and a top legislator, was killed during recent clearing operations in Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sudanese Jihadist killed in Mosul, mourning ceremony held back home |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/sudanese-jihadist-killed-mosul-mourning-ceremony-held-back-home/ |publisher=Iraqi News |accessdate=6 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170806085214/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/sudanese-jihadist-killed-mosul-mourning-ceremony-held-back-home/ |archive-date=6 August 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 8 August, a security source said that ISF in coordination with the Nineveh police, had arrested Ahmed Sabhan Abdel Wahid al-Dulaimi, a senior ISIL intelligence official, in east Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |title=Security forces arrest IS senior intelligence official in Mosul |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/security-forces-arrest-senior-intelligence-official-mosul/ |publisher=Iraqi News |accessdate=8 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808133627/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/security-forces-arrest-senior-intelligence-official-mosul/ |archive-date=8 August 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Federal Police forces killed a senior ISIL judge, Abdul-Sattar Mohamed Ali, aka Abi al-Hakam al-Aawar, in a raid at a basement in the Old City.<ref>{{cite web |title=Police kill senior Islamic State judge in Old City of Mosul |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/police-kill-senior-islamic-state-judge-old-city-mosul/ |publisher=Iraqi News |accessdate=9 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170809201057/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/police-kill-senior-islamic-state-judge-old-city-mosul/ |archive-date=9 August 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 10 August, a source revealed that two civilians were killed and three others wounded when ISIL gunmen opened fire on them. Meanwhile, Federal Police chief, Shaker Jawdat, said in a statement that 47 ISIL members had been killed and arrested since the beginning of July. He also added that 192 explosive belts, ten tons of ammonia nitrates and five barrels of C4 and six booby-trapping workshops were seized.<ref>{{cite web |title=IS kill, wound 5 civilians at Mosul bridge, IS month deaths declared |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/kill-wound-5-civilians-mosul-bridge-month-deaths-declared/ |publisher=Iraqi News |accessdate=10 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811054846/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/kill-wound-5-civilians-mosul-bridge-month-deaths-declared/ |archive-date=11 August 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nJawdat stated on 11 August that a workshop for manufacturing Katyusha rockets was found in Mesherfa district. Nineveh police intelligence department's Cap. Ahmed al-Obeidi told BasNews that they confiscated the biggest workshop used by ISIL to manufacture explosive belts and rockets in western Mosul.<ref>{{cite web |title=Three IS members killed, biggest explosives workshop found in western Mosul |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/three-members-killed-biggest-explosives-workshop-found-western-mosul/ |publisher=Iraqi News |accessdate=11 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170813220705/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/three-members-killed-biggest-explosives-workshop-found-western-mosul/ |archive-date=13 August 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nSecurity forces arrested an unnamed ISIL military commander for eastern Mosul area, along with ten others in Mosul on 14 August.<ref>{{cite web |title=Intelligence agency says senior IS military leader arrested in Mosul |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/intelligence-agency-says-senior-military-leader-arrested-mosul/ |publisher=Iraqi News |accessdate=14 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170820202609/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/intelligence-agency-says-senior-military-leader-arrested-mosul/ |archive-date=20 August 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nFederal Police chief, Lt. Gen. Shaker Jawdat, said in a statement that an ISIL chemical reservoir was found in Mekkawi street in the Old City. It contained C4, ammonia and other substances.<ref>{{cite web |title=Iraqi troops run into Islamic State chemicals reservoir in Mosul |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-troops-run-islamic-state-chemicals-reservoir-mosul/ |publisher=Iraqi News |accessdate=17 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170817135038/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-troops-run-islamic-state-chemicals-reservoir-mosul/ |archive-date=17 August 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n;October\nLieutenant-Colonel Abdul Salam al-Jabouri said on 12 October that some ISIL terrorists who had survived the military offensive in Mosul were detected in the marshlands area alongside near the Tigris, after they sent threats to some Tribal Mobilization leaders via SMS.<ref name=\"new activity\">{{cite news |url=http://www.thebaghdadpost.com/en/story/18156/Security-forces-detect-new-activity-for-ISIS-terrorists-in-Mosul |title=Security forces detect new activity for ISIS terrorists in Mosul |work=Baghdad Post |access-date=12 October 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171013120401/http://www.thebaghdadpost.com/en/story/18156/Security-forces-detect-new-activity-for-ISIS-terrorists-in-Mosul |archive-date=13 October 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n;January 2018\nAbu Omer, an ISIL leader who was notorious for appearing in ISIL's execution videos, was reported to have been captured in January 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/iraqis-find-isis-executioner-in-mosul-ruins-7rsvrmk86|title=Iraqis find Isis executioner in Mosul ruins|work=The Telegraph|access-date=4 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180105124621/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/iraqis-find-isis-executioner-in-mosul-ruins-7rsvrmk86|archive-date=5 January 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Hisham al-Hashimi, adviser to the Iraqi government and other Middle Eastern government on ISIL matters, confirmed his identity.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newsweek.com/who-abu-omer-isis-executioner-found-ruins-mosul-after-citys-fall-769370|title=WHO IS ABU OMER? ISIS EXECUTIONER FOUND IN RUINS OF MOSUL AFTER CITY'S FALL|work=Newsweek|access-date=4 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180104170530/http://www.newsweek.com/who-abu-omer-isis-executioner-found-ruins-mosul-after-citys-fall-769370|archive-date=4 January 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== Subsequent offensives ===\n{{See also|Battle of Tal Afar (2017)|Hawija offensive (2017)}}\nDuring the last stages of battle to retake Mosul, [[Lise Grande]] stated that per an initial assessment, basic infrastructure repair will cost over US$1 billion. She stated that while stabilization in east Mosul can be achieved in two months, in some districts of Mosul it might take years, with six out of 44 districts almost completely destroyed. All the districts of Mosul received light or moderate damage.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN19Q28F |title=Basic infrastructure repair in Mosul will cost over $1 billion: U.N. |publisher=Reuters |date=5 July 2017 |accessdate=10 July 2017}}</ref> Per the United Nations, 15 districts out of the 54 residential districts in the western half of Mosul were heavily damaged while at least 23 were moderately damaged in the battle. The UN also estimated that more than 5,000 buildings have been damaged and another 490 were destroyed in the Old City alone during the battle.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-40558836 |publisher=BBC News |date=10 July 2017 |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraq PM Abadi formally declares victory |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170711051709/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-40558836 |archivedate=11 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[Amnesty International]] accused Iraqi and United States forces of using unnecessarily powerful weapons.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-40564159 |title=Mosul: US commander says Iraq must stop Islamic State 2.0 |publisher=BBC |date=11 July 2017 |accessdate=11 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170716072826/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-40564159 |archivedate=16 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Sporadic clashes occurred after the victory declaration as Iraqi troops targeted holdouts.<ref name=\"holdouts\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-40569090 |title=Mosul: Clashes continue as troops target IS 'holdouts' |publisher=BBC News |date=11 July 2017 |accessdate=11 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170713054212/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-40569090 |archivedate=13 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Fighting continued in the Imam Gharbi village to the south of Mosul<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKBN19W0NN |title=Islamic State tightens grip on village near Mosul after defeat |work=Reuters |date=11 July 2017 |accessdate=11 July 2017}}</ref> and it was recaptured by Iraqi forces on 20 July.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-07/20/c_136459168.htm |title=Iraqi forces recapture village from IS militants in Salahudin province |publisher=Xinhua News Agency |date=20 July 2017 |accessdate=21 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170720113339/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-07/20/c_136459168.htm |archivedate=20 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> According to the [[American Schools of Oriental Research]], [[Destruction of cultural heritage by ISIL|IS damaged]] 15 religious sites in Mosul, while Coalition forces damaged 47, of which 38 were largely destroyed.<ref>{{cite news |title=War in the Arab world has devastated the region's heritage |url=https://www.economist.com/news/middle-east-and-africa/21726750-jihadists-are-not-only-ones-blame-war-arab-world-has-devastated |accessdate=19 August 2017 |work=[[The Economist]] |date=19 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170818234547/https://www.economist.com/news/middle-east-and-africa/21726750-jihadists-are-not-only-ones-blame-war-arab-world-has-devastated |archive-date=18 August 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe Iraqi forces launched a ground offensive to retake Tal Afar, one of the last cities held by the militants, located {{convert|55|km|mi}} west of Mosul, on 20 August 2017.<ref>{{cite news |title=IS conflict: Iraq launches ground offensive in Tal Afar |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/amp/world-middle-east-40990509 |accessdate=19 August 2017 |work=[[BBC]] |date=20 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170821011834/http://www.bbc.com/news/amp/world-middle-east-40990509 |archive-date=21 August 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The city was captured on 28 August, with Iraqi forces capturing the rest of the district by 2 September.\n\nFollowing the end of the Tal Afar offensive, the Iraqi Army launched another offensive to retake the ISIL-controlled Hawija Pocket on 20 September 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://isis.liveuamap.com/en/2017/21-september-the-iraqi-army-and-the-pmu-control-4-villages|title=The Iraqi army and the PMU control 4 villages in North-East of Sharqat|publisher=isis.liveuamap.com|accessdate=5 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171002113424/https://isis.liveuamap.com/en/2017/21-september-the-iraqi-army-and-the-pmu-control-4-villages|archive-date=2 October 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Humanitarian issues and human rights abuses ==\n{{Main|Human rights abuses during the Battle of Mosul (2016\u201317)}}\nUp to 1.5 million civilians lived in the city, sparking concerns among various organizations of a large humanitarian crisis.<ref name=\"afp1017\">{{cite news |title=Battle for Mosul sparks fears of humanitarian crisis |url=http://www.timeslive.co.za/world/2016/10/17/Battle-for-Mosul-sparks-fears-of-humanitarian-crisis |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=Times LIVE |agency=Agence France Press |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017132839/http://www.timeslive.co.za/world/2016/10/17/Battle-for-Mosul-sparks-fears-of-humanitarian-crisis |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[Lise Grande]], the United Nations' humanitarian coordinator in Iraq, stated, \"In a worst-case scenario, we're literally looking at the single largest humanitarian operation in the world in 2016.\"<ref name=\"afp1017\" /> [[Save the Children]] warned that massive civilian bloodshed was likely, unless safe routes were authorized to let civilians flee.<ref>{{cite news |title=Children's charity warns Mosul population could face bloodshed without safe routes |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/171020161 |accessdate=18 October 2016 |agency=rudaw.net |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161229093549/http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/171020161 |archivedate=29 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The U.S. government has accused ISIL of using civilians as [[human shield]]s.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37699233 |title=Mosul battle: US says IS using human shields |date=2016-10-19 |publisher=BBC News|access-date=2017-02-06 |language=en-GB |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116235621/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37699233 |archivedate=16 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== ISIL abuses, abductions and atrocities ===\nFears that civilians could be used as human shields by ISIL were realized as it was confirmed the group had been abducting civilians from villages for this purpose, which received widespread condemnation from human rights groups and the [[United Nations Security Council]].<ref name=\"ap1102\">{{cite news |title=The Latest: UN alarmed at Islamic State using human shields |url=https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2016-11-02/the-latest-aid-agency-mosul-civilians-face-grave-danger |accessdate=2 November 2016 |agency=Associated Press |date=2 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220074813/http://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2016-11-02/the-latest-aid-agency-mosul-civilians-face-grave-danger |archivedate=20 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Mosul battle: US says IS using human shields |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37699233 |publisher=BBC News |date=19 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170116235621/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37699233 |archivedate=16 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nShortly after the battle began, news surfaced of ISIL kidnapping and executing civilians in Mosul. Pentagon spokesman Capt. Jeff Davis stated that ISIL was using civilians as human shields and holding people against their will in the city.<ref name=\"bbc1019\">{{cite news |title=Mosul battle: US says IS using human shields |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37699233 |accessdate=19 October 2016 |publisher=BBC News |date=19 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019225517/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37699233 |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe ''[[International Business Times]]'' reported that ISIL has forced boys from Mosul as young as 12 to fight for them, and that ISIL had trained the children to \"behead prisoners and make suicide bombs.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/caliphate-cubs-young-12-ordered-fight-by-isis-mosul-1590305 |title=Caliphate Cubs as young as 12 ordered to fight by Isis in Mosul |first=Callum |last=Paton |date=7 November 2016 |work=International Business Times |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170131062628/http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/caliphate-cubs-young-12-ordered-fight-by-isis-mosul-1590305 |archivedate=31 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nAn Iraqi intelligence source stated on 21 October that ISIL executed 284 men and boys abducted from Mosul for the purpose of using them as human shields. The civilians were shot and put in a mass grave. A United Nations official said the UN is \"gravely worried\" about the fate of 200 families from Somalia and 350 families from Najafia who were abducted Monday by ISIL, who could be used as human shields.<ref name=\"cnn1021\">{{cite news |last1=Tawfeeq |first1=Mohammed |last2=Smith-Spark |first2=Laura |last3=Park |first3=Madison |last4=Alkhshali |first4=Hamdi |title=Source: ISIS executes hundreds of Mosul area residents |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/21/middleeast/iraq-kirkuk-attacks/ |accessdate=22 October 2016 |publisher=CNN |date=21 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161022013507/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/21/middleeast/iraq-kirkuk-attacks/ |archivedate=22 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 October, CNN reported that ISIL has been carrying out \"retribution killings\" of civilians as revenge for others welcoming Iraqi and Peshmerga troops in villages restored under government control.<ref name=\"cnn1026\"/>\n\n=== Allegations against anti-ISIL forces ===\nThe presence with Iraqi forces of several militias with histories of human rights abuses was criticized; Human Rights Watch called for Shia militias from the Popular Mobilization Forces (PMF) not to enter Mosul, following allegations of abuse of Sunni Muslims in anti-ISIL operations in [[Battle of Fallujah (2016)|Fallujah]], [[Second Battle of Tikrit|Tikrit]] and [[Siege of Amirli|Amirli]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Ban militias with abuse records from Mosul fight: HRW |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/07/ban-militias-abuse-records-mosul-fight-hrw-160731082420989.html |accessdate=26 October 2016 |publisher=Al Jazeera |date=26 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161027055233/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/07/ban-militias-abuse-records-mosul-fight-hrw-160731082420989.html |archivedate=27 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Wille |first1=Belkis |title=How Retaking Mosul Could Spell Disaster for Civilians |url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2016/10/14/how-retaking-mosul-could-spell-disaster-civilians |accessdate=26 October 2016 |publisher=Human Rights Watch |date=14 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161027060140/https://www.hrw.org/news/2016/10/14/how-retaking-mosul-could-spell-disaster-civilians |archivedate=27 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Dolamari |first1=Mewan |title=US accepts Shia-militia role in Mosul battle despite human rights abuses |url=http://www.kurdistan24.net/en/news/592a25ae-efa0-4753-80b8-949ecf587307/US-accepts-Shia-militia-role-in-Mosul-battle-despite-human-rights-abuses |accessdate=26 October 2016 |publisher=kurdistan24.net |date=7 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161024214751/http://www.kurdistan24.net/en/news/592a25ae-efa0-4753-80b8-949ecf587307/US-accepts-Shia-militia-role-in-Mosul-battle-despite-human-rights-abuses |archivedate=24 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi Prime Minister Haider al-Abadi later stated that only the Iraqi army and the Iraqi national police would enter the city itself.<ref name=\"cnn1016\" /><ref name=\"of1017\">{{cite news |title=Trompettes et tambours m\u00e9diatiques pour la reconqu\u00eate de Mossoul |url=http://www.ouest-france.fr/monde/irak/trompettes-et-tambours-mediatiques-pour-la-reconquete-de-mossoul-4565599 |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=Ouest-France |date=17 October 2016 |language=fr-FR |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20161031070410/http://www.ouest-france.fr/monde/irak/trompettes-et-tambours-mediatiques-pour-la-reconquete-de-mossoul-4565599 |archivedate=31 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 October, ''[[International Business Times]]'' reported that \"disturbing and graphic footage posted to social media allegedly shows Iraqi security forces [[torture|torturing]] and interrogating young children for information about ISIL as they attempt to retake Mosul from the Islamic State terror group.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi Forces Torture Child With Hammer For ISIS Information: In War On Islamic State, Is Iraq Torturing Innocent Civilians? |url=http://www.ibtimes.com/iraqi-forces-torture-child-hammer-isis-information-war-islamic-state-iraq-torturing-2435190 |work=[[International Business Times]] |date=21 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161022022928/http://www.ibtimes.com/iraqi-forces-torture-child-hammer-isis-information-war-islamic-state-iraq-torturing-2435190 |archivedate=22 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March, a U.S.-led coalition [[2017 Mosul airstrike|airstrike in Mosul]] killed more than 200 civilians.<ref>\"[http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/03/voices-concern-high-civilian-deaths-mosul-170325111006277.html Coalition says it hit Mosul site where civilians died] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170325145630/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/03/voices-concern-high-civilian-deaths-mosul-170325111006277.html |date=25 March 2017}}\". Al Jazeera. 26 March 2017.</ref><ref>\"[https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-air-strike-mosul-200-civilians-killed-isis-northern-iraq-pentagon-central-command-islamic-state-a7651451.html US admits it conducted Mosul air strike 'at location' where '200' civilians died] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170401144628/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-air-strike-mosul-200-civilians-killed-isis-northern-iraq-pentagon-central-command-islamic-state-a7651451.html |date=1 April 2017}}\". ''The Independent.'' 26 March 2017.</ref> [[Amnesty International]]'s senior investigator on crisis response said: \"The high civilian toll suggests that coalition forces leading the offensive in Mosul have failed to take adequate precautions to prevent civilian deaths, in flagrant violation of international humanitarian law.\"<ref>\"[https://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2017/03/iraq-civilians-killed-by-airstrikes-in-their-homes-after-they-were-told-not-to-flee-mosul/ Iraq: Civilians killed by airstrikes in their homes after they were told not to flee Mosul] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170401145402/https://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2017/03/iraq-civilians-killed-by-airstrikes-in-their-homes-after-they-were-told-not-to-flee-mosul/ |date=1 April 2017}}\". Amnesty International. 28 March 2017.</ref>\n\nAn estimate in mid-July 2017 by Kurdish intelligence put the total number of civilian casualties at 40,000. The largest portion of this loss of life is attributable to the unyielding artillery bombardment by Iraqi government forces \u2013 in particular, units of the Iraqi Federal Police \u2013 of west Mosul. Killings by ISIL and air strikes were two other significant sources of civilian deaths.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Cockburn |first=Patrick |authorlink=Patrick Cockburn |date=19 July 2017 |title=The massacre of Mosul: 40,000 feared dead in battle to take back city from Isis as scale of civilian casualties revealed |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/mosul-massacre-battle-isis-iraq-city-civilian-casualties-killed-deaths-fighting-forces-islamic-state-a7848781.html |newspaper=The Independent |access-date= 19 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170719205134/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/mosul-massacre-battle-isis-iraq-city-civilian-casualties-killed-deaths-fighting-forces-islamic-state-a7848781.html |archivedate=19 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== Use of chemical weapons ===\nThe [[World Health Organization]] stated on 4 March 2017 that twelve people were being treated in [[Erbil, Iraq|Erbil]] for possible exposure to chemical weapons in Mosul. The WHO said that they had enabled \"an emergency response plan to safely treat men, women and children who may be exposed to the highly toxic chemical[s]\" and were preparing for more patients with exposure to these agents. According to the UN, four patients show \"severe signs associated with exposure to a blister agent\", which they were exposed to on the eastern side of the city.<ref>[http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/03/alleged-mosul-chemical-attack-amounts-war-crime-170304132854968.html \"Alleged Mosul chemical attack mounts to war crime\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170304164307/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/03/alleged-mosul-chemical-attack-amounts-war-crime-170304132854968.html |date=4 March 2017}}, via aljazeera.com. Retrieved 4 March 2017</ref><ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-mosul-chemical-idUSKBN16B074?il=0 \"Twelve treated for chemical weapons agent...\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731013039/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-mosul-chemical-idUSKBN16B074?il=0 |date=31 July 2017}}, via reuters.com. Retrieved 4 March 2017</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, American and Australian advisory forces embedded with Iraqi units were attacked with low-grade, \"rudimentary\" chemical weapons during an offensive.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-04-19/australian-medics-treated-iraqis-hit-by-is-chemical-attack/8452144 |title=Australian soldiers caught up in Islamic State chemical attack in Mosul |last=March |first=Stephanie |date=20 April 2017 |publisher=ABC News (Australia)|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170425041821/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-04-19/australian-medics-treated-iraqis-hit-by-is-chemical-attack/8452144|archive-date=25 April 2017|url-status=live|access-date=25 April 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== Displacements and relief efforts ===\nItalian [[Filippo Grandi]], the [[United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees|UN High Commissioner for Refugees]], arrived in [[Erbil]] on 17 October to meet with Kurdish officials.<ref>{{cite news |title=UN: Protection of civilians must be ensured in Mosul offensive |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/171020162 |accessdate=18 October 2016 |publisher=Rudaw Media Network |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019013359/http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/171020162 |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The UN has set up five refugee camps capable of taking up to 45,000 people and has the capability of taking in up to 120,000 if more sites are available for camps.<ref name=\"cnn1018\">{{cite news |last1=Paton Walsh |first1=Nick |last2=McKirdy |first2=Euan |title=Mosul: Territory recaptured from ISIS |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/18/middleeast/mosul-isis-operation-iraq/index.html |accessdate=18 October 2016 |publisher=CNN |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018084717/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/18/middleeast/mosul-isis-operation-iraq/index.html |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Dozens of families from Mosul arrived in the [[Al-Hawl]] camp in [[Rojava]], Northern Syria, bringing the number of Iraqis in al-Hawl to more than 6,000. On 18 October, more than 2,000 refugees from Mosul were attempting to cross into Syria, according to the [[People's Protection Units|People's Defense Units]] (YPG).<ref name=\"rudaw1018\"/> The UN is attempting to communicate with citizens inside Mosul that they should not flee to the West of the city toward Syria, an area still under ISIL control, but to the camps in the east.<ref>{{cite news |title=Dozens of Mosul IDP families arrive in Rojava |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/syria/181020161 |accessdate=18 October 2016 |agency=Rudaw Media Network |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026114831/http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/syria/181020161 |archivedate=26 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nAustralia announced it would donate US$7.5 million in humanitarian aid to the operation, and New Zealand pledged NZ$1 million (US$718,600).<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraq's operation to liberate Mosul receives international support amid humanitarian concerns |url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1012371.shtml |accessdate=19 October 2016 |work=Global Times |agency=Xinhua |date=19 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019212044/http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1012371.shtml |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Mosul refugees VOA 03.jpg|thumb|A displaced Sunni Arab family from Mosul]]\nThe [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) said it had trained 90 Iraqi medics in \"mass casualty management\" as part of its preparations for the Mosul operation, with a special focus on responding to chemical attacks, AP reported. ISIL has previously used chemical weapons in attacks on Iraqi and coalition forces, and there are fears that it might do so again inside Mosul, where more than a million civilians live.<ref name=\"bbc1027\"/>\n\nOn 3 November, Kurdish and UN aid workers said that more than 40,000 refugees had fled to Kurdistan in the first few weeks of fighting. Ten new refugee camps have been built in the [[Dohuk Governorate]], [[Erbil Governorate]] and in the town of Khazir.<ref>{{cite news |title=Refugee arrivals in Kurdistan exceed 40,000; greater numbers expected in coming days |url=http://rudaw.net/english/kurdistan/03112016 |accessdate=3 November 2016 |publisher=Rudaw Media Network |date=3 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104025732/http://rudaw.net/english/kurdistan/03112016 |archivedate=4 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> According to the United Nations and UNICEF, 22,000 people had been displaced, including more than 9,000 children.<ref>{{cite news |title=The Latest: White House: IS propaganda can't change reality |url=https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2016-11-03/the-latest-iraqi-forces-in-mosul-fight-face-suicide-bombers |accessdate=4 November 2016 |work=U.S. News & World Report |date=3 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104141429/http://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2016-11-03/the-latest-iraqi-forces-in-mosul-fight-face-suicide-bombers |archivedate=4 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 November, the [[United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees]] (UNHCR) stated that 33,996 people had been displaced from the [[Mosul District]]. 63 percent of families are missing civil documentation and 21 percent of families are headed by a female. The previous 48 hours saw a 53 percent increase in displacement.<ref name=\"unhcr1109\" /> The following day, WHO announced it had established 82 \"rapid response teams\" to prepare for possible concerns among civilians fleeing Mosul, including health epidemics such as [[cholera]], and exposure to chemicals and smoke from burning oil wells.<ref>{{cite news |title=People living in 'smoke-filled hell' in areas recaptured from ISIS |url=https://www.oxfamamerica.org/press/people-living-in-smoked-filled-hell-in-areas-recaptured-from-isis-oxfam/ |accessdate=8 November 2016 |publisher=Oxfam |date=4 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161108194916/https://www.oxfamamerica.org/press/people-living-in-smoked-filled-hell-in-areas-recaptured-from-isis-oxfam/ |archivedate=8 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> A particular concern is potential disease outbreaks among young children who have not been immunized since ISIL took over the city in June 2014.<ref>{{cite news |title=The Latest: UN health agency deploys teams for Mosul exodus |url=http://www.hawaiinewsnow.com/story/33644866/the-latest-un-health-agency-deploys-teams-for-mosul-exodus |accessdate=7 November 2016 |agency=Associated Press |date=7 November 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107223110/http://www.hawaiinewsnow.com/story/33644866/the-latest-un-health-agency-deploys-teams-for-mosul-exodus |archivedate=7 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nMore than 900 Iraqi civilians have fled to the Al-Hawl refugee camp located in the [[Rojava]] region of northeastern [[Syria]], while another 700 civilians have migrated to the Turkish\u2013Iraqi borders.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://euromedmonitor.org/en/article/1516/ISIS-is-creating-humanitarian-crisis-in-Mosul--but-government/international-forces-are-contributing-to-mayhem |title=ISIS is creating humanitarian crisis in Mosul, but government/international forces are contributing to mayhem |last=Monitor |first=Euro-Med |newspaper=Euro-Mediterranean|access-date=2016-11-14 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161115132124/http://euromedmonitor.org/en/article/1516/ISIS-is-creating-humanitarian-crisis-in-Mosul--but-government/international-forces-are-contributing-to-mayhem |archivedate=15 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Context ==\n=== International reactions ===\n;{{flag|France}}:\n* [[Jean-Marc Ayrault]], France's Minister of Foreign Affairs, said on 27 October, \"We know that we will face significant challenges and it is our responsibility to face them together, alongside Iraq, while fully respecting its independence and sovereignty.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=France Diplomacy on Twitter |url=https://twitter.com/francediplo_EN/status/791678626970365952 |accessdate=7 November 2016 |publisher=Twitter |date=27 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161229093250/https://twitter.com/francediplo_EN/status/791678626970365952 |archivedate=29 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* President [[Emmanuel Macron]] congratulated Iraqi forces and tweeted on 9 July 2017: \"Mosul liberated from Daesh. Homage from France to all those, with our troops, who contributed to this victory.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Battle for Mosul: Emmanuel Macron hails Iraqi troops after city freed from Islamic State |url=http://www.firstpost.com/world/battle-for-mosul-emmanuel-macron-hails-iraqi-troops-after-city-freed-from-islamic-state-3794219.html |accessdate=12 July 2017 |work=FirstPost |date=9 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170709172428/http://www.firstpost.com/world/battle-for-mosul-emmanuel-macron-hails-iraqi-troops-after-city-freed-from-islamic-state-3794219.html |archivedate=9 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n;{{flag|Lebanon}}:\n* Lebanese Foreign Ministry on 10 July 2017 called for intensified regional efforts to contain the spread of terrorism \"from one nest to another\" and hailed the recapture of the city as a \"great victory\" for the Iraqi people.<ref>{{cite news |title=The Latest: Lebanon welcomes liberation of Mosul from IS |url=http://www.miamiherald.com/news/nation-world/article160656194.html |accessdate=7 November 2016 |work=Miami Herald |date=11 July 2017 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170711111435/http://www.miamiherald.com/news/nation-world/article160656194.html |archivedate=11 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Lebanon Welcomes Liberation Of Mosul From IS |url=http://www.kurv.com/lebanon-welcomes-liberation-of-mosul-from-is/ |accessdate=11 July 2017 |work=Kurv |date=11 July 2017}}{{dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes}}</ref>\n;{{flag|Russia}}:\n* President [[Vladimir Putin]] on 17 October said: \"We hope that our American partners, and in this case our French partners as well, will act selectively and do everything to minimise \u2014 and even better, to rule out \u2014 civilian casualties.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Osborne |first1=Samuel |title=Putin urges the West to avoid civilian casualties in Iraq |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/russia-putin-isis-mosul-civilian-deaths-comments-after-aleppo-bombing-a7365236.html |accessdate=7 November 2016 |work=The Independent |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107221022/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/russia-putin-isis-mosul-civilian-deaths-comments-after-aleppo-bombing-a7365236.html |archivedate=7 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n;{{flag|Turkey}}:\n* Turkish President [[Recep Tayyip Erdogan]] insisted unsuccessfully on a Turkish role in the Battle for Mosul (see [[Battle of Mosul (2016)#Turkey|Turkish involvement]] below).\n* On 26 October, [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Turkey)|Turkish FM]] [[Mevl\u00fct \u00c7avu\u015fo\u011flu]] said \"Fighting ISIL is necessary, but the process after ISIL must be planned carefully.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://aa.com.tr/en/todays-headlines/turkey-will-not-forsake-tal-afars-turkmen-cavusoglu/672817 |title=Turkey will not forsake Tal Afar's Turkmen: Cavusoglu |agency=Anadolu Agency |date=26 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103220934/http://aa.com.tr/en/todays-headlines/turkey-will-not-forsake-tal-afars-turkmen-cavusoglu/672817 |archivedate=3 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* Exiled former Iraqi vice-president [[Tariq al-Hashimi]] condemned the cooperation between the United States and Iran during the course of the conflict, he also condemned the Shia dominated Popular Mobilization Force for taking part in the battle of Mosul and urged the international community to intervene to not allow them to take part in the operation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=82&v=LG2XoPyt1l4|title=Former vice president of Iraq Tariq al-Hashimi talks Mosul and DAESH|date=26 September 2016|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n;{{flag|United States}}:\n* President [[Barack Obama]] said on 18 October, \"Mosul will be a difficult fight and there will be advances and setbacks. I am confident, just as ISIL has been defeated in communities across Iraq, ISIL will be defeated in Mosul as well, and that will be another step toward their ultimate destruction.\"\n* Secretary of Defense [[Ashton Carter]] said on 16 October, in a statement,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gaouette |first1=Nicole |title=Obama: Mosul will be 'difficult fight' |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/18/politics/obama-well-defeat-isis-in-mosul-but-it-will-be-difficult-fight/index.html |accessdate=7 November 2016 |publisher=CNN |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107160957/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/18/politics/obama-well-defeat-isis-in-mosul-but-it-will-be-difficult-fight/index.html |archivedate=7 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> \"This is a decisive moment in the campaign to deliver ISIL a lasting defeat.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.defense.gov/News/News-Releases/News-Release-View/Article/975156/statement-by-secretary-of-defense-ash-carter-on-iraqi-announcement-regarding-mo |title=Statement by Secretary of Defense Ash Carter on Iraqi Announcement Reg |publisher=U.S. Department of Defense|access-date=1 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105045042/http://www.defense.gov/News/News-Releases/News-Release-View/Article/975156/statement-by-secretary-of-defense-ash-carter-on-iraqi-announcement-regarding-mo |archivedate=5 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* Lieutenant General [[Stephen Townsend]], the commander of the Combined Joint Task Force-Operation Inherent Resolve, said on 29 March 2017, \"Our enemy, ISIS, are evil and murderous butchers, engaged in purposeful and mass slaughter.\" \"To put things in a little perspective for you, this is the most significant urban combat to take place since World War II; it is tough and brutal. House by house, block by block fights.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.express.co.uk/news/world/785469/battle-for-mosul-latest-soldiers-islamic-state-isis-brutal-street-fighting |title=Battle for Mosul: Soldiers facing most brutal street fighting since WWII to defeat ISIS |work=Express |accessdate=29 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170329193727/http://www.express.co.uk/news/world/785469/battle-for-mosul-latest-soldiers-islamic-state-isis-brutal-street-fighting |archive-date=29 March 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n;{{flag|Iran}}:\n* Rear Admiral [[Ali Shamkhani]], the Secretary of Iran's [[Supreme National Security Council]], condemned the U.S.-led coalition [[2017 Mosul airstrike|airstrikes in Mosul]] in March 2017 which killed more than 200 civilians and accused the United States of committing [[war crime]]s, saying: \"This war crime is similar to the behavior of Daesh [Islamic State] and other Takfiri groups in targeting civilians and innocent people and should be urgently addressed in courts of justice.\"<ref>\"[http://www.presstv.com/Detail/2017/03/26/515669/Iran-Shamkhani-Mosul-airstrikes-US-crimes-- Iran urges 'war crime' hearing into US killings in Mosul] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170410213801/http://www.presstv.com/Detail/2017/03/26/515669/Iran-Shamkhani-Mosul-airstrikes-US-crimes-- |date=10 April 2017}}.\" Press TV. 26 March 2017.</ref>\n\n=== Other ===\n{{flagicon image|Flag of Iraq (1991-2004).svg}} '''[[Iraqi Baath Party]]'''\n* Secretary General of the Iraqi Baath Party and former Vice-Chairman of the [[Iraqi Revolutionary Command Council]] and current leader of the [[Army of the Men of the Naqshbandi Order]], [[Izzat Ibrahim al-Douri]] released a statement in early 2018 commemorating the anniversary of the Baath Party's foundation, in the statement he condemned the Iraqi Government and the military action taken in Iraq against ISIL calling on \"Baathist Youth\" to continue to rebel against the Iraqi Government, he also referred to Iranian forces and allied paramilitary groups as [[Safavids]]. Douri also stated he had great hope in [[Saudi Arabia]] to help Iraq against Iran's influence, in the statement Douri said that Iraqi Prime Minister Haider al-Abadi personally destroyed [[Tikrit]], Mosul, [[Fallujah]] and other Sunni majority cities in northern Iraq as part of their war against ISIL and that [[Badr Organization]] was directly under Iranian control. He also threatened to go to war with the Iraqi government and allied Shiite militias.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/080420181 |title=Archived copy |access-date=17 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180926122202/http://www.rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/080420181 |archive-date=26 September 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2018/07/16/VIDEO-Iraqi-protesters-burn-pictures-of-Khomeini-in-Basra.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=17 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180724010843/https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2018/07/16/VIDEO-Iraqi-protesters-burn-pictures-of-Khomeini-in-Basra.html |archive-date=24 July 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== Media coverage and social media ===\nSeveral media outlets including [[Al Jazeera]] and [[Channel 4]] live streamed the first day's battle on Facebook, a first in war coverage.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Mezzofiore |first1=Gianluca |title=The battle for Mosul is being live streamed on Facebook |url=http://mashable.com/2016/10/17/mosul-offensive-facebook-live/ |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=Mashable |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018211708/http://mashable.com/2016/10/17/mosul-offensive-facebook-live/ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Morley |first1=Nicole |title=The battle to defeat Isis in Mosul is being livestreamed on Facebook |url=http://metro.co.uk/2016/10/17/the-battle-to-defeat-isis-in-mosul-is-being-livestreamed-on-facebook-6197208/ |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=Metro |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018214150/http://metro.co.uk/2016/10/17/the-battle-to-defeat-isis-in-mosul-is-being-livestreamed-on-facebook-6197208/ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Paton |first1=Callum |title=Battle for Mosul: War broadcast live on Facebook as Iraqi Kurdish forces advance on Isis stronghold |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/battle-mosul-watch-live-stream-iraqi-forces-start-offensive-isis-stronghold-1586793 |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=International Business Times |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018211526/http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/battle-mosul-watch-live-stream-iraqi-forces-start-offensive-isis-stronghold-1586793 |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Additional live video feeds were available on YouTube and the streaming app [[Periscope (app)|Periscope]]. Iraqi and Kurdish officials are also joining in on social media using the [[hashtag]] #FreeMosul.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Chiel |first1=Ethan |title=The Battle to Retake a City From ISIS Is Being Livestreamed |url=http://fusion.net/story/358656/mosul-livestream/ |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Fusion |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018234258/http://fusion.net/story/358656/mosul-livestream/ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Brendan Gauthier, assistant editor of ''[[Salon (website)|Salon]]'', noted that given ISIL's slick campaigns on social media, \"It's only appropriate then that the Iraqi military's effort to reclaim Mosul from the PR machine turned extremist group be live-streamed.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gauthier |first1=Brendan |title=The battle for Mosul is live-streamed: Al Jazeera English live feed documents the potential fall of ISIS |url=http://www.salon.com/2016/10/17/the-battle-for-mosul-live-streamed-al-jazeera-english-live-feed-documents-the-potential-fall-of-isis/ |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Salon |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020041437/http://www.salon.com/2016/10/17/the-battle-for-mosul-live-streamed-al-jazeera-english-live-feed-documents-the-potential-fall-of-isis/ |archivedate=20 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 October, several Iraqi media outlets established the National Media Alliance to support journalists reporting on the battle. The groups include both government-run and private media, including [[Al Iraqiya]] and [[Al Sumaria]]. The alliance provides technical and journalistic services, including a joint operations newsroom. It was formed to counter ISIL propaganda and foster cooperation among the various media groups in order to reduce chaos and improve safety. Journalist Walid al-Tai told [[Al-Monitor]], \"One of the reasons behind the establishment of the alliance is to avoid any chaotic media coverage of the battle as every media and military institution is sending its correspondents to battlefronts. This leads to conflict in the coverage of the fighting and a greater number of casualties among journalists.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi journalists join hands under National Media Alliance |url=http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2016/11/iraq-media-journalists-mosul.html |accessdate=8 November 2016 |work=Al-Monitor |date=7 November 2016 |language=en-us |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161108170357/http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2016/11/iraq-media-journalists-mosul.html |archivedate=8 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nJournalist Mustafa Habib reported that Iraqi citizens are coordinating efforts on Facebook and Twitter to counter ISIL propaganda, such as fake photos and videos, that may be used to intimidate locals in Mosul. A communications department of a Shia militia also announced it would be contributing to a social media campaign, and that 500 Iraqi journalists were [[embedded journalism|embedded]] with the militias surrounding Mosul to report updates.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Habib |first1=Mustafa |title=100,000+ Iraqi Civilians Fighting The Battle For Mosul Online |url=http://www.niqash.org/en/articles/society/5381/100000-Iraqi-Civilians-Fighting-The-Battle-For-Mosul-Online.htm |accessdate=19 October 2016 |work=Niqash |date=19 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020040130/http://www.niqash.org/en/articles/society/5381/100000-Iraqi-Civilians-Fighting-The-Battle-For-Mosul-Online.htm |archivedate=20 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 October 2016, ''[[The New Yorker]]''{{'}}s [[Robin Wright (author)|Robin Wright]] interviewed the anonymous self-described historian ''[[Mosul Eye]]'', a purported Mosuli who has blogged from the city about life in Mosul under ISIL despite death threats from the group. Responding to Wright's questions, ''Mosul Eye'' estimated the size and make-up of ISIL's force in Mosul, hopes for the future (\"gain back power over the city\" with help of \"an international trusteeship to protect Mosul\"), and the level of support for ISIL inside Mosul (\"There is no support for ISIL in Mosul. They are left only with weapons that they will use to kill themselves once the liberating forces make the decision to raid the city.\").<ref name=\"auto1\" />\n\n=== {{anchor|Turkey}} Turkish involvement ===\nThe involvement of Turkey in the operation has considerably strained its relations with Iraq.<ref name=\"aj1023\">{{cite news |title=Battle for Mosul: Turkey confirms military involvement |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/10/battle-mosul-turkey-confirms-military-involvement-161023144053661.html |accessdate=23 October 2016 |publisher=Al Jazeera |date=23 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161024024338/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/10/battle-mosul-turkey-confirms-military-involvement-161023144053661.html |archivedate=24 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Turkey has 1,500 to 2,000 soldiers in Iraq,<ref name=\"MathieuKodmani1016\">{{cite news |last1=Mathieu |first1=Luc |last2=Kodmani |first2=Hala |title=\"Le gouvernement irakien n'a pas de plan pour le jour d'apr\u00e8s\" |url=http://www.liberation.fr/planete/2016/10/16/le-gouvernement-irakien-n-a-pas-de-plan-pour-le-jour-d-apres_1522350 |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Lib\u00e9ration.fr |date=16 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018153917/http://www.liberation.fr/planete/2016/10/16/le-gouvernement-irakien-n-a-pas-de-plan-pour-le-jour-d-apres_1522350 |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> including 500 Turkish soldiers deployed to a base near [[Bashiqa]], where they trained 1,500 Iraqi Sunni volunteers, mainly [[Iraqi Turkmen|Turkmens]], and Arabs to recapture Mosul from ISIL.<ref>{{cite news |title=Offensive sur Mossoul: Washington tente de d\u00e9samorcer les tensions Turquie-Irak |url=http://www.lorientlejour.com/article/1012257/offensive-sur-mossoul-washington-tente-de-desamorcer-les-tensions-turquie-irak.html |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=L'Orient-Le Jour |date=12 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018201453/http://www.lorientlejour.com/article/1012257/offensive-sur-mossoul-washington-tente-de-desamorcer-les-tensions-turquie-irak.html |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Reconqu\u00eate de Mossoul: la Turquie entend peser sur le champ de bataille irakien |url=http://www.rfi.fr/moyen-orient/20161017-irak-reconquete-mossoul-turquie-peser-bataille-kurdes-chiites |accessdate=18 October 2016 |publisher=[[Radio France Internationale|RFI]] |date=17 October 2016 |language=fr-FR |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018001553/http://www.rfi.fr/moyen-orient/20161017-irak-reconquete-mossoul-turquie-peser-bataille-kurdes-chiites |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Turkey's participation is against the wishes of the Iraqi government, which has said the Turks are violating Iraq's sovereignty. Turkey has refused to withdraw its forces.<ref name=\"aj1023\" /> Turkish President [[Recep Tayyip Erdogan]] told the Turkish parliament on 1 October, \"We will play a role in the Mosul liberation operation and no one can prevent us from participating,\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lister |first1=Tim |last2=Alkhshali |first2=Hamdi |title=Stakes high for Iraq as Mosul offensive looms |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/04/middleeast/iraq-mosul-campaign-analysis-lister/ |accessdate=18 October 2016 |publisher=CNN |date=4 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017100051/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/04/middleeast/iraq-mosul-campaign-analysis-lister/ |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> and said their presence was to ensure that Mosul did not fall to Kurdish or Shia control and become a threat to Turkey.<ref>{{cite news |title=Erdogan: Iraq unable to liberate Mosul on its own |url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2016/10/15/Erdogan-Iraq-cannot-handle-Mosul-assault-alone.html |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Al Arabiya |date=15 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018002427/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2016/10/15/Erdogan-Iraq-cannot-handle-Mosul-assault-alone.html |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/24/world/middleeast/turkeys-push-to-join-battle-for-mosul-inflames-tension-with-iraq.html |title=Turkey's Push to Join Battle for Mosul Inflames Tension With Iraq |work=The New York Times |date=23 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026234159/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/24/world/middleeast/turkeys-push-to-join-battle-for-mosul-inflames-tension-with-iraq.html |archivedate=26 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Turkey's presence was criticized by Kurds in northern Iraq,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hesen |first1=R\u00eabaz |title=People of South Kurdistan: Turkey after a permanent occupation in Mosul |url=https://anfenglish.com/kurdistan/people-of-south-kurdistan-turkey-after-a-permanent-occupation-in-mosul |accessdate=18 October 2016 |agency=[[Firat News Agency]] |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019032915/https://anfenglish.com/kurdistan/people-of-south-kurdistan-turkey-after-a-permanent-occupation-in-mosul |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> and thousands of protestors demonstrated at the Turkish Embassy in [[Baghdad]] on 18 October, demanding Turkish forces withdraw from Iraq.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0622\u0644\u0627\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0627\u0642\u064a\u064a\u0646 \u064a\u062a\u0638\u0627\u0647\u0631\u0648\u0646 \u0644\u0644\u0645\u0637\u0627\u0644\u0628\u0629 \u0628\u062e\u0631\u0648\u062c \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0631\u0643\u064a\u0629 (Thousands of Iraqis Demonstrate to Demand the Withdrawal of Turkish Troops) |url=http://www.alhurra.com/a/iraq-protests-turkish-embassy/330392.html |accessdate=18 October 2016 |publisher=\u0642\u0646\u0627\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0631\u0629 (Al Hurra) |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020122928/http://www.alhurra.com/a/iraq-protests-turkish-embassy/330392.html |archivedate=20 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The United States has reportedly attempted to persuade Iraq to cooperate with Turkey on the Mosul offensive.<ref>{{cite news |last=Baldor |first=Lolita C. |title=Carter says Turkey should play role in Mosul fight |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/carter-to-meet-with-turkey-leaders-stress-iraqi-sovereignty/2016/10/21/b8865da6-9756-11e6-9cae-2a3574e296a6_story.html |accessdate=23 October 2016 |work=The Washington Post |agency=Associated Press |date=22 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161022185255/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/carter-to-meet-with-turkey-leaders-stress-iraqi-sovereignty/2016/10/21/b8865da6-9756-11e6-9cae-2a3574e296a6_story.html |archivedate=22 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Al-Abadi declined the offer of Turkish assistance, saying, \"I know that the Turks want to participate. We tell them thank you, this is something the Iraqis will handle and the Iraqis will liberate Mosul and the rest of the territories.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Baldor |first1=Lolita C. |title=Iraqi leader resists US push for Turkish role in Mosul fight |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/the_americas/us-defense-secretary-carter-arrives-in-iraq/2016/10/22/d6242c72-9827-11e6-9cae-2a3574e296a6_story.html |accessdate=23 October 2016 |work=The Washington Post |agency=Associated Press |date=22 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161023185826/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/the_americas/us-defense-secretary-carter-arrives-in-iraq/2016/10/22/d6242c72-9827-11e6-9cae-2a3574e296a6_story.html |archivedate=23 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> However, on 23 October, Turkish Prime Minister [[Binali Y\u0131ld\u0131r\u0131m]] announced Turkish troops had fired on ISIL positions near Mosul after requests for assistance from the Peshmerga.<ref name=\"aj1023\" />\n\nThe situation between Turkey and Iraq escalated on 1 November, the day Iraqi forces entered Mosul. Turkey announced it was sending tanks and artillery from Ankara to [[Silopi]] near the Iraqi border. Turkey's Minister of Defense [[Fikri I\u015f\u0131k]] said the deployment was a move to \"prepare for \"important developments\" in the region and be ready for any possible scenario\" and stated that \"further action can be taken if Turkey's red lines are crossed\" warning Shi'ite militias and [[PKK]] not to \"terrorize\" and take hold of [[Iraqi Turkmens|Iraqi Turkmen]]-majority regions in the area.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.aljazeera.com.tr/haber/savunma-bakani-sinirda |publisher=[[Al Jazeera T\u00fcrk]] |title=Milli Savunma Bakan\u0131 Fikri I\u015f\u0131k s\u0131n\u0131rda (''National Defence Minister Fikri I\u015f\u0131k on the border'') |date=2 November 2016 |accessdate=4 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103165544/http://www.aljazeera.com.tr/haber/savunma-bakani-sinirda |archivedate=3 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.aljazeera.com.tr/haber/isik-kirmizi-cizgilerimiz-asilirsa |publisher=[[Al Jazeera T\u00fcrk]] |title=K\u0131rm\u0131z\u0131 \u00e7izgilerimiz a\u015f\u0131l\u0131rsa... (''If our red lines are crossed...'') |date=2 November 2016 |accessdate=5 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104234135/http://www.aljazeera.com.tr/haber/isik-kirmizi-cizgilerimiz-asilirsa |archivedate=4 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Iraq-Turkey tension rises amid battle for Mosul |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/11/iraq-turkey-tension-rises-battle-mosul-161102062236590.html |accessdate=2 November 2016 |publisher=Al Jazeera |date=2 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103140950/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/11/iraq-turkey-tension-rises-battle-mosul-161102062236590.html |archivedate=3 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Prime Minister Al-Abadi warned Turkey not to \"invade\" Iraq, predicting war if they did. Al-Abadi, addressing journalists in Baghdad, said, \"We warn Turkey if they want to enter Iraq, they will end up becoming fragmented... We do not want to fight Turkey. We do not want a confrontation with Turkey. God forbid, even if we engage in war with them, the Turks will pay a heavy price. They will be damaged. Yes, we too will be damaged, but whenever a country fights a neighboring country, there will be no winner, both will end up losing.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Abadi warns Turkey: Don't enter Iraq or you will pay the price |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/011120162 |accessdate=2 November 2016 |publisher=Rudaw Media Agency |date=1 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161102160035/http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/011120162 |archivedate=2 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 November, Iraq rejected Turkey's proposal to continue running the Bashiqa military camp, no matter if it were formally transferred under the auspices of the coalition forces, and suggested that Turkey hand over control of the camp to Iraq's central government.<ref>{{cite news |title=Baghdad proposes Ankara handover of Bashiqa camp to Iraq |url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/baghdad-proposes-ankara-handover-of-bashiqa-camp-to-iraq.aspx?pageID=238&nID=106016&NewsCatID=352 |work=Hurriyet Daily News |date=12 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161112220005/http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/baghdad-proposes-ankara-handover-of-bashiqa-camp-to-iraq.aspx?pageID=238&nid=106016&NewsCatID=352 |archivedate=12 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n== Violation of the laws of war ==\n{{See also|Eddie Gallagher (Navy SEAL)|2017 Mosul massacre}}\nIn February 2017, [[Human Rights Watch]] issued a report regarding the violation of the laws of war in [[Iraq]]. According to the report, Islamic State fighters occupied Al-Salam Hospital in [[Mosul]] in June 2014, and put the staff and the patients at risk of attacks. During the Battle of Mosul, seven Iraqi soldiers' corpses were dragged through the streets, and the bodies of three soldiers were hanged from a bridge in the city. As the report mentioned, ISIL fighters occupied a clinic in the town of [[Hamam al-Alil|Hammam al-Alil]], which was then hit by an airstrike without warning on 18 October, killing at least eight civilians. Previously, they occupied other clinics in other towns controlled by the Islamic State fighters in Iraq, as well operating offices in all the medical facilities in the Republican, Ibn Sina, al-Salam, and Mosul General Hospitals.\n\nHuman Rights Watch has also accused the [[Iraqi security forces|Iraqi Security Forces]] and [[Popular Mobilization Forces]] of dragging the bodies of alleged ISIL fighters in the town of [[Qayyarah]] and in the city of [[Fallujah]], after Iraqi forces took eastern Mosul on 24 January 2017.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2017/02/08/iraq-mosul-battle-isis-used-hospital-base |title=Iraq: In Mosul Battle, ISIS Used Hospital Base |date=2017-02-08 |publisher=Human Rights Watch|access-date=2017-02-14 |language=en |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170215030113/https://www.hrw.org/news/2017/02/08/iraq-mosul-battle-isis-used-hospital-base |archivedate=15 February 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> They warned that allowing [[Popular Mobilization Forces]] to conduct the screenings of men and boys fleeing Mosul for having fought for ISIL would have \"dire human rights consequences.\"<ref name=HRW>{{Cite news |url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2017/03/19/where-are-mosuls-detainees-going |title=Where are Mosul's Detainees Going?|access-date=2017-03-21 |language=en |url-status=live |publisher=HUman RIghts Watch |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170322203800/https://www.hrw.org/news/2017/03/19/where-are-mosuls-detainees-going |archivedate=22 March 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nHuman Rights Watch warned that [[Popular Mobilization Forces]] were poorly trained to conduct these screenings. They argued that the irregular nature of screening and detention practices and isolation of detainees in custody risk abuse of the detainees, including arbitrary detention and enforced disappearances. Despite assurances from the Iraqi government that the [[Popular Mobilization Forces|PMF]] would not screen detainees in Mosul, an observer reported that three PMF groups were seen at a screening site on 11 March 2017: [[Hezbollah Brigades]], [[Liwa Abu al-Fadhal al-Abbas|al-Abbas Brigades]], and [[Kata'ib al-Imam Ali|Imam Ali Battalions]].<ref name=HRW />\n\nOn 11 July 2017, a report was published by Amnesty International, accusing both sides of violating international laws in the battle, about a day after victory was declared by Iraqi forces. The report accused Iraqi forces and the US-led Coalition of carrying out a series of unlawful attacks in west Mosul, using heavily on [[Improvised Rocket Assisted Munitions]] (IRAMs), explosive weapons and the failure of government to take necessary precautions to prevent the loss of civilian lives and in some cases including disproportionate attacks.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/07/amnesty-sides-violated-international-law-mosul-170711090407536.html |title=Amnesty: All sides violated international law in Mosul|access-date=2017-07-11 |language=en |url-status=live |publisher=Al Jazeera |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170711133102/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/07/amnesty-sides-violated-international-law-mosul-170711090407536.html |archivedate=11 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nAccording to a report published by [[UN Assistance Mission for Iraq]] and the [[Office of the UN High Commissioner for Human Rights]] in November 2017, at least 2,521 civilians were killed in the battle, mostly because of ISIL including executions of at least 741. It also recorded 461 civilian deaths in airstrikes during the most intensive phase from 19 February. It noted that ISIL had announced in November 2016 that civilians under government-held areas would be considered \"legitimate targets\" as they didn't fight the pro-government forces. It also called upon Iraqi authorities to investigate alleged violations and human rights abuses by Iraqi security forces during the battle.<ref>{{Cite news|publisher=UN|url=http://www.un.org/apps/news/story.asp?NewsID=58017#.Wf6j3xlX7qA|title=UN report concludes ISIL committed 'international crimes' during Mosul battle|access-date=2017-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171105064633/http://www.un.org/apps/news/story.asp?NewsID=58017#.Wf6j3xlX7qA|archive-date=5 November 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nAn [[Associated Press]] investigation that cross-referenced independent databases from non-governmental organizations, claimed that 9,000\u201311,000 residents of Mosul were killed in the battle. It blamed airstrikes and shellings by Iraqi forces and anti-ISIL coalition of being responsible for at least 3,200 civilian deaths. The coalition on the other hand has acknowledged responsibility for 326 deaths. ISIL was held responsible for killing one third of the civilians out of the death toll. AP also obtained a list of 9,606 people killed in the battle from Mosul's morgue while Iraqi Prime Minister Haider al-Abadi had claimed 1,260 deaths. 4,200 were confirmed to be civilians. Names of ISIL fighters and casualties from outside Mosul were discarded by the investigation. It stated however that some ISIL members might be among the remaining 6,000.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/9000-died-battle-islamic-state-group-mosul-51900465|title=Mosul is a graveyard: Final IS battle kills 9,000 civilians|agency=Associated Press|access-date=2017-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171225063540/http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/9000-died-battle-islamic-state-group-mosul-51900465|archive-date=25 December 2017|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Asia|War}}\n{{col-begin|width=100%}}{{col-break}}\n* [[Battle of Aleppo (2012\u20132016)]]\n* [[Siege of Deir ez-Zor (2014\u201317)]]\n* [[Siege of Koban\u00ee]]\n* [[Tell Abyad offensive]]\n* [[Battle of Ramadi (2015\u201316)]]\n* [[Nineveh Plains offensive]]\n{{col-break}}\n* [[Battle of al-Bab]]\n* [[Palmyra offensive (December 2016)]]\n* [[Battle of Marawi]]\n* [[Central Syria campaign (2017)]]\n* [[2017 Mayadin offensive]]\n* [[Battle of Baghuz Fawqani]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Battle of Mosul}}\n* [http://syriancivilwarmap.com/ Interactive Syria and Iraq map with current Mosul military situation]\n* [http://isis.liveuamap.com/ ISIS Map]\n* [https://www.rt.com/mosulsos/ MosulSOS\u2014RT Trends]\n* [http://www.cnn.com/2016/11/05/middleeast/iraq-inside-mosul-battle/ CNN report \u2013 28 hours: Leading the Mosul attack, under fire then trapped]\n* [https://www.google.com/maps/d/viewer?mid=1b8Nfs3pWEKxFotW5_91engr9n8s&ll=36.36518764353825%2C43.09335683408199&z=13 Map of all restored Mosul city districts \u2013 with timeline notes attached for each district], published by Google Maps\n* {{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/08/01/world/middleeast/mosul-isis-survivors-rights.html|title=In Mosul, Revealing the Last ISIS Stronghold|author=Ivor Prickett|publisher=The New York Times|date=1 August 2017|accessdate=5 November 2017}}\n\n{{Military intervention against ISIL}}\n{{Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Battle of Mosul (2016\u201317)}}\n[[Category:Battles involving Canada|Mosul (2016\u201317)]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 2016]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 2017]]\n[[Category: